74 public:
75  using DeclContextDesc = std::pair<Decl::Kind, StringRef>;

77  template <size_t N>
78  static constexpr DeclContextDesc MakeDeclContextDesc(Decl::Kind K,
79  const char (&Str)[N]) {
80  // FIXME: This SHOULD be able to use the StringLiteral constructor here
81  // instead, however this seems to fail with an 'invalid string literal' note
82  // on the correct constructor in some build configurations. We need to
83  // figure that out before reverting this to use the StringLiteral
84  // constructor.
85  return DeclContextDesc{K, StringRef{Str, N - 1}};
86  }
87 
88  static constexpr DeclContextDesc MakeDeclContextDesc(Decl::Kind K,
89  StringRef SR) {
90  return DeclContextDesc{K, SR};
91  }

144 ExprResult Sema::ActOnSYCLBuiltinNumFieldsExpr(ParsedType PT) {
145  TypeSourceInfo *TInfo = nullptr;
146  QualType QT = GetTypeFromParser(PT, &TInfo);
147  assert(TInfo && "couldn't get type info from a type from the parser?");
148  SourceLocation TypeLoc = TInfo->getTypeLoc().getBeginLoc();
149 
150  return BuildSYCLBuiltinNumFieldsExpr(TypeLoc, QT);
151 }
152 
153 ExprResult Sema::BuildSYCLBuiltinNumFieldsExpr(SourceLocation Loc,
154  QualType SourceTy) {
155  if (!SourceTy->isDependentType()) {
156  if (RequireCompleteType(Loc, SourceTy,
157  diag::err_sycl_type_trait_requires_complete_type,
158  /*__builtin_num_fields*/ 0))
159  return ExprError();
160 
161  if (!SourceTy->isRecordType()) {
162  Diag(Loc, diag::err_sycl_type_trait_requires_record_type)
163  << /*__builtin_num_fields*/ 0;
164  return ExprError();
165  }
166  }
167  return new (Context)
168  SYCLBuiltinNumFieldsExpr(Loc, SourceTy, Context.getSizeType());
169 }

177  return BuildSYCLBuiltinFieldTypeExpr(TypeLoc, QT, Idx);

180 ExprResult Sema::BuildSYCLBuiltinFieldTypeExpr(SourceLocation Loc,
181  QualType SourceTy, Expr *Idx) {
182  // If the expression appears in an evaluated context, we want to give an
183  // error so that users don't attempt to use the value of this expression.
184  if (!isUnevaluatedContext()) {
185  Diag(Loc, diag::err_sycl_builtin_type_trait_evaluated)
186  << /*__builtin_field_type*/ 0;
187  return ExprError();
188  }
189 
190  // We may not be able to calculate the field type (the source type may be a
191  // dependent type), so use the source type as a basic fallback. This will
192  // ensure that the AST node will have a dependent type that gets resolved
193  // later to the real type.
194  QualType FieldTy = SourceTy;
195  ExprValueKind ValueKind = VK_PRValue;
196  if (!SourceTy->isDependentType()) {
197  if (RequireCompleteType(Loc, SourceTy,
198  diag::err_sycl_type_trait_requires_complete_type,
199  /*__builtin_field_type*/ 1))
200  return ExprError();
201 
202  if (!SourceTy->isRecordType()) {
203  Diag(Loc, diag::err_sycl_type_trait_requires_record_type)
204  << /*__builtin_field_type*/ 1;
205  return ExprError();
206  }
207 
208  if (!Idx->isValueDependent()) {
209  Optional<llvm::APSInt> IdxVal = Idx->getIntegerConstantExpr(Context);
210  if (IdxVal) {
211  RecordDecl *RD = SourceTy->getAsRecordDecl();
212  assert(RD && "Record type but no record decl?");
213  int64_t Index = IdxVal->getExtValue();
214 
215  if (Index < 0) {
216  Diag(Idx->getExprLoc(),
217  diag::err_sycl_type_trait_requires_nonnegative_index)
218  << /*fields*/ 0;
219  return ExprError();
220  }
221 
222  // Ensure that the index is within range.
223  int64_t NumFields = std::distance(RD->field_begin(), RD->field_end());
224  if (Index >= NumFields) {
225  Diag(Idx->getExprLoc(),
226  diag::err_sycl_builtin_type_trait_index_out_of_range)
227  << toString(*IdxVal, 10) << SourceTy << /*fields*/ 0;
228  return ExprError();
229  }
230  const FieldDecl *FD = *std::next(RD->field_begin(), Index);
231  FieldTy = FD->getType();
232 
233  // If the field type was a reference type, adjust it now.
234  if (FieldTy->isLValueReferenceType()) {
235  ValueKind = VK_LValue;
236  FieldTy = FieldTy.getNonReferenceType();
237  } else if (FieldTy->isRValueReferenceType()) {
238  ValueKind = VK_XValue;
239  FieldTy = FieldTy.getNonReferenceType();
240  }
241  }
242  }
243  }
244  return new (Context)
245  SYCLBuiltinFieldTypeExpr(Loc, SourceTy, Idx, FieldTy, ValueKind);
246 }

257 ExprResult Sema::BuildSYCLBuiltinNumBasesExpr(SourceLocation Loc,
258  QualType SourceTy) {
259  if (!SourceTy->isDependentType()) {
260  if (RequireCompleteType(Loc, SourceTy,
261  diag::err_sycl_type_trait_requires_complete_type,
262  /*__builtin_num_bases*/ 2))
263  return ExprError();
264 
265  if (!SourceTy->isRecordType()) {
266  Diag(Loc, diag::err_sycl_type_trait_requires_record_type)
267  << /*__builtin_num_bases*/ 2;
268  return ExprError();
269  }
270  }
271  return new (Context)
272  SYCLBuiltinNumBasesExpr(Loc, SourceTy, Context.getSizeType());

284 ExprResult Sema::BuildSYCLBuiltinBaseTypeExpr(SourceLocation Loc,
285  QualType SourceTy, Expr *Idx) {
286  // If the expression appears in an evaluated context, we want to give an
287  // error so that users don't attempt to use the value of this expression.
288  if (!isUnevaluatedContext()) {
289  Diag(Loc, diag::err_sycl_builtin_type_trait_evaluated)
290  << /*__builtin_base_type*/ 1;
291  return ExprError();
292  }
293 
294  // We may not be able to calculate the base type (the source type may be a
295  // dependent type), so use the source type as a basic fallback. This will
296  // ensure that the AST node will have a dependent type that gets resolved
297  // later to the real type.
298  QualType BaseTy = SourceTy;
299  if (!SourceTy->isDependentType()) {
300  if (RequireCompleteType(Loc, SourceTy,
301  diag::err_sycl_type_trait_requires_complete_type,
302  /*__builtin_base_type*/ 3))
303  return ExprError();
304 
305  if (!SourceTy->isRecordType()) {
306  Diag(Loc, diag::err_sycl_type_trait_requires_record_type)
307  << /*__builtin_base_type*/ 3;
308  return ExprError();
309  }
310 
311  if (!Idx->isValueDependent()) {
312  Optional<llvm::APSInt> IdxVal = Idx->getIntegerConstantExpr(Context);
313  if (IdxVal) {
314  CXXRecordDecl *RD = SourceTy->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
315  assert(RD && "Record type but no record decl?");
316  int64_t Index = IdxVal->getExtValue();
317 
318  if (Index < 0) {
319  Diag(Idx->getExprLoc(),
320  diag::err_sycl_type_trait_requires_nonnegative_index)
321  << /*bases*/ 1;
322  return ExprError();
323  }
324 
325  // Ensure that the index is within range.
326  if (Index >= RD->getNumBases()) {
327  Diag(Idx->getExprLoc(),
328  diag::err_sycl_builtin_type_trait_index_out_of_range)
329  << toString(*IdxVal, 10) << SourceTy << /*bases*/ 1;
330  return ExprError();
331  }
332 
333  const CXXBaseSpecifier &Spec = *std::next(RD->bases_begin(), Index);
334  BaseTy = Spec.getType();
335  }
336  }
337  }
338  return new (Context) SYCLBuiltinBaseTypeExpr(Loc, SourceTy, Idx, BaseTy);
339 }

341 // This information is from Section 4.13 of the SYCL spec
342 // https://www.khronos.org/registry/SYCL/specs/sycl-1.2.1.pdf
343 // This function returns false if the math lib function
344 // corresponding to the input builtin is not supported
345 // for SYCL
346 static bool IsSyclMathFunc(unsigned BuiltinID) {
347  switch (BuiltinID) {
348  case Builtin::BIlround:
349  case Builtin::BI__builtin_lround:
350  case Builtin::BIceill:
351  case Builtin::BI__builtin_ceill:
352  case Builtin::BIcopysignl:
353  case Builtin::BI__builtin_copysignl:
354  case Builtin::BIcosl:
355  case Builtin::BI__builtin_cosl:
356  case Builtin::BIexpl:
357  case Builtin::BI__builtin_expl:
358  case Builtin::BIexp2l:
359  case Builtin::BI__builtin_exp2l:
360  case Builtin::BIfabsl:
361  case Builtin::BI__builtin_fabsl:
362  case Builtin::BIfloorl:
363  case Builtin::BI__builtin_floorl:
364  case Builtin::BIfmal:
365  case Builtin::BI__builtin_fmal:
366  case Builtin::BIfmaxl:
367  case Builtin::BI__builtin_fmaxl:
368  case Builtin::BIfminl:
369  case Builtin::BI__builtin_fminl:
370  case Builtin::BIfmodl:
371  case Builtin::BI__builtin_fmodl:
372  case Builtin::BIlogl:
373  case Builtin::BI__builtin_logl:
374  case Builtin::BIlog10l:
375  case Builtin::BI__builtin_log10l:
376  case Builtin::BIlog2l:
377  case Builtin::BI__builtin_log2l:
378  case Builtin::BIpowl:
379  case Builtin::BI__builtin_powl:
380  case Builtin::BIrintl:
381  case Builtin::BI__builtin_rintl:
382  case Builtin::BIroundl:
383  case Builtin::BI__builtin_roundl:
384  case Builtin::BIsinl:
385  case Builtin::BI__builtin_sinl:
386  case Builtin::BIsqrtl:
387  case Builtin::BI__builtin_sqrtl:
388  case Builtin::BItruncl:
389  case Builtin::BI__builtin_truncl:
390  case Builtin::BIlroundl:
391  case Builtin::BI__builtin_lroundl:
392  case Builtin::BIlroundf:
393  case Builtin::BI__builtin_lroundf:
394  return false;
395  default:
396  break;
397  }
398  return true;
399 }

401 bool Sema::isKnownGoodSYCLDecl(const Decl *D) {
402  if (const FunctionDecl *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(D)) {
403  const IdentifierInfo *II = FD->getIdentifier();
404  // Allow to use `::printf` only for CUDA.
405  if (Context.getTargetInfo().getTriple().isNVPTX()) {
406  if (FD->getBuiltinID() == Builtin::BIprintf)
407  return true;
408  }
409  const DeclContext *DC = FD->getDeclContext();
410  if (II && II->isStr("__spirv_ocl_printf") &&
411  !FD->isDefined() &&
412  FD->getLanguageLinkage() == CXXLanguageLinkage &&
413  DC->getEnclosingNamespaceContext()->isTranslationUnit())
414  return true;
415  }
416  return false;
417 }

419 static bool isZeroSizedArray(Sema &SemaRef, QualType Ty) {
420  if (const auto *CAT = SemaRef.getASTContext().getAsConstantArrayType(Ty))
421  return CAT->getSize() == 0;
422  return false;
423 }
424 
425 static void checkSYCLType(Sema &S, QualType Ty, SourceRange Loc,
426  llvm::DenseSet<QualType> Visited,
427  SourceRange UsedAtLoc = SourceRange()) {
428  // Not all variable types are supported inside SYCL kernels,
429  // for example the quad type __float128 will cause errors in the
430  // SPIR-V translation phase.
431  // Here we check any potentially unsupported declaration and issue
432  // a deferred diagnostic, which will be emitted iff the declaration
433  // is discovered to reside in kernel code.
434  // The optional UsedAtLoc param is used when the SYCL usage is at a
435  // different location than the variable declaration and we need to
436  // inform the user of both, e.g. struct member usage vs declaration.
437 
438  bool Emitting = false;
439 
440  //--- check types ---
441 
442  // zero length arrays
443  if (isZeroSizedArray(S, Ty)) {
444  S.SYCLDiagIfDeviceCode(Loc.getBegin(), diag::err_typecheck_zero_array_size)
445  << 1;
446  Emitting = true;
447  }
448 
449  // variable length arrays
450  if (Ty->isVariableArrayType()) {
451  S.SYCLDiagIfDeviceCode(Loc.getBegin(), diag::err_vla_unsupported);
452  Emitting = true;
453  }
454 
455  // Sub-reference array or pointer, then proceed with that type.
456  while (Ty->isAnyPointerType() || Ty->isArrayType())
457  Ty = QualType{Ty->getPointeeOrArrayElementType(), 0};
458 
459  // __int128, __int128_t, __uint128_t, long double, __float128
460  if (Ty->isSpecificBuiltinType(BuiltinType::Int128) ||
461  Ty->isSpecificBuiltinType(BuiltinType::UInt128) ||
462  Ty->isSpecificBuiltinType(BuiltinType::LongDouble) ||
463  (Ty->isSpecificBuiltinType(BuiltinType::Float128) &&
464  !S.Context.getTargetInfo().hasFloat128Type())) {
465  S.SYCLDiagIfDeviceCode(Loc.getBegin(), diag::err_type_unsupported)
466  << Ty.getUnqualifiedType().getCanonicalType();
467  Emitting = true;
468  }
469 
470  if (Emitting && UsedAtLoc.isValid())
471  S.SYCLDiagIfDeviceCode(UsedAtLoc.getBegin(), diag::note_used_here);
472 
473  //--- now recurse ---
474  // Pointers complicate recursion. Add this type to Visited.
475  // If already there, bail out.
476  if (!Visited.insert(Ty).second)
477  return;
478 
479  if (const auto *ATy = dyn_cast<AttributedType>(Ty))
480  return checkSYCLType(S, ATy->getModifiedType(), Loc, Visited);
481 
482  if (const auto *RD = Ty->getAsRecordDecl()) {
483  for (const auto &Field : RD->fields())
484  checkSYCLType(S, Field->getType(), Field->getSourceRange(), Visited, Loc);
485  } else if (const auto *FPTy = dyn_cast<FunctionProtoType>(Ty)) {
486  for (const auto &ParamTy : FPTy->param_types())
487  checkSYCLType(S, ParamTy, Loc, Visited);
488  checkSYCLType(S, FPTy->getReturnType(), Loc, Visited);
489  }
490 }
491 
492 void Sema::checkSYCLDeviceVarDecl(VarDecl *Var) {
493  assert(getLangOpts().SYCLIsDevice &&
494  "Should only be called during SYCL compilation");
495  QualType Ty = Var->getType();
496  SourceRange Loc = Var->getLocation();
497  llvm::DenseSet<QualType> Visited;
498 
499  checkSYCLType(*this, Ty, Loc, Visited);
500 }

502 // Tests whether given function is a lambda function or '()' operator used as
503 // SYCL kernel body function (e.g. in parallel_for).
504 // NOTE: This is incomplete implemenation. See TODO in the FE TODO list for the
505 // ESIMD extension.
506 static bool isSYCLKernelBodyFunction(FunctionDecl *FD) {
507  return FD->getOverloadedOperator() == OO_Call;
508 }
509 
510 static bool isSYCLUndefinedAllowed(const FunctionDecl *Callee,
511  const SourceManager &SrcMgr) {
512  if (!Callee)
513  return false;
514 
515  // The check below requires declaration name, make sure we have it.
516  if (!Callee->getIdentifier())
517  return false;
518 
519  // libstdc++-11 introduced an undefined function "void __failed_assertion()"
520  // which may lead to SemaSYCL check failure. However, this undefined function
521  // is used to trigger some compilation error when the check fails at compile
522  // time and will be ignored when the check succeeds. We allow calls to this
523  // function to support some important std functions in SYCL device.
524  return (Callee->getName() == LibstdcxxFailedAssertion) &&
525  Callee->getNumParams() == 0 && Callee->getReturnType()->isVoidType() &&
526  SrcMgr.isInSystemHeader(Callee->getLocation());
527 }

529 // Helper function to report conflicting function attributes.
530 // F - the function, A1 - function attribute, A2 - the attribute it conflicts
531 // with.
532 static void reportConflictingAttrs(Sema &S, FunctionDecl *F, const Attr *A1,
533  const Attr *A2) {
534  S.Diag(F->getLocation(), diag::err_conflicting_sycl_kernel_attributes);
535  S.Diag(A1->getLocation(), diag::note_conflicting_attribute);
536  S.Diag(A2->getLocation(), diag::note_conflicting_attribute);
537  F->setInvalidDecl();
538 }

540 /// Returns the signed constant integer value represented by given expression
541 static int64_t getIntExprValue(const Expr *E, ASTContext &Ctx) {
542  return E->getIntegerConstantExpr(Ctx)->getSExtValue();
543 }
544 
545 // Collect function attributes related to SYCL.
546 static void collectSYCLAttributes(Sema &S, FunctionDecl *FD,
547  llvm::SmallVectorImpl<Attr *> &Attrs,
548  bool DirectlyCalled) {
549  if (!FD->hasAttrs())
550  return;
551 
552  // In SYCL 1.2.1 mode, the attributes are propagated from the function they
553  // are applied to onto the kernel which calls the function.
554  // In SYCL 2020 mode, the attributes are not propagated to the kernel.
555  if (DirectlyCalled || S.getASTContext().getLangOpts().getSYCLVersion() <
556  LangOptions::SYCL_2020) {
557  llvm::copy_if(FD->getAttrs(), std::back_inserter(Attrs), [](Attr *A) {
558  // FIXME: Make this list self-adapt as new SYCL attributes are added.
559  return isa<IntelReqdSubGroupSizeAttr, IntelNamedSubGroupSizeAttr,
560  ReqdWorkGroupSizeAttr, WorkGroupSizeHintAttr,
561  SYCLIntelKernelArgsRestrictAttr, SYCLIntelNumSimdWorkItemsAttr,
562  SYCLIntelSchedulerTargetFmaxMhzAttr,
563  SYCLIntelMaxWorkGroupSizeAttr, SYCLIntelMaxGlobalWorkDimAttr,
564  SYCLIntelNoGlobalWorkOffsetAttr, SYCLSimdAttr>(A);
565  });
566  }
567 
568  // Attributes that should not be propagated from device functions to a kernel.
569  if (DirectlyCalled) {
570  llvm::copy_if(FD->getAttrs(), std::back_inserter(Attrs), [](Attr *A) {
571  return isa<SYCLIntelLoopFuseAttr, SYCLIntelFPGAMaxConcurrencyAttr,
572  SYCLIntelFPGADisableLoopPipeliningAttr,
573  SYCLIntelFPGAInitiationIntervalAttr,
574  SYCLIntelUseStallEnableClustersAttr, SYCLDeviceHasAttr,
575  SYCLAddIRAttributesFunctionAttr>(A);
576  });
577  }
578 }

580 class DiagDeviceFunction : public RecursiveASTVisitor<DiagDeviceFunction> {
581  Sema &SemaRef;
582  const llvm::SmallPtrSetImpl<const FunctionDecl *> &RecursiveFuncs;
583 
584 public:
585  DiagDeviceFunction(
586  Sema &S,
587  const llvm::SmallPtrSetImpl<const FunctionDecl *> &RecursiveFuncs)
588  : RecursiveASTVisitor(), SemaRef(S), RecursiveFuncs(RecursiveFuncs) {}
589 
590  void CheckBody(Stmt *ToBeDiagnosed) { TraverseStmt(ToBeDiagnosed); }
591 
592  bool VisitCallExpr(CallExpr *e) {
593  if (FunctionDecl *Callee = e->getDirectCallee()) {
594  Callee = Callee->getCanonicalDecl();
595  assert(Callee && "Device function canonical decl must be available");
596 
597  // Remember that all SYCL kernel functions have deferred
598  // instantiation as template functions. It means that
599  // all functions used by kernel have already been parsed and have
600  // definitions.
601  if (RecursiveFuncs.count(Callee)) {
602  SemaRef.Diag(e->getExprLoc(), diag::err_sycl_restrict)
603  << Sema::KernelCallRecursiveFunction;
604  SemaRef.Diag(Callee->getSourceRange().getBegin(),
605  diag::note_sycl_recursive_function_declared_here)
606  << Sema::KernelCallRecursiveFunction;
607  }
608 
609  if (const CXXMethodDecl *Method = dyn_cast<CXXMethodDecl>(Callee))
610  if (Method->isVirtual())
611  SemaRef.Diag(e->getExprLoc(), diag::err_sycl_restrict)
612  << Sema::KernelCallVirtualFunction;
613 
614  if (auto const *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(Callee)) {
615  // FIXME: We need check all target specified attributes for error if
616  // that function with attribute can not be called from sycl kernel. The
617  // info is in ParsedAttr. We don't have to map from Attr to ParsedAttr
618  // currently. Erich is currently working on that in LLVM, once that is
619  // committed we need to change this".
620  if (FD->hasAttr<DLLImportAttr>()) {
621  SemaRef.Diag(e->getExprLoc(), diag::err_sycl_restrict)
622  << Sema::KernelCallDllimportFunction;
623  SemaRef.Diag(FD->getLocation(), diag::note_callee_decl) << FD;
624  }
625  }
626  // Specifically check if the math library function corresponding to this
627  // builtin is supported for SYCL
628  unsigned BuiltinID = Callee->getBuiltinID();
629  if (BuiltinID && !IsSyclMathFunc(BuiltinID)) {
630  StringRef Name = SemaRef.Context.BuiltinInfo.getName(BuiltinID);
631  SemaRef.Diag(e->getExprLoc(), diag::err_builtin_target_unsupported)
632  << Name << "SYCL device";
633  }
634  } else if (!SemaRef.getLangOpts().SYCLAllowFuncPtr &&
635  !e->isTypeDependent() &&
636  !isa<CXXPseudoDestructorExpr>(e->getCallee())) {
637  bool MaybeConstantExpr = false;
638  Expr *NonDirectCallee = e->getCallee();
639  if (!NonDirectCallee->isValueDependent())
640  MaybeConstantExpr =
641  NonDirectCallee->isCXX11ConstantExpr(SemaRef.getASTContext());
642  if (!MaybeConstantExpr)
643  SemaRef.Diag(e->getExprLoc(), diag::err_sycl_restrict)
644  << Sema::KernelCallFunctionPointer;
645  }
646  return true;
647  }
648 
649  bool VisitCXXTypeidExpr(CXXTypeidExpr *E) {
650  SemaRef.Diag(E->getExprLoc(), diag::err_sycl_restrict) << Sema::KernelRTTI;
651  return true;
652  }
653 
654  bool VisitCXXDynamicCastExpr(const CXXDynamicCastExpr *E) {
655  SemaRef.Diag(E->getExprLoc(), diag::err_sycl_restrict) << Sema::KernelRTTI;
656  return true;
657  }
658 
659  // Skip checking rules on variables initialized during constant evaluation.
660  bool TraverseVarDecl(VarDecl *VD) {
661  if (VD->isConstexpr())
662  return true;
663  return RecursiveASTVisitor::TraverseVarDecl(VD);
664  }
665 
666  // Skip checking rules on template arguments, since these are constant
667  // expressions.
668  bool TraverseTemplateArgumentLoc(const TemplateArgumentLoc &ArgLoc) {
669  return true;
670  }
671 
672  // Skip checking the static assert, both components are required to be
673  // constant expressions.
674  bool TraverseStaticAssertDecl(StaticAssertDecl *D) { return true; }
675 
676  // Make sure we skip the condition of the case, since that is a constant
677  // expression.
678  bool TraverseCaseStmt(CaseStmt *S) {
679  return TraverseStmt(S->getSubStmt());
680  }
681 
682  // Skip checking the size expr, since a constant array type loc's size expr is
683  // a constant expression.
684  bool TraverseConstantArrayTypeLoc(const ConstantArrayTypeLoc &ArrLoc) {
685  return true;
686  }
687 
688  bool TraverseIfStmt(IfStmt *S) {
689  if (llvm::Optional<Stmt *> ActiveStmt =
690  S->getNondiscardedCase(SemaRef.Context)) {
691  if (*ActiveStmt)
692  return TraverseStmt(*ActiveStmt);
693  return true;
694  }
695  return RecursiveASTVisitor::TraverseIfStmt(S);
696  }
697 };
698 
699 // This type manages the list of device functions and recursive functions, as
700 // well as an entry point for attribute collection, for the translation unit
701 // during MarkDevices. On construction, this type makes sure that all of the
702 // root-device functions, (that is, those marked with SYCL_EXTERNAL) are
703 // collected. On destruction, it manages and runs the diagnostics required.
704 // When processing individual kernel/external functions, the
705 // SingleDeviceFunctionTracker type updates this type.
706 class DeviceFunctionTracker {
707  friend class SingleDeviceFunctionTracker;
708  CallGraph CG;
709  Sema &SemaRef;
710  // The list of functions used on the device, kept so we can diagnose on them
711  // later.
712  llvm::SmallPtrSet<FunctionDecl *, 16> DeviceFunctions;
713  llvm::SmallPtrSet<const FunctionDecl *, 16> RecursiveFunctions;
714 
715  void CollectSyclExternalFuncs() {
716  for (CallGraphNode::CallRecord Record : CG.getRoot()->callees())
717  if (auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(Record.Callee->getDecl()))
718  if (FD->hasBody() && FD->hasAttr<SYCLDeviceAttr>())
719  SemaRef.addSyclDeviceDecl(FD);
720  }
721 
722  CallGraphNode *getNodeForKernel(FunctionDecl *Kernel) {
723  assert(CG.getNode(Kernel) && "No call graph entry for a kernel?");
724  return CG.getNode(Kernel);
725  }
726 
727  void AddSingleFunction(
728  const llvm::SmallPtrSetImpl<FunctionDecl *> &DevFuncs,
729  const llvm::SmallPtrSetImpl<const FunctionDecl *> &Recursive) {
730  DeviceFunctions.insert(DevFuncs.begin(), DevFuncs.end());
731  RecursiveFunctions.insert(Recursive.begin(), Recursive.end());
732  }
733 
734 public:
735  DeviceFunctionTracker(Sema &S) : SemaRef(S) {
736  CG.setSkipConstantExpressions(S.Context);
737  CG.addToCallGraph(S.getASTContext().getTranslationUnitDecl());
738  CollectSyclExternalFuncs();
739  }
740 
741  ~DeviceFunctionTracker() {
742  DiagDeviceFunction Diagnoser{SemaRef, RecursiveFunctions};
743  for (const FunctionDecl *FD : DeviceFunctions)
744  if (const FunctionDecl *Def = FD->getDefinition())
745  Diagnoser.CheckBody(Def->getBody());
746  }
747 };
748 
749 // This type does the heavy lifting for the management of device functions,
750 // recursive function detection, and attribute collection for a single
751 // kernel/external function. It walks the callgraph to find all functions that
752 // are called, marks the recursive-functions, and figures out the list of
753 // attributes that apply to this kernel.
754 //
755 // Upon destruction, this type updates the DeviceFunctionTracker.
756 class SingleDeviceFunctionTracker {
757  DeviceFunctionTracker &Parent;
758  FunctionDecl *SYCLKernel = nullptr;
759  FunctionDecl *KernelBody = nullptr;
760  llvm::SmallPtrSet<FunctionDecl *, 16> DeviceFunctions;
761  llvm::SmallPtrSet<const FunctionDecl *, 16> RecursiveFunctions;
762  llvm::SmallVector<Attr *> CollectedAttributes;
763 
764  FunctionDecl *GetFDFromNode(CallGraphNode *Node) {
765  FunctionDecl *FD = Node->getDecl()->getAsFunction();
766  if (!FD)
767  return nullptr;
768 
769  return FD->getMostRecentDecl();
770  }
771 
772  void VisitCallNode(CallGraphNode *Node, FunctionDecl *CurrentDecl,
773  llvm::SmallVectorImpl<FunctionDecl *> &CallStack) {
774  // If this isn't a function, I don't think there is anything we can do here.
775  if (!CurrentDecl)
776  return;
777 
778  // Determine if this is a recursive function. If so, we're done.
779  if (llvm::is_contained(CallStack, CurrentDecl)) {
780  RecursiveFunctions.insert(CurrentDecl->getCanonicalDecl());
781  return;
782  }
783 
784  // If this is a routine that is not defined and it does not have either
785  // a SYCLKernel or SYCLDevice attribute on it, add it to the set of
786  // routines potentially reachable on device. This is to diagnose such
787  // cases later in finalizeSYCLDeviceAnalysis().
788  if (!CurrentDecl->isDefined() && !CurrentDecl->hasAttr<SYCLKernelAttr>() &&
789  !CurrentDecl->hasAttr<SYCLDeviceAttr>())
790  Parent.SemaRef.addFDToReachableFromSyclDevice(CurrentDecl,
791  CallStack.back());
792 
793  // We previously thought we could skip this function if we'd seen it before,
794  // but if we haven't seen it before in this call graph, we can end up
795  // missing a recursive call. SO, we have to revisit call-graphs we've
796  // already seen, just in case it ALSO has recursion. For example:
797  // void recurse1();
798  // void recurse2() { recurse1(); }
799  // void recurse1() { recurse2(); }
800  // void CallerInKernel() { recurse1(); recurse2(); }
801  // When checking 'recurse1', we'd have ended up 'visiting' recurse2 without
802  // realizing it was recursive, since we never went into the
803  // child-of-its-child, since THAT was recursive and exited early out of
804  // necessity.
805  // Then when we go to visit the kernel's call to recurse2, we would
806  // immediately escape not noticing it was recursive. SO, we have to do a
807  // little extra work in this case, and make sure we visit the entire call
808  // graph.
809  DeviceFunctions.insert(CurrentDecl);
810 
811  // Collect attributes for functions that aren't the root kernel.
812  if (!CallStack.empty()) {
813  bool DirectlyCalled = CallStack.size() == 1;
814  collectSYCLAttributes(Parent.SemaRef, CurrentDecl, CollectedAttributes,
815  DirectlyCalled);
816  }
817 
818  // Calculate the kernel body. Note the 'isSYCLKernelBodyFunction' only
819  // tests that it is operator(), so hopefully this doesn't get us too many
820  // false-positives.
821  if (isSYCLKernelBodyFunction(CurrentDecl)) {
822  // This is a direct callee of the kernel.
823  if (CallStack.size() == 1 &&
824  CallStack.back()->hasAttr<SYCLKernelAttr>()) {
825  assert(!KernelBody && "inconsistent call graph - only one kernel body "
826  "function can be called");
827  KernelBody = CurrentDecl;
828  } else if (CallStack.size() == 2 && KernelBody == CallStack.back()) {
829  // To implement rounding-up of a parallel-for range the
830  // SYCL header implementation modifies the kernel call like this:
831  // auto Wrapper = [=](TransformedArgType Arg) {
832  // if (Arg[0] >= NumWorkItems[0])
833  // return;
834  // Arg.set_allowed_range(NumWorkItems);
835  // KernelFunc(Arg);
836  // };
837  //
838  // This transformation leads to a condition where a kernel body
839  // function becomes callable from a new kernel body function.
840  // Hence this test.
841  // FIXME: We need to be more selective here, this can be hit by simply
842  // having a kernel lambda with a lambda call inside of it.
843  KernelBody = CurrentDecl;
844  }
845  }
846 
847  // Recurse.
848  CallStack.push_back(CurrentDecl);
849  llvm::SmallPtrSet<FunctionDecl *, 16> SeenCallees;
850  for (CallGraphNode *CI : Node->callees()) {
851  FunctionDecl *CurFD = GetFDFromNode(CI);
852 
853  // Make sure we only visit each callee 1x from this function to avoid very
854  // time consuming template recursion cases.
855  if (!llvm::is_contained(SeenCallees, CurFD)) {
856  VisitCallNode(CI, CurFD, CallStack);
857  SeenCallees.insert(CurFD);
858  }
859  }
860  CallStack.pop_back();
861  }
862 
863  // Function to walk the call graph and identify the important information.
864  void Init() {
865  CallGraphNode *KernelNode = Parent.getNodeForKernel(SYCLKernel);
866  llvm::SmallVector<FunctionDecl *> CallStack;
867  VisitCallNode(KernelNode, GetFDFromNode(KernelNode), CallStack);
868  }
869 
870 public:
871  SingleDeviceFunctionTracker(DeviceFunctionTracker &P, Decl *Kernel)
872  : Parent(P), SYCLKernel(Kernel->getAsFunction()) {
873  Init();
874  }
875 
876  FunctionDecl *GetSYCLKernel() { return SYCLKernel; }
877 
878  FunctionDecl *GetKernelBody() { return KernelBody; }
879 
880  llvm::SmallVectorImpl<Attr *> &GetCollectedAttributes() {
881  return CollectedAttributes;
882  }
883 
884  llvm::SmallPtrSetImpl<FunctionDecl *> &GetDeviceFunctions() {
885  return DeviceFunctions;
886  }
887 
888  ~SingleDeviceFunctionTracker() {
889  Parent.AddSingleFunction(DeviceFunctions, RecursiveFunctions);
890  }
891 };
892 
893 class KernelBodyTransform : public TreeTransform<KernelBodyTransform> {
894 public:
895  KernelBodyTransform(std::pair<DeclaratorDecl *, DeclaratorDecl *> &MPair,
896  Sema &S)
897  : TreeTransform<KernelBodyTransform>(S), MappingPair(MPair), SemaRef(S) {}
898  bool AlwaysRebuild() { return true; }
899 
900  ExprResult TransformDeclRefExpr(DeclRefExpr *DRE) {
901  auto Ref = dyn_cast<DeclaratorDecl>(DRE->getDecl());
902  if (Ref && Ref == MappingPair.first) {
903  auto NewDecl = MappingPair.second;
904  return DeclRefExpr::Create(
905  SemaRef.getASTContext(), DRE->getQualifierLoc(),
906  DRE->getTemplateKeywordLoc(), NewDecl, false, DRE->getNameInfo(),
907  NewDecl->getType(), DRE->getValueKind());
908  }
909  return DRE;
910  }
911 
912 private:
913  std::pair<DeclaratorDecl *, DeclaratorDecl *> MappingPair;
914  Sema &SemaRef;
915 };

917 // Searches for a call to PFWG lambda function and captures it.
918 class FindPFWGLambdaFnVisitor
919  : public RecursiveASTVisitor<FindPFWGLambdaFnVisitor> {
920 public:
921  // LambdaObjTy - lambda type of the PFWG lambda object
922  FindPFWGLambdaFnVisitor(const CXXRecordDecl *LambdaObjTy)
923  : LambdaFn(nullptr), LambdaObjTy(LambdaObjTy) {}
924 
925  bool VisitCallExpr(CallExpr *Call) {
926  auto *M = dyn_cast<CXXMethodDecl>(Call->getDirectCallee());
927  if (!M || (M->getOverloadedOperator() != OO_Call))
928  return true;
929 
930  unsigned int NumPFWGLambdaArgs =
931  M->getNumParams() + 1; // group, optional kernel_handler and lambda obj
932  if (Call->getNumArgs() != NumPFWGLambdaArgs)
933  return true;
934  if (!Util::isSyclType(Call->getArg(1)->getType(), "group", true /*Tmpl*/))
935  return true;
936  if ((Call->getNumArgs() > 2) &&
937  !Util::isSyclKernelHandlerType(Call->getArg(2)->getType()))
938  return true;
939  if (Call->getArg(0)->getType()->getAsCXXRecordDecl() != LambdaObjTy)
940  return true;
941  LambdaFn = M; // call to PFWG lambda found - record the lambda
942  return false; // ... and stop searching
943  }
944 
945  // Returns the captured lambda function or nullptr;
946  CXXMethodDecl *getLambdaFn() const { return LambdaFn; }
947 
948 private:
949  CXXMethodDecl *LambdaFn;
950  const CXXRecordDecl *LambdaObjTy;
951 };
952 
953 class MarkWIScopeFnVisitor : public RecursiveASTVisitor<MarkWIScopeFnVisitor> {
954 public:
955  MarkWIScopeFnVisitor(ASTContext &Ctx) : Ctx(Ctx) {}
956 
957  bool VisitCXXMemberCallExpr(CXXMemberCallExpr *Call) {
958  FunctionDecl *Callee = Call->getDirectCallee();
959  if (!Callee)
960  // not a direct call - continue search
961  return true;
962  QualType Ty = Ctx.getRecordType(Call->getRecordDecl());
963  if (!Util::isSyclType(Ty, "group", true /*Tmpl*/))
964  // not a member of cl::sycl::group - continue search
965  return true;
966  auto Name = Callee->getName();
967  if (((Name != "parallel_for_work_item") && (Name != "wait_for")) ||
968  Callee->hasAttr<SYCLScopeAttr>())
969  return true;
970  // it is a call to cl::sycl::group::parallel_for_work_item/wait_for -
971  // mark the callee
972  Callee->addAttr(
973  SYCLScopeAttr::CreateImplicit(Ctx, SYCLScopeAttr::Level::WorkItem));
974  // continue search as there can be other PFWI or wait_for calls
975  return true;
976  }
977 
978 private:
979  ASTContext &Ctx;
980 };

982 static bool isSYCLPrivateMemoryVar(VarDecl *VD) {
983  return Util::isSyclType(VD->getType(), "private_memory", true /*Tmpl*/);
984 }
985 
986 static void addScopeAttrToLocalVars(CXXMethodDecl &F) {
987  for (Decl *D : F.decls()) {
988  VarDecl *VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(D);
989 
990  if (!VD || isa<ParmVarDecl>(VD) ||
991  VD->getStorageDuration() != StorageDuration::SD_Automatic)
992  continue;
993  // Local variables of private_memory type in the WG scope still have WI
994  // scope, all the rest - WG scope. Simple logic
995  // "if no scope than it is WG scope" won't work, because compiler may add
996  // locals not declared in user code (lambda object parameter, byval
997  // arguments) which will result in alloca w/o any attribute, so need WI
998  // scope too.
999  SYCLScopeAttr::Level L = isSYCLPrivateMemoryVar(VD)
1000  ? SYCLScopeAttr::Level::WorkItem
1001  : SYCLScopeAttr::Level::WorkGroup;
1002  VD->addAttr(SYCLScopeAttr::CreateImplicit(F.getASTContext(), L));
1003  }
1004 }

1006 /// Return method by name
1007 static CXXMethodDecl *getMethodByName(const CXXRecordDecl *CRD,
1008  StringRef MethodName) {
1009  CXXMethodDecl *Method;
1010  auto It = std::find_if(CRD->methods().begin(), CRD->methods().end(),
1011  [MethodName](const CXXMethodDecl *Method) {
1012  return Method->getNameAsString() == MethodName;
1013  });
1014  Method = (It != CRD->methods().end()) ? *It : nullptr;
1015  return Method;
1016 }

1018 static KernelInvocationKind
1019 getKernelInvocationKind(FunctionDecl *KernelCallerFunc) {
1020  return llvm::StringSwitch<KernelInvocationKind>(KernelCallerFunc->getName())
1021  .Case("kernel_single_task", InvokeSingleTask)
1022  .Case("kernel_parallel_for", InvokeParallelFor)
1023  .Case("kernel_parallel_for_work_group", InvokeParallelForWorkGroup)
1024  .Default(InvokeUnknown);
1025 }

1027 // The SYCL kernel's 'object type' used for diagnostics and naming/mangling is
1028 // the first parameter to a function template using the sycl_kernel
1029 // attribute. In SYCL 1.2.1, this was passed by value,
1030 // and in SYCL 2020, it is passed by reference.
1031 static QualType GetSYCLKernelObjectType(const FunctionDecl *KernelCaller) {
1032  assert(KernelCaller->getNumParams() > 0 && "Insufficient kernel parameters");
1033  QualType KernelParamTy = KernelCaller->getParamDecl(0)->getType();
1034 
1035  // SYCL 2020 kernels are passed by reference.
1036  if (KernelParamTy->isReferenceType())
1037  KernelParamTy = KernelParamTy->getPointeeType();
1038 
1039  // SYCL 1.2.1
1040  return KernelParamTy.getUnqualifiedType();
1041 }

1043 /// Creates a kernel parameter descriptor
1044 /// \param Src field declaration to construct name from
1045 /// \param Ty the desired parameter type
1046 /// \return the constructed descriptor
1047 static ParamDesc makeParamDesc(const FieldDecl *Src, QualType Ty) {
1048  ASTContext &Ctx = Src->getASTContext();
1049  std::string Name = (Twine("_arg_") + Src->getName()).str();
1050  return std::make_tuple(Ty, &Ctx.Idents.get(Name),
1051  Ctx.getTrivialTypeSourceInfo(Ty));
1052 }
1053 
1054 static ParamDesc makeParamDesc(ASTContext &Ctx, StringRef Name, QualType Ty) {
1055  return std::make_tuple(Ty, &Ctx.Idents.get(Name),
1056  Ctx.getTrivialTypeSourceInfo(Ty));
1057 }

1060 static target getAccessTarget(const ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl *AccTy) {
1061  return static_cast<target>(
1062  AccTy->getTemplateArgs()[3].getAsIntegral().getExtValue());
1063 }

1065 // The first template argument to the kernel caller function is used to identify
1066 // the kernel itself.
1067 static QualType calculateKernelNameType(ASTContext &Ctx,
1068  const FunctionDecl *KernelCallerFunc) {
1069  const TemplateArgumentList *TAL =
1070  KernelCallerFunc->getTemplateSpecializationArgs();
1071  assert(TAL && "No template argument info");
1072  return TAL->get(0).getAsType().getCanonicalType();
1073 }

1075 // Gets a name for the OpenCL kernel function, calculated from the first
1076 // template argument of the kernel caller function.
1077 static std::pair<std::string, std::string>
1078 constructKernelName(Sema &S, const FunctionDecl *KernelCallerFunc,
1079  MangleContext &MC) {
1080  QualType KernelNameType =
1081  calculateKernelNameType(S.getASTContext(), KernelCallerFunc);
1082 
1083  SmallString<256> Result;
1084  llvm::raw_svector_ostream Out(Result);
1085 
1086  MC.mangleTypeName(KernelNameType, Out);
1087 
1088  return {std::string(Out.str()), SYCLUniqueStableNameExpr::ComputeName(
1089  S.getASTContext(), KernelNameType)};
1090 }

1092 static bool isDefaultSPIRArch(ASTContext &Context) {
1093  llvm::Triple T = Context.getTargetInfo().getTriple();
1094  if (T.isSPIR() && T.getSubArch() == llvm::Triple::NoSubArch)
1095  return true;
1096  return false;

1099 static ParmVarDecl *getSyclKernelHandlerArg(FunctionDecl *KernelCallerFunc) {
1100  // Specialization constants in SYCL 2020 are not captured by lambda and
1101  // accessed through new optional lambda argument kernel_handler
1102  auto IsHandlerLambda = [](ParmVarDecl *PVD) {
1103  return Util::isSyclKernelHandlerType(PVD->getType());
1104  };
1105 
1106  assert(llvm::count_if(KernelCallerFunc->parameters(), IsHandlerLambda) <= 1 &&
1107  "Multiple kernel_handler parameters");
1108 
1109  auto KHArg = llvm::find_if(KernelCallerFunc->parameters(), IsHandlerLambda);
1110 
1111  return (KHArg != KernelCallerFunc->param_end()) ? *KHArg : nullptr;
1112 }

1114 static bool isReadOnlyAccessor(const TemplateArgument &AccessModeArg) {
1115  const auto *AccessModeArgEnumType =
1116  AccessModeArg.getIntegralType()->castAs<EnumType>();
1117  const EnumDecl *ED = AccessModeArgEnumType->getDecl();
1118 
1119  auto ReadOnly =
1120  llvm::find_if(ED->enumerators(), [&](const EnumConstantDecl *E) {
1121  return E->getName() == "read";
1122  });
1123 
1124  return ReadOnly != ED->enumerator_end() &&
1125  (*ReadOnly)->getInitVal() == AccessModeArg.getAsIntegral();
1126 }

1131 template <typename T> struct bind_param { using type = T; };
1132 
1133 template <> struct bind_param<CXXBaseSpecifier &> {
1134  using type = const CXXBaseSpecifier &;
1135 };
1136

1143 class KernelObjVisitor {
1144  Sema &SemaRef;
1145 
1146  template <typename ParentTy, typename... HandlerTys>
1147  void VisitUnionImpl(const CXXRecordDecl *Owner, ParentTy &Parent,
1148  const CXXRecordDecl *Wrapper, HandlerTys &... Handlers) {
1149  (void)std::initializer_list<int>{
1150  (Handlers.enterUnion(Owner, Parent), 0)...};
1151  VisitRecordHelper(Wrapper, Wrapper->fields(), Handlers...);
1152  (void)std::initializer_list<int>{
1153  (Handlers.leaveUnion(Owner, Parent), 0)...};
1154  }
1155 
1156  // These enable handler execution only when previous Handlers succeed.
1157  template <typename... Tn>
1158  bool handleField(FieldDecl *FD, QualType FDTy, Tn &&... tn) {
1159  bool result = true;
1160  (void)std::initializer_list<int>{(result = result && tn(FD, FDTy), 0)...};
1161  return result;
1162  }
1163  template <typename... Tn>
1164  bool handleField(const CXXBaseSpecifier &BD, QualType BDTy, Tn &&... tn) {
1165  bool result = true;
1166  std::initializer_list<int>{(result = result && tn(BD, BDTy), 0)...};
1167  return result;
1168  }
1169 
1170 // This definition using std::bind is necessary because of a gcc 7.x bug.
1171 #define KF_FOR_EACH(FUNC, Item, Qt) \
1172  handleField( \
1173  Item, Qt, \
1174  std::bind(static_cast<bool (std::decay_t<decltype(Handlers)>::*)( \
1175  bind_param_t<decltype(Item)>, QualType)>( \
1176  &std::decay_t<decltype(Handlers)>::FUNC), \
1177  std::ref(Handlers), _1, _2)...)
1178 
1179  // The following simpler definition works with gcc 8.x and later.
1180  //#define KF_FOR_EACH(FUNC) \
1181 // handleField(Field, FieldTy, ([&](FieldDecl *FD, QualType FDTy) { \
1182 // return Handlers.f(FD, FDTy); \
1183 // })...)
1184 
1185  // Parent contains the FieldDecl or CXXBaseSpecifier that was used to enter
1186  // the Wrapper structure that we're currently visiting. Owner is the parent
1187  // type (which doesn't exist in cases where it is a FieldDecl in the
1188  // 'root'), and Wrapper is the current struct being unwrapped.
1189  template <typename ParentTy, typename... HandlerTys>
1190  void visitComplexRecord(const CXXRecordDecl *Owner, ParentTy &Parent,
1191  const CXXRecordDecl *Wrapper, QualType RecordTy,
1192  HandlerTys &... Handlers) {
1193  (void)std::initializer_list<int>{
1194  (Handlers.enterStruct(Owner, Parent, RecordTy), 0)...};
1195  VisitRecordHelper(Wrapper, Wrapper->bases(), Handlers...);
1196  VisitRecordHelper(Wrapper, Wrapper->fields(), Handlers...);
1197  (void)std::initializer_list<int>{
1198  (Handlers.leaveStruct(Owner, Parent, RecordTy), 0)...};
1199  }
1200 
1201  template <typename ParentTy, typename... HandlerTys>
1202  void visitSimpleRecord(const CXXRecordDecl *Owner, ParentTy &Parent,
1203  const CXXRecordDecl *Wrapper, QualType RecordTy,
1204  HandlerTys &... Handlers) {
1205  (void)std::initializer_list<int>{
1206  (Handlers.handleNonDecompStruct(Owner, Parent, RecordTy), 0)...};
1207  }
1208 
1209  template <typename ParentTy, typename... HandlerTys>
1210  void visitRecord(const CXXRecordDecl *Owner, ParentTy &Parent,
1211  const CXXRecordDecl *Wrapper, QualType RecordTy,
1212  HandlerTys &... Handlers);
1213 
1214  template <typename ParentTy, typename... HandlerTys>
1215  void VisitUnion(const CXXRecordDecl *Owner, ParentTy &Parent,
1216  const CXXRecordDecl *Wrapper, HandlerTys &... Handlers);
1217 
1218  template <typename... HandlerTys>
1219  void VisitRecordHelper(const CXXRecordDecl *Owner,
1220  clang::CXXRecordDecl::base_class_const_range Range,
1221  HandlerTys &... Handlers) {
1222  for (const auto &Base : Range) {
1223  QualType BaseTy = Base.getType();
1224  // Handle accessor class as base
1225  if (Util::isSyclSpecialType(BaseTy)) {
1226  (void)std::initializer_list<int>{
1227  (Handlers.handleSyclSpecialType(Owner, Base, BaseTy), 0)...};
1228  } else
1229  // For all other bases, visit the record
1230  visitRecord(Owner, Base, BaseTy->getAsCXXRecordDecl(), BaseTy,
1231  Handlers...);
1232  }
1233  }
1234 
1235  template <typename... HandlerTys>
1236  void VisitRecordHelper(const CXXRecordDecl *Owner,
1237  RecordDecl::field_range Range,
1238  HandlerTys &... Handlers) {
1239  VisitRecordFields(Owner, Handlers...);
1240  }
1241 
1242  template <typename... HandlerTys>
1243  void visitArrayElementImpl(const CXXRecordDecl *Owner, FieldDecl *ArrayField,
1244  QualType ElementTy, uint64_t Index,
1245  HandlerTys &... Handlers) {
1246  (void)std::initializer_list<int>{
1247  (Handlers.nextElement(ElementTy, Index), 0)...};
1248  visitField(Owner, ArrayField, ElementTy, Handlers...);
1249  }
1250 
1251  template <typename... HandlerTys>
1252  void visitFirstArrayElement(const CXXRecordDecl *Owner, FieldDecl *ArrayField,
1253  QualType ElementTy, HandlerTys &... Handlers) {
1254  visitArrayElementImpl(Owner, ArrayField, ElementTy, 0, Handlers...);
1255  }
1256  template <typename... HandlerTys>
1257  void visitNthArrayElement(const CXXRecordDecl *Owner, FieldDecl *ArrayField,
1258  QualType ElementTy, uint64_t Index,
1259  HandlerTys &... Handlers);
1260 
1261  template <typename... HandlerTys>
1262  void visitSimpleArray(const CXXRecordDecl *Owner, FieldDecl *Field,
1263  QualType ArrayTy, HandlerTys &... Handlers) {
1264  (void)std::initializer_list<int>{
1265  (Handlers.handleSimpleArrayType(Field, ArrayTy), 0)...};
1266  }
1267 
1268  template <typename... HandlerTys>
1269  void visitComplexArray(const CXXRecordDecl *Owner, FieldDecl *Field,
1270  QualType ArrayTy, HandlerTys &... Handlers) {
1271  // Array workflow is:
1272  // handleArrayType
1273  // enterArray
1274  // nextElement
1275  // VisitField (same as before, note that The FieldDecl is the of array
1276  // itself, not the element)
1277  // ... repeat per element, opt-out for duplicates.
1278  // leaveArray
1279 
1280  if (!KF_FOR_EACH(handleArrayType, Field, ArrayTy))
1281  return;
1282 
1283  const ConstantArrayType *CAT =
1284  SemaRef.getASTContext().getAsConstantArrayType(ArrayTy);
1285  assert(CAT && "Should only be called on constant-size array.");
1286  QualType ET = CAT->getElementType();
1287  uint64_t ElemCount = CAT->getSize().getZExtValue();
1288 
1289  (void)std::initializer_list<int>{
1290  (Handlers.enterArray(Field, ArrayTy, ET), 0)...};
1291 
1292  visitFirstArrayElement(Owner, Field, ET, Handlers...);
1293  for (uint64_t Index = 1; Index < ElemCount; ++Index)
1294  visitNthArrayElement(Owner, Field, ET, Index, Handlers...);
1295 
1296  (void)std::initializer_list<int>{
1297  (Handlers.leaveArray(Field, ArrayTy, ET), 0)...};
1298  }
1299 
1300  template <typename... HandlerTys>
1301  void visitArray(const CXXRecordDecl *Owner, FieldDecl *Field,
1302  QualType ArrayTy, HandlerTys &... Handlers);
1303 
1304  template <typename... HandlerTys>
1305  void visitField(const CXXRecordDecl *Owner, FieldDecl *Field,
1306  QualType FieldTy, HandlerTys &... Handlers) {
1307  if (Util::isSyclSpecialType(FieldTy))
1308  KF_FOR_EACH(handleSyclSpecialType, Field, FieldTy);
1309  else if (Util::isSyclSpecConstantType(FieldTy))
1310  KF_FOR_EACH(handleSyclSpecConstantType, Field, FieldTy);
1311  else if (FieldTy->isStructureOrClassType()) {
1312  if (KF_FOR_EACH(handleStructType, Field, FieldTy)) {
1313  CXXRecordDecl *RD = FieldTy->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
1314  visitRecord(Owner, Field, RD, FieldTy, Handlers...);
1315  }
1316  } else if (FieldTy->isUnionType()) {
1317  if (KF_FOR_EACH(handleUnionType, Field, FieldTy)) {
1318  CXXRecordDecl *RD = FieldTy->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
1319  VisitUnion(Owner, Field, RD, Handlers...);
1320  }
1321  } else if (FieldTy->isReferenceType())
1322  KF_FOR_EACH(handleReferenceType, Field, FieldTy);
1323  else if (FieldTy->isPointerType())
1324  KF_FOR_EACH(handlePointerType, Field, FieldTy);
1325  else if (FieldTy->isArrayType())
1326  visitArray(Owner, Field, FieldTy, Handlers...);
1327  else if (FieldTy->isScalarType() || FieldTy->isVectorType())
1328  KF_FOR_EACH(handleScalarType, Field, FieldTy);
1329  else
1330  KF_FOR_EACH(handleOtherType, Field, FieldTy);
1331  }
1332 
1333 public:
1334  KernelObjVisitor(Sema &S) : SemaRef(S) {}
1335 
1336  template <typename... HandlerTys>
1337  void VisitRecordBases(const CXXRecordDecl *KernelFunctor,
1338  HandlerTys &... Handlers) {
1339  VisitRecordHelper(KernelFunctor, KernelFunctor->bases(), Handlers...);
1340  }
1341 
1342  // A visitor function that dispatches to functions as defined in
1343  // SyclKernelFieldHandler for the purposes of kernel generation.
1344  template <typename... HandlerTys>
1345  void VisitRecordFields(const CXXRecordDecl *Owner, HandlerTys &... Handlers) {
1346  for (const auto Field : Owner->fields())
1347  visitField(Owner, Field, Field->getType(), Handlers...);
1348  }
1349 #undef KF_FOR_EACH
1350 };
1351 
1352 // A base type that the SYCL OpenCL Kernel construction task uses to implement
1353 // individual tasks.
1354 class SyclKernelFieldHandlerBase {
1355 public:
1356  static constexpr const bool VisitUnionBody = false;
1357  static constexpr const bool VisitNthArrayElement = true;
1358  // Opt-in based on whether we should visit inside simple containers (structs,
1359  // arrays). All of the 'check' types should likely be true, the int-header,
1360  // and kernel decl creation types should not.
1361  static constexpr const bool VisitInsideSimpleContainers = true;
1362  // Mark these virtual so that we can use override in the implementer classes,
1363  // despite virtual dispatch never being used.
1364 
1365  // SYCL special class can be a base class or a field decl, so both must be
1366  // handled.
1367  virtual bool handleSyclSpecialType(const CXXRecordDecl *,
1368  const CXXBaseSpecifier &, QualType) {
1369  return true;
1370  }
1371  virtual bool handleSyclSpecialType(FieldDecl *, QualType) { return true; }
1372 
1373  virtual bool handleSyclSpecConstantType(FieldDecl *, QualType) {
1374  return true;
1375  }
1376 
1377  virtual bool handleStructType(FieldDecl *, QualType) { return true; }
1378  virtual bool handleUnionType(FieldDecl *, QualType) { return true; }
1379  virtual bool handleReferenceType(FieldDecl *, QualType) { return true; }
1380  virtual bool handlePointerType(FieldDecl *, QualType) { return true; }
1381  virtual bool handleArrayType(FieldDecl *, QualType) { return true; }
1382  virtual bool handleScalarType(FieldDecl *, QualType) { return true; }
1383  // Most handlers shouldn't be handling this, just the field checker.
1384  virtual bool handleOtherType(FieldDecl *, QualType) { return true; }
1385 
1386  // Handle a simple struct that doesn't need to be decomposed, only called on
1387  // handlers with VisitInsideSimpleContainers as false. Replaces
1388  // handleStructType, enterStruct, leaveStruct, and visiting of sub-elements.
1389  virtual bool handleNonDecompStruct(const CXXRecordDecl *, FieldDecl *,
1390  QualType) {
1391  return true;
1392  }
1393  virtual bool handleNonDecompStruct(const CXXRecordDecl *,
1394  const CXXBaseSpecifier &, QualType) {
1395  return true;
1396  }
1397 
1398  // Instead of handleArrayType, enterArray, leaveArray, and nextElement (plus
1399  // descending down the elements), this function gets called in the event of an
1400  // array containing simple elements (even in the case of an MD array).
1401  virtual bool handleSimpleArrayType(FieldDecl *, QualType) { return true; }
1402 
1403  // The following are only used for keeping track of where we are in the base
1404  // class/field graph. Int Headers use this to calculate offset, most others
1405  // don't have a need for these.
1406 
1407  virtual bool enterStruct(const CXXRecordDecl *, FieldDecl *, QualType) {
1408  return true;
1409  }
1410  virtual bool leaveStruct(const CXXRecordDecl *, FieldDecl *, QualType) {
1411  return true;
1412  }
1413  virtual bool enterStruct(const CXXRecordDecl *, const CXXBaseSpecifier &,
1414  QualType) {
1415  return true;
1416  }
1417  virtual bool leaveStruct(const CXXRecordDecl *, const CXXBaseSpecifier &,
1418  QualType) {
1419  return true;
1420  }
1421  virtual bool enterUnion(const CXXRecordDecl *, FieldDecl *) { return true; }
1422  virtual bool leaveUnion(const CXXRecordDecl *, FieldDecl *) { return true; }
1423 
1424  // The following are used for stepping through array elements.
1425  virtual bool enterArray(FieldDecl *, QualType ArrayTy, QualType ElementTy) {
1426  return true;
1427  }
1428  virtual bool leaveArray(FieldDecl *, QualType ArrayTy, QualType ElementTy) {
1429  return true;
1430  }
1431 
1432  virtual bool nextElement(QualType, uint64_t) { return true; }
1433 
1434  virtual ~SyclKernelFieldHandlerBase() = default;
1435 };
1436 
1437 // A class to act as the direct base for all the SYCL OpenCL Kernel construction
1438 // tasks that contains a reference to Sema (and potentially any other
1439 // universally required data).
1440 class SyclKernelFieldHandler : public SyclKernelFieldHandlerBase {
1441 protected:
1442  Sema &SemaRef;
1443  SyclKernelFieldHandler(Sema &S) : SemaRef(S) {}
1444 };
1445 
1446 // A class to represent the 'do nothing' case for filtering purposes.
1447 class SyclEmptyHandler final : public SyclKernelFieldHandlerBase {};
1448 SyclEmptyHandler GlobalEmptyHandler;
1449 
1450 template <bool Keep, typename H> struct HandlerFilter;
1451 template <typename H> struct HandlerFilter<true, H> {
1452  H &Handler;
1453  HandlerFilter(H &Handler) : Handler(Handler) {}
1454 };
1455 template <typename H> struct HandlerFilter<false, H> {
1456  SyclEmptyHandler &Handler = GlobalEmptyHandler;
1457  HandlerFilter(H &Handler) {}
1458 };
1459 
1460 template <bool B, bool... Rest> struct AnyTrue;
1461 
1462 template <bool B> struct AnyTrue<B> { static constexpr bool Value = B; };
1463 
1464 template <bool B, bool... Rest> struct AnyTrue {
1465  static constexpr bool Value = B || AnyTrue<Rest...>::Value;
1466 };
1467 
1468 template <bool B, bool... Rest> struct AllTrue;
1469 
1470 template <bool B> struct AllTrue<B> { static constexpr bool Value = B; };
1471 
1472 template <bool B, bool... Rest> struct AllTrue {
1473  static constexpr bool Value = B && AllTrue<Rest...>::Value;
1474 };
1475 
1476 template <typename ParentTy, typename... Handlers>
1477 void KernelObjVisitor::VisitUnion(const CXXRecordDecl *Owner, ParentTy &Parent,
1478  const CXXRecordDecl *Wrapper,
1479  Handlers &... handlers) {
1480  // Don't continue descending if none of the handlers 'care'. This could be 'if
1481  // constexpr' starting in C++17. Until then, we have to count on the
1482  // optimizer to realize "if (false)" is a dead branch.
1483  if (AnyTrue<Handlers::VisitUnionBody...>::Value)
1484  VisitUnionImpl(
1485  Owner, Parent, Wrapper,
1486  HandlerFilter<Handlers::VisitUnionBody, Handlers>(handlers).Handler...);
1487 }
1488 
1489 template <typename... Handlers>
1490 void KernelObjVisitor::visitNthArrayElement(const CXXRecordDecl *Owner,
1491  FieldDecl *ArrayField,
1492  QualType ElementTy, uint64_t Index,
1493  Handlers &... handlers) {
1494  // Don't continue descending if none of the handlers 'care'. This could be 'if
1495  // constexpr' starting in C++17. Until then, we have to count on the
1496  // optimizer to realize "if (false)" is a dead branch.
1497  if (AnyTrue<Handlers::VisitNthArrayElement...>::Value)
1498  visitArrayElementImpl(
1499  Owner, ArrayField, ElementTy, Index,
1500  HandlerFilter<Handlers::VisitNthArrayElement, Handlers>(handlers)
1501  .Handler...);
1502 }
1503 
1504 template <typename ParentTy, typename... HandlerTys>
1505 void KernelObjVisitor::visitRecord(const CXXRecordDecl *Owner, ParentTy &Parent,
1506  const CXXRecordDecl *Wrapper,
1507  QualType RecordTy,
1508  HandlerTys &... Handlers) {
1509  RecordDecl *RD = RecordTy->getAsRecordDecl();
1510  assert(RD && "should not be null.");
1511  if (RD->hasAttr<SYCLRequiresDecompositionAttr>()) {
1512  // If this container requires decomposition, we have to visit it as
1513  // 'complex', so all handlers are called in this case with the 'complex'
1514  // case.
1515  visitComplexRecord(Owner, Parent, Wrapper, RecordTy, Handlers...);
1516  } else {
1517  // "Simple" Containers are those that do NOT need to be decomposed,
1518  // "Complex" containers are those that DO. In the case where the container
1519  // does NOT need to be decomposed, we can call VisitSimpleRecord on the
1520  // handlers that have opted-out of VisitInsideSimpleContainers. The 'if'
1521  // makes sure we only do that if at least 1 has opted out.
1522  if (!AllTrue<HandlerTys::VisitInsideSimpleContainers...>::Value)
1523  visitSimpleRecord(
1524  Owner, Parent, Wrapper, RecordTy,
1525  HandlerFilter<!HandlerTys::VisitInsideSimpleContainers, HandlerTys>(
1526  Handlers)
1527  .Handler...);
1528 
1529  // Even though this is a 'simple' container, some handlers (via
1530  // VisitInsideSimpleContainers = true) need to treat it as if it needs
1531  // decomposing, so we call VisitComplexRecord iif at least one has.
1532  if (AnyTrue<HandlerTys::VisitInsideSimpleContainers...>::Value)
1533  visitComplexRecord(
1534  Owner, Parent, Wrapper, RecordTy,
1535  HandlerFilter<HandlerTys::VisitInsideSimpleContainers, HandlerTys>(
1536  Handlers)
1537  .Handler...);
1538  }
1539 }
1540 
1541 template <typename... HandlerTys>
1542 void KernelObjVisitor::visitArray(const CXXRecordDecl *Owner, FieldDecl *Field,
1543  QualType ArrayTy, HandlerTys &... Handlers) {
1544 
1545  if (Field->hasAttr<SYCLRequiresDecompositionAttr>()) {
1546  visitComplexArray(Owner, Field, ArrayTy, Handlers...);
1547  } else {
1548  if (!AllTrue<HandlerTys::VisitInsideSimpleContainers...>::Value)
1549  visitSimpleArray(
1550  Owner, Field, ArrayTy,
1551  HandlerFilter<!HandlerTys::VisitInsideSimpleContainers, HandlerTys>(
1552  Handlers)
1553  .Handler...);
1554 
1555  if (AnyTrue<HandlerTys::VisitInsideSimpleContainers...>::Value)
1556  visitComplexArray(
1557  Owner, Field, ArrayTy,
1558  HandlerFilter<HandlerTys::VisitInsideSimpleContainers, HandlerTys>(
1559  Handlers)
1560  .Handler...);
1561  }
1562 }
1563 
1564 // A type to check the validity of all of the argument types.
1565 class SyclKernelFieldChecker : public SyclKernelFieldHandler {
1566  bool IsInvalid = false;
1567  DiagnosticsEngine &Diag;
1568  bool IsSIMD = false;
1569  // Check whether the object should be disallowed from being copied to kernel.
1570  // Return true if not copyable, false if copyable.
1571  bool checkNotCopyableToKernel(const FieldDecl *FD, QualType FieldTy) {
1572  if (FieldTy->isArrayType()) {
1573  if (const auto *CAT =
1574  SemaRef.getASTContext().getAsConstantArrayType(FieldTy)) {
1575  QualType ET = CAT->getElementType();
1576  return checkNotCopyableToKernel(FD, ET);
1577  }
1578  return Diag.Report(FD->getLocation(),
1579  diag::err_sycl_non_constant_array_type)
1580  << FieldTy;
1581  }
1582 
1583  return false;
1584  }
1585 
1586  bool checkPropertyListType(TemplateArgument PropList, SourceLocation Loc) {
1587  if (PropList.getKind() != TemplateArgument::ArgKind::Type)
1588  return SemaRef.Diag(
1589  Loc, diag::err_sycl_invalid_accessor_property_template_param);
1590 
1591  QualType PropListTy = PropList.getAsType();
1592  if (!Util::isAccessorPropertyListType(PropListTy))
1593  return SemaRef.Diag(
1594  Loc, diag::err_sycl_invalid_accessor_property_template_param);
1595 
1596  const auto *AccPropListDecl =
1597  cast<ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl>(PropListTy->getAsRecordDecl());
1598  if (AccPropListDecl->getTemplateArgs().size() != 1)
1599  return SemaRef.Diag(Loc,
1600  diag::err_sycl_invalid_property_list_param_number)
1601  << "accessor_property_list";
1602 
1603  const auto TemplArg = AccPropListDecl->getTemplateArgs()[0];
1604  if (TemplArg.getKind() != TemplateArgument::ArgKind::Pack)
1605  return SemaRef.Diag(
1606  Loc,
1607  diag::err_sycl_invalid_accessor_property_list_template_param)
1608  << /*accessor_property_list*/ 0 << /*parameter pack*/ 0;
1609 
1610  for (TemplateArgument::pack_iterator Prop = TemplArg.pack_begin();
1611  Prop != TemplArg.pack_end(); ++Prop) {
1612  if (Prop->getKind() != TemplateArgument::ArgKind::Type)
1613  return SemaRef.Diag(
1614  Loc,
1615  diag::err_sycl_invalid_accessor_property_list_template_param)
1616  << /*accessor_property_list pack argument*/ 1 << /*type*/ 1;
1617  QualType PropTy = Prop->getAsType();
1618  if (Util::isSyclBufferLocationType(PropTy) &&
1619  checkBufferLocationType(PropTy, Loc))
1620  return true;
1621  }
1622  return false;
1623  }
1624 
1625  bool checkBufferLocationType(QualType PropTy, SourceLocation Loc) {
1626  const auto *PropDecl =
1627  cast<ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl>(PropTy->getAsRecordDecl());
1628  if (PropDecl->getTemplateArgs().size() != 1)
1629  return SemaRef.Diag(Loc,
1630  diag::err_sycl_invalid_property_list_param_number)
1631  << "buffer_location";
1632 
1633  const auto BufferLoc = PropDecl->getTemplateArgs()[0];
1634  if (BufferLoc.getKind() != TemplateArgument::ArgKind::Integral)
1635  return SemaRef.Diag(
1636  Loc,
1637  diag::err_sycl_invalid_accessor_property_list_template_param)
1638  << /*buffer_location*/ 2 << /*non-negative integer*/ 2;
1639 
1640  int LocationID = static_cast<int>(BufferLoc.getAsIntegral().getExtValue());
1641  if (LocationID < 0)
1642  return SemaRef.Diag(
1643  Loc,
1644  diag::err_sycl_invalid_accessor_property_list_template_param)
1645  << /*buffer_location*/ 2 << /*non-negative integer*/ 2;
1646 
1647  return false;
1648  }
1649 
1650  bool checkSyclSpecialType(QualType Ty, SourceRange Loc) {
1651  assert(Util::isSyclSpecialType(Ty) &&
1652  "Should only be called on sycl special class types.");
1653  const RecordDecl *RecD = Ty->getAsRecordDecl();
1654  if (IsSIMD && !Util::isSyclType(Ty, "accessor", true /*Tmp*/))
1655  return SemaRef.Diag(Loc.getBegin(),
1656  diag::err_sycl_esimd_not_supported_for_type)
1657  << RecD;
1658  if (const ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl *CTSD =
1659  dyn_cast<ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl>(RecD)) {
1660  const TemplateArgumentList &TAL = CTSD->getTemplateArgs();
1661  TemplateArgument TA = TAL.get(0);
1662 
1663  // Parameter packs are used by properties so they are always valid.
1664  if (TA.getKind() != TemplateArgument::Pack) {
1665  llvm::DenseSet<QualType> Visited;
1666  checkSYCLType(SemaRef, TA.getAsType(), Loc, Visited);
1667  }
1668 
1669  if (TAL.size() > 5)
1670  return checkPropertyListType(TAL.get(5), Loc.getBegin());
1671  }
1672  return false;
1673  }
1674 
1675 public:
1676  SyclKernelFieldChecker(Sema &S, bool isSIMD)
1677  : SyclKernelFieldHandler(S), Diag(S.getASTContext().getDiagnostics()),
1678  IsSIMD(isSIMD) {}
1679  static constexpr const bool VisitNthArrayElement = false;
1680  bool isValid() { return !IsInvalid; }
1681 
1682  bool handleReferenceType(FieldDecl *FD, QualType FieldTy) final {
1683  Diag.Report(FD->getLocation(), diag::err_bad_kernel_param_type) << FieldTy;
1684  IsInvalid = true;
1685  return isValid();
1686  }
1687 
1688  bool handleStructType(FieldDecl *FD, QualType FieldTy) final {
1689  IsInvalid |= checkNotCopyableToKernel(FD, FieldTy);
1690  CXXRecordDecl *RD = FieldTy->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
1691  assert(RD && "Not a RecordDecl inside the handler for struct type");
1692  if (RD->isLambda()) {
1693  for (const LambdaCapture &LC : RD->captures())
1694  if (LC.capturesThis() && LC.isImplicit()) {
1695  SemaRef.Diag(LC.getLocation(), diag::err_implicit_this_capture);
1696  IsInvalid = true;
1697  }
1698  }
1699  return isValid();
1700  }
1701 
1702  bool handleSyclSpecialType(const CXXRecordDecl *, const CXXBaseSpecifier &BS,
1703  QualType FieldTy) final {
1704  IsInvalid |= checkSyclSpecialType(FieldTy, BS.getBeginLoc());
1705  return isValid();
1706  }
1707 
1708  bool handleSyclSpecialType(FieldDecl *FD, QualType FieldTy) final {
1709  IsInvalid |= checkSyclSpecialType(FieldTy, FD->getLocation());
1710  return isValid();
1711  }
1712 
1713  bool handleArrayType(FieldDecl *FD, QualType FieldTy) final {
1714  IsInvalid |= checkNotCopyableToKernel(FD, FieldTy);
1715  return isValid();
1716  }
1717 
1718  bool handlePointerType(FieldDecl *FD, QualType FieldTy) final {
1719  while (FieldTy->isAnyPointerType()) {
1720  FieldTy = QualType{FieldTy->getPointeeOrArrayElementType(), 0};
1721  if (FieldTy->isVariableArrayType()) {
1722  Diag.Report(FD->getLocation(), diag::err_vla_unsupported);
1723  IsInvalid = true;
1724  break;
1725  }
1726  }
1727  return isValid();
1728  }
1729 
1730  bool handleOtherType(FieldDecl *FD, QualType FieldTy) final {
1731  Diag.Report(FD->getLocation(), diag::err_bad_kernel_param_type) << FieldTy;
1732  IsInvalid = true;
1733  return isValid();
1734  }
1735 };
1736 
1737 // A type to check the validity of accessing accessor/sampler/stream
1738 // types as kernel parameters inside union.
1739 class SyclKernelUnionChecker : public SyclKernelFieldHandler {
1740  int UnionCount = 0;
1741  bool IsInvalid = false;
1742  DiagnosticsEngine &Diag;
1743 
1744 public:
1745  SyclKernelUnionChecker(Sema &S)
1746  : SyclKernelFieldHandler(S), Diag(S.getASTContext().getDiagnostics()) {}
1747  bool isValid() { return !IsInvalid; }
1748  static constexpr const bool VisitUnionBody = true;
1749  static constexpr const bool VisitNthArrayElement = false;
1750 
1751  bool checkType(SourceLocation Loc, QualType Ty) {
1752  if (UnionCount) {
1753  IsInvalid = true;
1754  Diag.Report(Loc, diag::err_bad_union_kernel_param_members) << Ty;
1755  }
1756  return isValid();
1757  }
1758 
1759  bool enterUnion(const CXXRecordDecl *RD, FieldDecl *FD) override {
1760  ++UnionCount;
1761  return true;
1762  }
1763 
1764  bool leaveUnion(const CXXRecordDecl *RD, FieldDecl *FD) override {
1765  --UnionCount;
1766  return true;
1767  }
1768 
1769  bool handleSyclSpecialType(FieldDecl *FD, QualType FieldTy) final {
1770  return checkType(FD->getLocation(), FieldTy);
1771  }
1772 
1773  bool handleSyclSpecialType(const CXXRecordDecl *, const CXXBaseSpecifier &BS,
1774  QualType FieldTy) final {
1775  return checkType(BS.getBeginLoc(), FieldTy);
1776  }
1777 };
