1779 // A type to mark whether a collection requires decomposition.
1780 class SyclKernelDecompMarker : public SyclKernelFieldHandler {
1781  llvm::SmallVector<bool, 16> CollectionStack;
1782 
1783 public:
1784  static constexpr const bool VisitUnionBody = false;
1785  static constexpr const bool VisitNthArrayElement = false;
1786 
1787  SyclKernelDecompMarker(Sema &S) : SyclKernelFieldHandler(S) {
1788  // In order to prevent checking this over and over, just add a dummy-base
1789  // entry.
1790  CollectionStack.push_back(true);
1791  }
1792 
1793  bool handleSyclSpecialType(const CXXRecordDecl *, const CXXBaseSpecifier &,
1794  QualType) final {
1795  CollectionStack.back() = true;
1796  return true;
1797  }
1798  bool handleSyclSpecialType(FieldDecl *, QualType) final {
1799  CollectionStack.back() = true;
1800  return true;
1801  }
1802 
1803  bool handleSyclSpecConstantType(FieldDecl *, QualType) final {
1804  CollectionStack.back() = true;
1805  return true;
1806  }
1807 
1808  bool handlePointerType(FieldDecl *, QualType) final {
1809  CollectionStack.back() = true;
1810  return true;
1811  }
1812 
1813  bool enterStruct(const CXXRecordDecl *, FieldDecl *, QualType) final {
1814  CollectionStack.push_back(false);
1815  return true;
1816  }
1817 
1818  bool leaveStruct(const CXXRecordDecl *, FieldDecl *, QualType Ty) final {
1819  if (CollectionStack.pop_back_val()) {
1820  RecordDecl *RD = Ty->getAsRecordDecl();
1821  assert(RD && "should not be null.");
1822  if (!RD->hasAttr<SYCLRequiresDecompositionAttr>())
1823  RD->addAttr(SYCLRequiresDecompositionAttr::CreateImplicit(
1824  SemaRef.getASTContext()));
1825  CollectionStack.back() = true;
1826  }
1827  return true;
1828  }
1829 
1830  bool enterStruct(const CXXRecordDecl *, const CXXBaseSpecifier &,
1831  QualType) final {
1832  CollectionStack.push_back(false);
1833  return true;
1834  }
1835 
1836  bool leaveStruct(const CXXRecordDecl *, const CXXBaseSpecifier &,
1837  QualType Ty) final {
1838  if (CollectionStack.pop_back_val()) {
1839  RecordDecl *RD = Ty->getAsRecordDecl();
1840  assert(RD && "should not be null.");
1841  if (!RD->hasAttr<SYCLRequiresDecompositionAttr>())
1842  RD->addAttr(SYCLRequiresDecompositionAttr::CreateImplicit(
1843  SemaRef.getASTContext()));
1844  CollectionStack.back() = true;
1845  }
1846 
1847  return true;
1848  }
1849 
1850  bool enterArray(FieldDecl *, QualType ArrayTy, QualType ElementTy) final {
1851  CollectionStack.push_back(false);
1852  return true;
1853  }
1854 
1855  bool leaveArray(FieldDecl *FD, QualType ArrayTy, QualType ElementTy) final {
1856  if (CollectionStack.pop_back_val()) {
1857  // Cannot assert, since in MD arrays we'll end up marking them multiple
1858  // times.
1859  if (!FD->hasAttr<SYCLRequiresDecompositionAttr>())
1860  FD->addAttr(SYCLRequiresDecompositionAttr::CreateImplicit(
1861  SemaRef.getASTContext()));
1862  CollectionStack.back() = true;
1863  }
1864  return true;
1865  }
1866 };
1867 
1868 // A type to Create and own the FunctionDecl for the kernel.
1869 class SyclKernelDeclCreator : public SyclKernelFieldHandler {
1870  FunctionDecl *KernelDecl;
1871  llvm::SmallVector<ParmVarDecl *, 8> Params;
1872  Sema::ContextRAII FuncContext;
1873  // Holds the last handled field's first parameter. This doesn't store an
1874  // iterator as push_back invalidates iterators.
1875  size_t LastParamIndex = 0;
1876  // Keeps track of whether we are currently handling fields inside a struct.
1877  int StructDepth = 0;
1878 
1879  void addParam(const FieldDecl *FD, QualType FieldTy) {
1880  ParamDesc newParamDesc = makeParamDesc(FD, FieldTy);
1881  addParam(newParamDesc, FieldTy);
1882  }
1883 
1884  void addParam(const CXXBaseSpecifier &BS, QualType FieldTy) {
1885  // TODO: There is no name for the base available, but duplicate names are
1886  // seemingly already possible, so we'll give them all the same name for now.
1887  // This only happens with the accessor types.
1888  StringRef Name = "_arg__base";
1889  ParamDesc newParamDesc =
1890  makeParamDesc(SemaRef.getASTContext(), Name, FieldTy);
1891  addParam(newParamDesc, FieldTy);
1892  }
1893  // Add a parameter with specified name and type
1894  void addParam(StringRef Name, QualType ParamTy) {
1895  ParamDesc newParamDesc =
1896  makeParamDesc(SemaRef.getASTContext(), Name, ParamTy);
1897  addParam(newParamDesc, ParamTy);
1898  }
1899 
1900  void addParam(ParamDesc newParamDesc, QualType FieldTy) {
1901  // Create a new ParmVarDecl based on the new info.
1902  ASTContext &Ctx = SemaRef.getASTContext();
1903  auto *NewParam = ParmVarDecl::Create(
1904  Ctx, KernelDecl, SourceLocation(), SourceLocation(),
1905  std::get<1>(newParamDesc), std::get<0>(newParamDesc),
1906  std::get<2>(newParamDesc), SC_None, /*DefArg*/ nullptr);
1907  NewParam->setScopeInfo(0, Params.size());
1908  NewParam->setIsUsed();
1909 
1910  LastParamIndex = Params.size();
1911  Params.push_back(NewParam);
1912  }
1913 
1914  // Handle accessor properties. If any properties were found in
1915  // the accessor_property_list - add the appropriate attributes to ParmVarDecl.
1916  void handleAccessorPropertyList(ParmVarDecl *Param,
1917  const CXXRecordDecl *RecordDecl,
1918  SourceLocation Loc) {
1919  const auto *AccTy = cast<ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl>(RecordDecl);
1920  if (AccTy->getTemplateArgs().size() < 6)
1921  return;
1922  const auto PropList = cast<TemplateArgument>(AccTy->getTemplateArgs()[5]);
1923  QualType PropListTy = PropList.getAsType();
1924  const auto *AccPropListDecl =
1925  cast<ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl>(PropListTy->getAsRecordDecl());
1926  const auto TemplArg = AccPropListDecl->getTemplateArgs()[0];
1927  // Move through TemplateArgs list of a property list and search for
1928  // properties. If found - apply the appropriate attribute to ParmVarDecl.
1929  for (TemplateArgument::pack_iterator Prop = TemplArg.pack_begin();
1930  Prop != TemplArg.pack_end(); ++Prop) {
1931  QualType PropTy = Prop->getAsType();
1932  if (Util::isSyclAccessorNoAliasPropertyType(PropTy))
1933  handleNoAliasProperty(Param, PropTy, Loc);
1934  if (Util::isSyclBufferLocationType(PropTy))
1935  handleBufferLocationProperty(Param, PropTy, Loc);
1936  }
1937  }
1938 
1939  void handleNoAliasProperty(ParmVarDecl *Param, QualType PropTy,
1940  SourceLocation Loc) {
1941  ASTContext &Ctx = SemaRef.getASTContext();
1942  Param->addAttr(RestrictAttr::CreateImplicit(Ctx, Loc));
1943  }
1944 
1945  // Obtain an integer value stored in a template parameter of buffer_location
1946  // property to pass it to buffer_location kernel attribute
1947  void handleBufferLocationProperty(ParmVarDecl *Param, QualType PropTy,
1948  SourceLocation Loc) {
1949  // If we have more than 1 buffer_location properties on a single
1950  // accessor - emit an error
1951  if (Param->hasAttr<SYCLIntelBufferLocationAttr>()) {
1952  SemaRef.Diag(Loc, diag::err_sycl_compiletime_property_duplication)
1953  << "buffer_location";
1954  return;
1955  }
1956  ASTContext &Ctx = SemaRef.getASTContext();
1957  const auto *PropDecl =
1958  cast<ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl>(PropTy->getAsRecordDecl());
1959  const auto BufferLoc = PropDecl->getTemplateArgs()[0];
1960  int LocationID = static_cast<int>(BufferLoc.getAsIntegral().getExtValue());
1961  Param->addAttr(
1962  SYCLIntelBufferLocationAttr::CreateImplicit(Ctx, LocationID));
1963  }
1964 
1965  // Additional processing is required for accessor type.
1966  void handleAccessorType(const CXXRecordDecl *RecordDecl, SourceLocation Loc) {
1967  handleAccessorPropertyList(Params.back(), RecordDecl, Loc);
1968  // Get access mode of accessor.
1969  const auto *AccessorSpecializationDecl =
1970  cast<ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl>(RecordDecl);
1971  const TemplateArgument &AccessModeArg =
1972  AccessorSpecializationDecl->getTemplateArgs().get(2);
1973 
1974  // Add implicit attribute to parameter decl when it is a read only
1975  // SYCL accessor.
1976  if (isReadOnlyAccessor(AccessModeArg))
1977  Params.back()->addAttr(
1978  SYCLAccessorReadonlyAttr::CreateImplicit(SemaRef.getASTContext()));
1979  Params.back()->addAttr(
1980  SYCLAccessorPtrAttr::CreateImplicit(SemaRef.getASTContext()));
1981  }
1982 
1983  // All special SYCL objects must have __init method. We extract types for
1984  // kernel parameters from __init method parameters. We will use __init method
1985  // and kernel parameters which we build here to initialize special objects in
1986  // the kernel body.
1987  bool handleSpecialType(FieldDecl *FD, QualType FieldTy) {
1988  const auto *RecordDecl = FieldTy->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
1989  assert(RecordDecl && "The type must be a RecordDecl");
1990  llvm::StringLiteral MethodName =
1991  KernelDecl->hasAttr<SYCLSimdAttr>() &&
1992  Util::isSyclType(FieldTy, "accessor", true /*Tmp*/)
1993  ? InitESIMDMethodName
1994  : InitMethodName;
1995  CXXMethodDecl *InitMethod = getMethodByName(RecordDecl, MethodName);
1996  assert(InitMethod && "The type must have the __init method");
1997 
1998  // Don't do -1 here because we count on this to be the first parameter added
1999  // (if any).
2000  size_t ParamIndex = Params.size();
2001  for (const ParmVarDecl *Param : InitMethod->parameters()) {
2002  QualType ParamTy = Param->getType();
2003  addParam(FD, ParamTy.getCanonicalType());
2004 
2005  // Propagate add_ir_attributes_kernel_parameter attribute.
2006  if (const auto *AddIRAttr =
2007  Param->getAttr<SYCLAddIRAttributesKernelParameterAttr>())
2008  Params.back()->addAttr(AddIRAttr->clone(SemaRef.getASTContext()));
2009 
2010  // FIXME: This code is temporary, and will be removed once __init_esimd
2011  // is removed and property list refactored.
2012  // The function handleAccessorType includes a call to
2013  // handleAccessorPropertyList. If new classes with property list are
2014  // added, this code needs to be refactored to call
2015  // handleAccessorPropertyList for each class which requires it.
2016  if (ParamTy.getTypePtr()->isPointerType() &&
2017  Util::isSyclType(FieldTy, "accessor", true /*Tmp*/))
2018  handleAccessorType(RecordDecl, FD->getBeginLoc());
2019  }
2020  LastParamIndex = ParamIndex;
2021  return true;
2022  }
2023 
2024  static void setKernelImplicitAttrs(ASTContext &Context, FunctionDecl *FD,
2025  bool IsSIMDKernel) {
2026  // Set implicit attributes.
2027  FD->addAttr(OpenCLKernelAttr::CreateImplicit(Context));
2028  FD->addAttr(ArtificialAttr::CreateImplicit(Context));
2029  if (IsSIMDKernel)
2030  FD->addAttr(SYCLSimdAttr::CreateImplicit(Context));
2031  }
2032 
2033  static FunctionDecl *createKernelDecl(ASTContext &Ctx, SourceLocation Loc,
2034  bool IsInline, bool IsSIMDKernel) {
2035  // Create this with no prototype, and we can fix this up after we've seen
2036  // all the params.
2037  FunctionProtoType::ExtProtoInfo Info(CC_OpenCLKernel);
2038  QualType FuncType = Ctx.getFunctionType(Ctx.VoidTy, {}, Info);
2039 
2040  FunctionDecl *FD = FunctionDecl::Create(
2041  Ctx, Ctx.getTranslationUnitDecl(), Loc, Loc, DeclarationName(),
2042  FuncType, Ctx.getTrivialTypeSourceInfo(Ctx.VoidTy), SC_None);
2043  FD->setImplicitlyInline(IsInline);
2044  setKernelImplicitAttrs(Ctx, FD, IsSIMDKernel);
2045 
2046  // Add kernel to translation unit to see it in AST-dump.
2047  Ctx.getTranslationUnitDecl()->addDecl(FD);
2048  return FD;
2049  }
2050 
2051 public:
2052  static constexpr const bool VisitInsideSimpleContainers = false;
2053  SyclKernelDeclCreator(Sema &S, SourceLocation Loc, bool IsInline,
2054  bool IsSIMDKernel, FunctionDecl *SYCLKernel)
2055  : SyclKernelFieldHandler(S),
2056  KernelDecl(
2057  createKernelDecl(S.getASTContext(), Loc, IsInline, IsSIMDKernel)),
2058  FuncContext(SemaRef, KernelDecl) {
2059  S.addSyclOpenCLKernel(SYCLKernel, KernelDecl);
2060  }
2061 
2062  ~SyclKernelDeclCreator() {
2063  ASTContext &Ctx = SemaRef.getASTContext();
2064  FunctionProtoType::ExtProtoInfo Info(CC_OpenCLKernel);
2065 
2066  SmallVector<QualType, 8> ArgTys;
2067  std::transform(std::begin(Params), std::end(Params),
2068  std::back_inserter(ArgTys),
2069  [](const ParmVarDecl *PVD) { return PVD->getType(); });
2070 
2071  QualType FuncType = Ctx.getFunctionType(Ctx.VoidTy, ArgTys, Info);
2072  KernelDecl->setType(FuncType);
2073  KernelDecl->setParams(Params);
2074 
2075  // Make sure that this is marked as a kernel so that the code-gen can make
2076  // decisions based on that. We cannot add this earlier, otherwise the call
2077  // to TransformStmt in replaceWithLocalClone can diagnose something that got
2078  // diagnosed on the actual kernel.
2079  KernelDecl->addAttr(
2080  SYCLKernelAttr::CreateImplicit(SemaRef.getASTContext()));
2081 
2082  SemaRef.addSyclDeviceDecl(KernelDecl);
2083  }
2084 
2085  bool enterStruct(const CXXRecordDecl *, FieldDecl *, QualType) final {
2086  ++StructDepth;
2087  return true;
2088  }
2089 
2090  bool leaveStruct(const CXXRecordDecl *, FieldDecl *, QualType) final {
2091  --StructDepth;
2092  return true;
2093  }
2094 
2095  bool enterStruct(const CXXRecordDecl *, const CXXBaseSpecifier &BS,
2096  QualType FieldTy) final {
2097  ++StructDepth;
2098  return true;
2099  }
2100 
2101  bool leaveStruct(const CXXRecordDecl *, const CXXBaseSpecifier &BS,
2102  QualType FieldTy) final {
2103  --StructDepth;
2104  return true;
2105  }
2106 
2107  bool handleSyclSpecialType(const CXXRecordDecl *, const CXXBaseSpecifier &BS,
2108  QualType FieldTy) final {
2109  const auto *RecordDecl = FieldTy->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
2110  assert(RecordDecl && "The type must be a RecordDecl");
2111  llvm::StringLiteral MethodName =
2112  KernelDecl->hasAttr<SYCLSimdAttr>() &&
2113  Util::isSyclType(FieldTy, "accessor", true /*Tmp*/)
2114  ? InitESIMDMethodName
2115  : InitMethodName;
2116  CXXMethodDecl *InitMethod = getMethodByName(RecordDecl, MethodName);
2117  assert(InitMethod && "The type must have the __init method");
2118 
2119  // Don't do -1 here because we count on this to be the first parameter added
2120  // (if any).
2121  size_t ParamIndex = Params.size();
2122  for (const ParmVarDecl *Param : InitMethod->parameters()) {
2123  QualType ParamTy = Param->getType();
2124  addParam(BS, ParamTy.getCanonicalType());
2125  // FIXME: This code is temporary, and will be removed once __init_esimd
2126  // is removed and property list refactored.
2127  // The function handleAccessorType includes a call to
2128  // handleAccessorPropertyList. If new classes with property list are
2129  // added, this code needs to be refactored to call
2130  // handleAccessorPropertyList for each class which requires it.
2131  if (ParamTy.getTypePtr()->isPointerType() &&
2132  Util::isSyclType(FieldTy, "accessor", true /*Tmp*/))
2133  handleAccessorType(RecordDecl, BS.getBeginLoc());
2134  }
2135  LastParamIndex = ParamIndex;
2136  return true;
2137  }
2138 
2139  bool handleSyclSpecialType(FieldDecl *FD, QualType FieldTy) final {
2140  return handleSpecialType(FD, FieldTy);
2141  }
2142 
2143  RecordDecl *wrapField(FieldDecl *Field, QualType FieldTy) {
2144  RecordDecl *WrapperClass =
2145  SemaRef.getASTContext().buildImplicitRecord("__wrapper_class");
2146  WrapperClass->startDefinition();
2147  Field = FieldDecl::Create(
2148  SemaRef.getASTContext(), WrapperClass, SourceLocation(),
2149  SourceLocation(), /*Id=*/nullptr, FieldTy,
2150  SemaRef.getASTContext().getTrivialTypeSourceInfo(FieldTy,
2151  SourceLocation()),
2152  /*BW=*/nullptr, /*Mutable=*/false, /*InitStyle=*/ICIS_NoInit);
2153  Field->setAccess(AS_public);
2154  WrapperClass->addDecl(Field);
2155  WrapperClass->completeDefinition();
2156  return WrapperClass;
2157  };
2158 
2159  bool handlePointerType(FieldDecl *FD, QualType FieldTy) final {
2160  // USM allows to use raw pointers instead of buffers/accessors, but these
2161  // pointers point to the specially allocated memory. For pointer fields we
2162  // add a kernel argument with the same type as field but global address
2163  // space, because OpenCL requires it.
2164  QualType PointeeTy = FieldTy->getPointeeType();
2165  Qualifiers Quals = PointeeTy.getQualifiers();
2166  auto AS = Quals.getAddressSpace();
2167  // Leave global_device and global_host address spaces as is to help FPGA
2168  // device in memory allocations
2169  if (AS != LangAS::sycl_global_device && AS != LangAS::sycl_global_host)
2170  Quals.setAddressSpace(LangAS::sycl_global);
2171  PointeeTy = SemaRef.getASTContext().getQualifiedType(
2172  PointeeTy.getUnqualifiedType(), Quals);
2173  QualType ModTy = SemaRef.getASTContext().getPointerType(PointeeTy);
2174  // When the kernel is generated, struct type kernel arguments are
2175  // decomposed; i.e. the parameters of the kernel are the fields of the
2176  // struct, and not the struct itself. This causes an error in the backend
2177  // when the struct field is a pointer, since non-USM pointers cannot be
2178  // passed directly. To work around this issue, all pointers inside the
2179  // struct are wrapped in a generated '__wrapper_class'.
2180  if (StructDepth) {
2181  RecordDecl *WrappedPointer = wrapField(FD, ModTy);
2182  ModTy = SemaRef.getASTContext().getRecordType(WrappedPointer);
2183  }
2184 
2185  addParam(FD, ModTy);
2186  return true;
2187  }
2188 
2189  bool handleSimpleArrayType(FieldDecl *FD, QualType FieldTy) final {
2190  // Arrays are always wrapped in a struct since they cannot be passed
2191  // directly.
2192  RecordDecl *WrappedArray = wrapField(FD, FieldTy);
2193  QualType ModTy = SemaRef.getASTContext().getRecordType(WrappedArray);
2194  addParam(FD, ModTy);
2195  return true;
2196  }
2197 
2198  bool handleScalarType(FieldDecl *FD, QualType FieldTy) final {
2199  addParam(FD, FieldTy);
2200  return true;
2201  }
2202 
2203  bool handleNonDecompStruct(const CXXRecordDecl *, FieldDecl *FD,
2204  QualType Ty) final {
2205  addParam(FD, Ty);
2206  return true;
2207  }
2208 
2209  bool handleNonDecompStruct(const CXXRecordDecl *Base,
2210  const CXXBaseSpecifier &BS, QualType Ty) final {
2211  addParam(BS, Ty);
2212  return true;
2213  }
2214 
2215  bool handleUnionType(FieldDecl *FD, QualType FieldTy) final {
2216  return handleScalarType(FD, FieldTy);
2217  }
2218 
2219  // Generate kernel argument to initialize specialization constants.
2220  void handleSyclKernelHandlerType() {
2221  ASTContext &Context = SemaRef.getASTContext();
2222  StringRef Name = "_arg__specialization_constants_buffer";
2223  addParam(Name, Context.getPointerType(Context.getAddrSpaceQualType(
2224  Context.CharTy, LangAS::sycl_global)));
2225  }
2226 
2227  void setBody(CompoundStmt *KB) { KernelDecl->setBody(KB); }
2228 
2229  FunctionDecl *getKernelDecl() { return KernelDecl; }
2230 
2231  llvm::ArrayRef<ParmVarDecl *> getParamVarDeclsForCurrentField() {
2232  return ArrayRef<ParmVarDecl *>(std::begin(Params) + LastParamIndex,
2233  std::end(Params));
2234  }
2235 };

2237 class SyclKernelArgsSizeChecker : public SyclKernelFieldHandler {
2238  SourceLocation KernelLoc;
2239  unsigned SizeOfParams = 0;
2240  bool IsSIMD = false;
2241 
2242  void addParam(QualType ArgTy) {
2243  SizeOfParams +=
2244  SemaRef.getASTContext().getTypeSizeInChars(ArgTy).getQuantity();
2245  }
2246 
2247  bool handleSpecialType(QualType FieldTy) {
2248  const CXXRecordDecl *RecordDecl = FieldTy->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
2249  assert(RecordDecl && "The type must be a RecordDecl");
2250  llvm::StringLiteral MethodName =
2251  (IsSIMD && Util::isSyclType(FieldTy, "accessor", true /*Tmp*/))
2252  ? InitESIMDMethodName
2253  : InitMethodName;
2254  CXXMethodDecl *InitMethod = getMethodByName(RecordDecl, MethodName);
2255  assert(InitMethod && "The type must have the __init method");
2256  for (const ParmVarDecl *Param : InitMethod->parameters())
2257  addParam(Param->getType());
2258  return true;
2259  }

2313 std::string getKernelArgDesc(StringRef KernelArgDescription) {

2320 class SyclOptReportCreator : public SyclKernelFieldHandler {
2321  SyclKernelDeclCreator &DC;
2322  SourceLocation KernelInvocationLoc;
2323 
2324  void addParam(const FieldDecl *KernelArg, QualType KernelArgType,
2325  StringRef KernelArgDescription) {
2326  StringRef NameToEmitInDescription = KernelArg->getName();
2327  const RecordDecl *KernelArgParent = KernelArg->getParent();
2328  if (KernelArgParent && KernelArgDescription == "decomposed struct/class")
2329  NameToEmitInDescription = KernelArgParent->getName();
2330 
2331  bool isWrappedField = KernelArgDescription == "WrappedPointer" ||
2332  KernelArgDescription == "WrappedArray";
2333 
2334  KernelArgDescription =
2335  (KernelArgDescription == "WrappedPointer"
2336  ? "nested pointer"
2337  : (KernelArgDescription == "WrappedArray" ? "array"
2338  : KernelArgDescription));
2339 
2340  unsigned KernelArgSize =
2341  SemaRef.getASTContext().getTypeSizeInChars(KernelArgType).getQuantity();
2342 
2343  SemaRef.getDiagnostics().getSYCLOptReport().AddKernelArgs(
2344  DC.getKernelDecl(), NameToEmitInDescription,
2345  isWrappedField ? "Compiler generated" : KernelArgType.getAsString(),
2346  KernelInvocationLoc, KernelArgSize,
2347  getKernelArgDesc(KernelArgDescription),
2348  (KernelArgDescription == "decomposed struct/class")
2349  ? ("Field:" + KernelArg->getName().str() + ", ")
2350  : "");
2351  }
2352 
2353  void addParam(const FieldDecl *FD, QualType FieldTy) {
2354  std::string KernelArgDescription = FieldTy.getAsString();
2355  const RecordDecl *RD = FD->getParent();
2356  if (FieldTy->isScalarType())
2357  KernelArgDescription = "";
2358  if (RD && RD->hasAttr<SYCLRequiresDecompositionAttr>())
2359  KernelArgDescription = "decomposed struct/class";
2360 
2361  addParam(FD, FieldTy, KernelArgDescription);
2362  }
2363 
2364  // Handles base classes.
2365  void addParam(const CXXBaseSpecifier &, QualType KernelArgType,
2366  StringRef KernelArgDescription) {
2367  unsigned KernelArgSize =
2368  SemaRef.getASTContext().getTypeSizeInChars(KernelArgType).getQuantity();
2369  SemaRef.getDiagnostics().getSYCLOptReport().AddKernelArgs(
2370  DC.getKernelDecl(), KernelArgType.getAsString(),
2371  KernelArgType.getAsString(), KernelInvocationLoc, KernelArgSize,
2372  getKernelArgDesc(KernelArgDescription), "");
2373  }
2374 
2375  // Handles specialization constants.
2376  void addParam(QualType KernelArgType, std::string KernelArgDescription) {
2377  unsigned KernelArgSize =
2378  SemaRef.getASTContext().getTypeSizeInChars(KernelArgType).getQuantity();
2379  SemaRef.getDiagnostics().getSYCLOptReport().AddKernelArgs(
2380  DC.getKernelDecl(), "", KernelArgType.getAsString(),
2381  KernelInvocationLoc, KernelArgSize,
2382  getKernelArgDesc(KernelArgDescription), "");
2383  }

2387  SyclOptReportCreator(Sema &S, SyclKernelDeclCreator &DC, SourceLocation Loc)

2389

2391  for (const auto *Param : DC.getParamVarDeclsForCurrentField())

2395 
2396  bool handleSyclSpecialType(const CXXRecordDecl *, const CXXBaseSpecifier &BS,
2397  QualType FieldTy) final {
2398  std::string KernelArgDescription = "base class " + FieldTy.getAsString();
2399  for (const auto *Param : DC.getParamVarDeclsForCurrentField()) {
2400  QualType KernelArgType = Param->getType();
2401  unsigned KernelArgSize = SemaRef.getASTContext()
2402  .getTypeSizeInChars(KernelArgType)
2403  .getQuantity();
2404  SemaRef.getDiagnostics().getSYCLOptReport().AddKernelArgs(
2405  DC.getKernelDecl(), FieldTy.getAsString(),
2406  KernelArgType.getAsString(), KernelInvocationLoc, KernelArgSize,
2407  getKernelArgDesc(KernelArgDescription), "");
2408  }
2409  return true;
2410  }
2411 
2412  bool handlePointerType(FieldDecl *FD, QualType FieldTy) final {
2413  std::string KernelArgDescription = ":";
2414  ParmVarDecl *KernelParameter = DC.getParamVarDeclsForCurrentField()[0];
2415  // Compiler generated openCL kernel argument for current pointer field
2416  // is not a pointer. This means we are processing a nested pointer and
2417  // the openCL kernel argument is of type __wrapper_class.
2418  if (!KernelParameter->getType()->isPointerType())
2419  KernelArgDescription = "WrappedPointer";
2420  for (const auto *Param : DC.getParamVarDeclsForCurrentField())
2421  addParam(FD, Param->getType(), KernelArgDescription);
2422  return true;
2423  }

2435  }

2459 static CXXMethodDecl *getOperatorParens(const CXXRecordDecl *Rec) {
2460  for (auto *MD : Rec->methods()) {
2461  if (MD->getOverloadedOperator() == OO_Call)
2462  return MD;
2463  }
2464  return nullptr;
2465 }

2467 static bool isESIMDKernelType(const CXXRecordDecl *KernelObjType) {
2468  const CXXMethodDecl *OpParens = getOperatorParens(KernelObjType);
2469  return (OpParens != nullptr) && OpParens->hasAttr<SYCLSimdAttr>();
2470 }

2472 class SyclKernelBodyCreator : public SyclKernelFieldHandler {
2473  SyclKernelDeclCreator &DeclCreator;
2474  llvm::SmallVector<Stmt *, 16> BodyStmts;
2475  llvm::SmallVector<InitListExpr *, 16> CollectionInitExprs;
2476  llvm::SmallVector<Stmt *, 16> FinalizeStmts;
2477  // This collection contains the information required to add/remove information
2478  // about arrays as we enter them. The InitializedEntity component is
2479  // necessary for initializing child members. uin64_t is the index of the
2480  // current element being worked on, which is updated every time we visit
2481  // nextElement.
2482  llvm::SmallVector<std::pair<InitializedEntity, uint64_t>, 8> ArrayInfos;
2483  VarDecl *KernelObjClone;
2484  InitializedEntity VarEntity;
2485  const CXXRecordDecl *KernelObj;
2486  llvm::SmallVector<Expr *, 16> MemberExprBases;
2487  FunctionDecl *KernelCallerFunc;
2488  SourceLocation KernelCallerSrcLoc; // KernelCallerFunc source location.
2489  // Contains a count of how many containers we're in. This is used by the
2490  // pointer-struct-wrapping code to ensure that we don't try to wrap
2491  // non-top-level pointers.
2492  uint64_t StructDepth = 0;
2493  VarDecl *KernelHandlerClone = nullptr;
2494 
2495  Stmt *replaceWithLocalClone(ParmVarDecl *OriginalParam, VarDecl *LocalClone,
2496  Stmt *FunctionBody) {
2497  // DeclRefExpr with valid source location but with decl which is not marked
2498  // as used is invalid.
2499  LocalClone->setIsUsed();
2500  std::pair<DeclaratorDecl *, DeclaratorDecl *> MappingPair =
2501  std::make_pair(OriginalParam, LocalClone);
2502  KernelBodyTransform KBT(MappingPair, SemaRef);
2503  return KBT.TransformStmt(FunctionBody).get();
2504  }
2505 
2506  // Using the statements/init expressions that we've created, this generates
2507  // the kernel body compound stmt. CompoundStmt needs to know its number of
2508  // statements in advance to allocate it, so we cannot do this as we go along.
2509  CompoundStmt *createKernelBody() {
2510  // Push the Kernel function scope to ensure the scope isn't empty
2511  SemaRef.PushFunctionScope();
2512 
2513  // Initialize kernel object local clone
2514  assert(CollectionInitExprs.size() == 1 &&
2515  "Should have been popped down to just the first one");
2516  KernelObjClone->setInit(CollectionInitExprs.back());
2517 
2518  // Replace references to the kernel object in kernel body, to use the
2519  // compiler generated local clone
2520  Stmt *NewBody =
2521  replaceWithLocalClone(KernelCallerFunc->getParamDecl(0), KernelObjClone,
2522  KernelCallerFunc->getBody());
2523 
2524  // If kernel_handler argument is passed by SYCL kernel, replace references
2525  // to this argument in kernel body, to use the compiler generated local
2526  // clone
2527  if (ParmVarDecl *KernelHandlerParam =
2528  getSyclKernelHandlerArg(KernelCallerFunc))
2529  NewBody = replaceWithLocalClone(KernelHandlerParam, KernelHandlerClone,
2530  NewBody);
2531 
2532  // Use transformed body (with clones) as kernel body
2533  BodyStmts.push_back(NewBody);
2534 
2535  BodyStmts.insert(BodyStmts.end(), FinalizeStmts.begin(),
2536  FinalizeStmts.end());
2537 
2538  return CompoundStmt::Create(SemaRef.getASTContext(), BodyStmts, {}, {});
2539  }
2540 
2541  void markParallelWorkItemCalls() {
2542  if (getKernelInvocationKind(KernelCallerFunc) ==
2543  InvokeParallelForWorkGroup) {
2544  FindPFWGLambdaFnVisitor V(KernelObj);
2545  V.TraverseStmt(KernelCallerFunc->getBody());
2546  CXXMethodDecl *WGLambdaFn = V.getLambdaFn();
2547  assert(WGLambdaFn && "PFWG lambda not found");
2548  // Mark the function that it "works" in a work group scope:
2549  // NOTE: In case of parallel_for_work_item the marker call itself is
2550  // marked with work item scope attribute, here the '()' operator of the
2551  // object passed as parameter is marked. This is an optimization -
2552  // there are a lot of locals created at parallel_for_work_group
2553  // scope before calling the lambda - it is more efficient to have
2554  // all of them in the private address space rather then sharing via
2555  // the local AS. See parallel_for_work_group implementation in the
2556  // SYCL headers.
2557  if (!WGLambdaFn->hasAttr<SYCLScopeAttr>()) {
2558  WGLambdaFn->addAttr(SYCLScopeAttr::CreateImplicit(
2559  SemaRef.getASTContext(), SYCLScopeAttr::Level::WorkGroup));
2560  // Search and mark parallel_for_work_item calls:
2561  MarkWIScopeFnVisitor MarkWIScope(SemaRef.getASTContext());
2562  MarkWIScope.TraverseDecl(WGLambdaFn);
2563  // Now mark local variables declared in the PFWG lambda with work group
2564  // scope attribute
2565  addScopeAttrToLocalVars(*WGLambdaFn);
2566  }
2567  }
2568  }
2569 
2570  // Creates a DeclRefExpr to the ParmVar that represents the current field.
2571  Expr *createParamReferenceExpr() {
2572  ParmVarDecl *KernelParameter =
2573  DeclCreator.getParamVarDeclsForCurrentField()[0];
2574 
2575  QualType ParamType = KernelParameter->getOriginalType();
2576  Expr *DRE = SemaRef.BuildDeclRefExpr(KernelParameter, ParamType, VK_LValue,
2577  KernelCallerSrcLoc);
2578  return DRE;
2579  }
2580 
2581  // Creates a DeclRefExpr to the ParmVar that represents the current pointer
2582  // field.
2583  Expr *createPointerParamReferenceExpr(QualType PointerTy, bool Wrapped) {
2584  ParmVarDecl *KernelParameter =
2585  DeclCreator.getParamVarDeclsForCurrentField()[0];
2586 
2587  QualType ParamType = KernelParameter->getOriginalType();
2588  Expr *DRE = SemaRef.BuildDeclRefExpr(KernelParameter, ParamType, VK_LValue,
2589  KernelCallerSrcLoc);
2590 
2591  // Struct Type kernel arguments are decomposed. The pointer fields are
2592  // then wrapped inside a compiler generated struct. Therefore when
2593  // generating the initializers, we have to 'unwrap' the pointer.
2594  if (Wrapped) {
2595  CXXRecordDecl *WrapperStruct = ParamType->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
2596  // Pointer field wrapped inside __wrapper_class
2597  FieldDecl *Pointer = *(WrapperStruct->field_begin());
2598  DRE = buildMemberExpr(DRE, Pointer);
2599  ParamType = Pointer->getType();
2600  }
2601 
2602  DRE = ImplicitCastExpr::Create(SemaRef.Context, ParamType,
2603  CK_LValueToRValue, DRE, /*BasePath=*/nullptr,
2604  VK_PRValue, FPOptionsOverride());
2605 
2606  if (PointerTy->getPointeeType().getAddressSpace() !=
2607  ParamType->getPointeeType().getAddressSpace())
2608  DRE = ImplicitCastExpr::Create(SemaRef.Context, PointerTy,
2609  CK_AddressSpaceConversion, DRE, nullptr,
2610  VK_PRValue, FPOptionsOverride());
2611 
2612  return DRE;
2613  }
2614 
2615  Expr *createSimpleArrayParamReferenceExpr(QualType ArrayTy) {
2616  ParmVarDecl *KernelParameter =
2617  DeclCreator.getParamVarDeclsForCurrentField()[0];
2618  QualType ParamType = KernelParameter->getOriginalType();
2619  Expr *DRE = SemaRef.BuildDeclRefExpr(KernelParameter, ParamType, VK_LValue,
2620  KernelCallerSrcLoc);
2621 
2622  // Unwrap the array.
2623  CXXRecordDecl *WrapperStruct = ParamType->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
2624  FieldDecl *ArrayField = *(WrapperStruct->field_begin());
2625  return buildMemberExpr(DRE, ArrayField);
2626  }
2627 
2628  // Returns 'true' if the thing we're visiting (Based on the FD/QualType pair)
2629  // is an element of an array. This will determine whether we do
2630  // MemberExprBases in some cases or not, AND determines how we initialize
2631  // values.
2632  bool isArrayElement(const FieldDecl *FD, QualType Ty) const {
2633  return !SemaRef.getASTContext().hasSameType(FD->getType(), Ty);
2634  }
2635 
2636  // Creates an initialized entity for a field/item. In the case where this is a
2637  // field, returns a normal member initializer, if we're in a sub-array of a MD
2638  // array, returns an element initializer.
2639  InitializedEntity getFieldEntity(FieldDecl *FD, QualType Ty) {
2640  if (isArrayElement(FD, Ty))
2641  return InitializedEntity::InitializeElement(SemaRef.getASTContext(),
2642  ArrayInfos.back().second,
2643  ArrayInfos.back().first);
2644  return InitializedEntity::InitializeMember(FD, &VarEntity);
2645  }

2648  InitializationKind InitKind =
2649  InitializationKind::CreateCopy(KernelCallerSrcLoc, KernelCallerSrcLoc);
2650  addFieldInit(FD, Ty, ParamRef, InitKind);
2651  }
2652 
2653  void addFieldInit(FieldDecl *FD, QualType Ty, MultiExprArg ParamRef,
2654  InitializationKind InitKind) {
2655  addFieldInit(FD, Ty, ParamRef, InitKind, getFieldEntity(FD, Ty));
2656  }

2658  void addFieldInit(FieldDecl *FD, QualType Ty, MultiExprArg ParamRef,
2659  InitializationKind InitKind, InitializedEntity Entity) {
2660  InitializationSequence InitSeq(SemaRef, Entity, InitKind, ParamRef);
2661  ExprResult Init = InitSeq.Perform(SemaRef, Entity, InitKind, ParamRef);
2662 
2663  InitListExpr *ParentILE = CollectionInitExprs.back();
2664  ParentILE->updateInit(SemaRef.getASTContext(), ParentILE->getNumInits(),
2665  Init.get());
2666  }

2668  void addBaseInit(const CXXBaseSpecifier &BS, QualType Ty,
2669  InitializationKind InitKind) {
2670  InitializedEntity Entity = InitializedEntity::InitializeBase(
2671  SemaRef.Context, &BS, /*IsInheritedVirtualBase*/ false, &VarEntity);
2672  InitializationSequence InitSeq(SemaRef, Entity, InitKind, None);
2673  ExprResult Init = InitSeq.Perform(SemaRef, Entity, InitKind, None);
2674 
2675  InitListExpr *ParentILE = CollectionInitExprs.back();
2676  ParentILE->updateInit(SemaRef.getASTContext(), ParentILE->getNumInits(),
2677  Init.get());
2678  }

2680  void addSimpleBaseInit(const CXXBaseSpecifier &BS, QualType Ty) {
2681  InitializationKind InitKind =
2682  InitializationKind::CreateCopy(KernelCallerSrcLoc, KernelCallerSrcLoc);
2683

2685  SemaRef.Context, &BS, /*IsInheritedVirtualBase*/ false, &VarEntity);
2686 
2687  Expr *ParamRef = createParamReferenceExpr();
2688  InitializationSequence InitSeq(SemaRef, Entity, InitKind, ParamRef);
2689  ExprResult Init = InitSeq.Perform(SemaRef, Entity, InitKind, ParamRef);
2690 
2691  InitListExpr *ParentILE = CollectionInitExprs.back();

2702  MemberExpr *buildMemberExpr(Expr *Base, ValueDecl *Member) {
2703  DeclAccessPair MemberDAP = DeclAccessPair::make(Member, AS_none);
2704  MemberExpr *Result = SemaRef.BuildMemberExpr(
2705  Base, /*IsArrow */ false, KernelCallerSrcLoc, NestedNameSpecifierLoc(),
2706  KernelCallerSrcLoc, Member, MemberDAP,
2707  /*HadMultipleCandidates*/ false,
2708  DeclarationNameInfo(Member->getDeclName(), KernelCallerSrcLoc),
2709  Member->getType(), VK_LValue, OK_Ordinary);
2710  return Result;
2711  }
2712 
2713  void addFieldMemberExpr(FieldDecl *FD, QualType Ty) {
2714  if (!isArrayElement(FD, Ty))
2715  MemberExprBases.push_back(buildMemberExpr(MemberExprBases.back(), FD));
2716  }
2717 
2718  void removeFieldMemberExpr(const FieldDecl *FD, QualType Ty) {
2719  if (!isArrayElement(FD, Ty))
2720  MemberExprBases.pop_back();
2721  }
2722 
2723  void createSpecialMethodCall(const CXXRecordDecl *RD, StringRef MethodName,
2724  SmallVectorImpl<Stmt *> &AddTo) {
2725  CXXMethodDecl *Method = getMethodByName(RD, MethodName);
2726  if (!Method)
2727  return;
2728 
2729  unsigned NumParams = Method->getNumParams();
2730  llvm::SmallVector<Expr *, 4> ParamDREs(NumParams);
2731  llvm::ArrayRef<ParmVarDecl *> KernelParameters =
2732  DeclCreator.getParamVarDeclsForCurrentField();
2733  for (size_t I = 0; I < NumParams; ++I) {
2734  QualType ParamType = KernelParameters[I]->getOriginalType();
2735  ParamDREs[I] = SemaRef.BuildDeclRefExpr(KernelParameters[I], ParamType,
2736  VK_LValue, KernelCallerSrcLoc);
2737  }
2738 
2739  MemberExpr *MethodME = buildMemberExpr(MemberExprBases.back(), Method);
2740 
2741  QualType ResultTy = Method->getReturnType();
2742  ExprValueKind VK = Expr::getValueKindForType(ResultTy);
2743  ResultTy = ResultTy.getNonLValueExprType(SemaRef.Context);
2744  llvm::SmallVector<Expr *, 4> ParamStmts;
2745  const auto *Proto = cast<FunctionProtoType>(Method->getType());
2746  SemaRef.GatherArgumentsForCall(KernelCallerSrcLoc, Method, Proto, 0,
2747  ParamDREs, ParamStmts);
2748  // [kernel_obj or wrapper object].accessor.__init(_ValueType*,
2749  // range<int>, range<int>, id<int>)
2750  AddTo.push_back(CXXMemberCallExpr::Create(
2751  SemaRef.Context, MethodME, ParamStmts, ResultTy, VK, KernelCallerSrcLoc,
2752  FPOptionsOverride()));
2753  }
2754 
2755  // Creates an empty InitListExpr of the correct number of child-inits
2756  // of this to append into.
2757  void addCollectionInitListExpr(const CXXRecordDecl *RD) {
2758  const ASTRecordLayout &Info =
2759  SemaRef.getASTContext().getASTRecordLayout(RD);
2760  uint64_t NumInitExprs = Info.getFieldCount() + RD->getNumBases();
2761  addCollectionInitListExpr(QualType(RD->getTypeForDecl(), 0), NumInitExprs);
2762  }
2763 
2764  InitListExpr *createInitListExpr(const CXXRecordDecl *RD) {
2765  const ASTRecordLayout &Info =
2766  SemaRef.getASTContext().getASTRecordLayout(RD);
2767  uint64_t NumInitExprs = Info.getFieldCount() + RD->getNumBases();
2768  return createInitListExpr(QualType(RD->getTypeForDecl(), 0), NumInitExprs);
2769  }
2770 
2771  InitListExpr *createInitListExpr(QualType InitTy, uint64_t NumChildInits) {
2772  InitListExpr *ILE = new (SemaRef.getASTContext()) InitListExpr(
2773  SemaRef.getASTContext(), KernelCallerSrcLoc, {}, KernelCallerSrcLoc);
2774  ILE->reserveInits(SemaRef.getASTContext(), NumChildInits);
2775  ILE->setType(InitTy);
2776 
2777  return ILE;
2778  }
2779 
2780  // Create an empty InitListExpr of the type/size for the rest of the visitor
2781  // to append into.
2782  void addCollectionInitListExpr(QualType InitTy, uint64_t NumChildInits) {
2783 
2784  InitListExpr *ILE = createInitListExpr(InitTy, NumChildInits);
2785  InitListExpr *ParentILE = CollectionInitExprs.back();
2786  ParentILE->updateInit(SemaRef.getASTContext(), ParentILE->getNumInits(),
2787  ILE);
2788 
2789  CollectionInitExprs.push_back(ILE);
2790  }

2792  static VarDecl *createKernelObjClone(ASTContext &Ctx, DeclContext *DC,
2793  const CXXRecordDecl *KernelObj) {
2794  TypeSourceInfo *TSInfo =
2795  KernelObj->isLambda() ? KernelObj->getLambdaTypeInfo() : nullptr;
2796  VarDecl *VD = VarDecl::Create(
2797  Ctx, DC, KernelObj->getLocation(), KernelObj->getLocation(),
2798  KernelObj->getIdentifier(), QualType(KernelObj->getTypeForDecl(), 0),
2799  TSInfo, SC_None);
2800 
2801  return VD;
2802  }

2804  const llvm::StringLiteral getInitMethodName() const {
2805  bool IsSIMDKernel = isESIMDKernelType(KernelObj);
2806  return IsSIMDKernel ? InitESIMDMethodName : InitMethodName;
2807  }
2808 
2809  // Default inits the type, then calls the init-method in the body.
2810  bool handleSpecialType(FieldDecl *FD, QualType Ty) {
2811  addFieldInit(FD, Ty, None,
2812  InitializationKind::CreateDefault(KernelCallerSrcLoc));
2813 
2814  addFieldMemberExpr(FD, Ty);
2815 
2816  const auto *RecordDecl = Ty->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
2817  createSpecialMethodCall(RecordDecl, getInitMethodName(), BodyStmts);
2818  CXXMethodDecl *FinalizeMethod =
2819  getMethodByName(RecordDecl, FinalizeMethodName);
2820  // A finalize-method is expected for special type such as stream.
2821  if (FinalizeMethod)
2822  createSpecialMethodCall(RecordDecl, FinalizeMethodName, FinalizeStmts);
2823 
2824  removeFieldMemberExpr(FD, Ty);
2825 
2826  return true;
2827  }
2828 
2829  bool handleSpecialType(const CXXBaseSpecifier &BS, QualType Ty) {
2830  const auto *RecordDecl = Ty->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
2831  addBaseInit(BS, Ty, InitializationKind::CreateDefault(KernelCallerSrcLoc));
2832  createSpecialMethodCall(RecordDecl, getInitMethodName(), BodyStmts);
2833  return true;
2834  }

2836  // Generate __init call for kernel handler argument
2837  void handleSpecialType(QualType KernelHandlerTy) {
2838  DeclRefExpr *KernelHandlerCloneRef =
2839  DeclRefExpr::Create(SemaRef.Context, NestedNameSpecifierLoc(),
2840  KernelCallerSrcLoc, KernelHandlerClone, false,
2841  DeclarationNameInfo(), KernelHandlerTy, VK_LValue);
2842  const auto *RecordDecl =
2843  KernelHandlerClone->getType()->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
2844  MemberExprBases.push_back(KernelHandlerCloneRef);
2845  createSpecialMethodCall(RecordDecl, InitSpecConstantsBuffer, BodyStmts);
2846  MemberExprBases.pop_back();
2847  }
2848 
2849  void createKernelHandlerClone(ASTContext &Ctx, DeclContext *DC,
2850  ParmVarDecl *KernelHandlerArg) {
2851  QualType Ty = KernelHandlerArg->getType();
2852  TypeSourceInfo *TSInfo = Ctx.getTrivialTypeSourceInfo(Ty);
2853  KernelHandlerClone =
2854  VarDecl::Create(Ctx, DC, KernelCallerSrcLoc, KernelCallerSrcLoc,
2855  KernelHandlerArg->getIdentifier(), Ty, TSInfo, SC_None);
2856 
2857  // Default initialize clone
2858  InitializedEntity VarEntity =
2859  InitializedEntity::InitializeVariable(KernelHandlerClone);
2860  InitializationKind InitKind =
2861  InitializationKind::CreateDefault(KernelCallerSrcLoc);
2862  InitializationSequence InitSeq(SemaRef, VarEntity, InitKind, None);
2863  ExprResult Init = InitSeq.Perform(SemaRef, VarEntity, InitKind, None);
2864  KernelHandlerClone->setInit(
2865  SemaRef.MaybeCreateExprWithCleanups(Init.get()));
2866  KernelHandlerClone->setInitStyle(VarDecl::CallInit);
2867  }
2868 
2869 public:
2870  static constexpr const bool VisitInsideSimpleContainers = false;
2871  SyclKernelBodyCreator(Sema &S, SyclKernelDeclCreator &DC,
2872  const CXXRecordDecl *KernelObj,
2873  FunctionDecl *KernelCallerFunc)
2874  : SyclKernelFieldHandler(S), DeclCreator(DC),
2875  KernelObjClone(createKernelObjClone(S.getASTContext(),
2876  DC.getKernelDecl(), KernelObj)),
2877  VarEntity(InitializedEntity::InitializeVariable(KernelObjClone)),
2878  KernelObj(KernelObj), KernelCallerFunc(KernelCallerFunc),
2879  KernelCallerSrcLoc(KernelCallerFunc->getLocation()) {
2880  CollectionInitExprs.push_back(createInitListExpr(KernelObj));
2881  markParallelWorkItemCalls();
2882 
2883  Stmt *DS = new (S.Context) DeclStmt(DeclGroupRef(KernelObjClone),
2884  KernelCallerSrcLoc, KernelCallerSrcLoc);
2885  BodyStmts.push_back(DS);
2886  DeclRefExpr *KernelObjCloneRef = DeclRefExpr::Create(
2887  S.Context, NestedNameSpecifierLoc(), KernelCallerSrcLoc, KernelObjClone,
2888  false, DeclarationNameInfo(), QualType(KernelObj->getTypeForDecl(), 0),
2889  VK_LValue);
2890  MemberExprBases.push_back(KernelObjCloneRef);
2891  }
2892 
2893  ~SyclKernelBodyCreator() {
2894  CompoundStmt *KernelBody = createKernelBody();
2895  DeclCreator.setBody(KernelBody);
2896  }

2951  // Default inits the type, then calls the init-method in the body
2952  void handleSyclKernelHandlerType(ParmVarDecl *KernelHandlerArg) {
2953 
2954  // Create and default initialize local clone of kernel handler
2955  createKernelHandlerClone(SemaRef.getASTContext(),
2956  DeclCreator.getKernelDecl(), KernelHandlerArg);
2957 
2958  // Add declaration statement to openCL kernel body
2959  Stmt *DS =
2960  new (SemaRef.Context) DeclStmt(DeclGroupRef(KernelHandlerClone),
2961  KernelCallerSrcLoc, KernelCallerSrcLoc);
2962  BodyStmts.push_back(DS);
2963 
2964  // Generate
2965  // KernelHandlerClone.__init_specialization_constants_buffer(specialization_constants_buffer)
2966  // call if target does not have native support for specialization constants.
2967  // Here, specialization_constants_buffer is the compiler generated kernel
2968  // argument of type char*.
2969  if (!isDefaultSPIRArch(SemaRef.Context))
2970  handleSpecialType(KernelHandlerArg->getType());
2971  }

2973  bool enterStruct(const CXXRecordDecl *RD, FieldDecl *FD, QualType Ty) final {
2974  ++StructDepth;
2975  addCollectionInitListExpr(Ty->getAsCXXRecordDecl());
2976 
2977  addFieldMemberExpr(FD, Ty);
2978  return true;
2979  }
2980 
2981  bool leaveStruct(const CXXRecordDecl *, FieldDecl *FD, QualType Ty) final {
2982  --StructDepth;
2983  CollectionInitExprs.pop_back();
2984 
2985  removeFieldMemberExpr(FD, Ty);
2986  return true;
2987  }
2988 
2989  bool enterStruct(const CXXRecordDecl *RD, const CXXBaseSpecifier &BS,
2990  QualType) final {
2991  ++StructDepth;
2992 
2993  CXXCastPath BasePath;
2994  QualType DerivedTy(RD->getTypeForDecl(), 0);
2995  QualType BaseTy = BS.getType();
2996  SemaRef.CheckDerivedToBaseConversion(DerivedTy, BaseTy, KernelCallerSrcLoc,
2997  SourceRange(), &BasePath,
2998  /*IgnoreBaseAccess*/ true);
2999  auto Cast = ImplicitCastExpr::Create(
3000  SemaRef.Context, BaseTy, CK_DerivedToBase, MemberExprBases.back(),
3001  /* CXXCastPath=*/&BasePath, VK_LValue, FPOptionsOverride());
3002  MemberExprBases.push_back(Cast);
3003 
3004  addCollectionInitListExpr(BaseTy->getAsCXXRecordDecl());
3005  return true;
3006  }
3007 
3008  bool leaveStruct(const CXXRecordDecl *RD, const CXXBaseSpecifier &BS,
3009  QualType) final {
3010  --StructDepth;
3011  MemberExprBases.pop_back();
3012  CollectionInitExprs.pop_back();
3013  return true;
3014  }
3015 
3016  bool enterArray(FieldDecl *FD, QualType ArrayType,
3017  QualType ElementType) final {
3018  uint64_t ArraySize = SemaRef.getASTContext()
3019  .getAsConstantArrayType(ArrayType)
3020  ->getSize()
3021  .getZExtValue();
3022  addCollectionInitListExpr(ArrayType, ArraySize);
3023  ArrayInfos.emplace_back(getFieldEntity(FD, ArrayType), 0);
3024 
3025  // If this is the top-level array, we need to make a MemberExpr in addition
3026  // to an array subscript.
3027  addFieldMemberExpr(FD, ArrayType);
3028  return true;
3029  }
3030 
3031  bool nextElement(QualType, uint64_t Index) final {
3032  ArrayInfos.back().second = Index;
3033 
3034  // Pop off the last member expr base.
3035  if (Index != 0)
3036  MemberExprBases.pop_back();
3037 
3038  QualType SizeT = SemaRef.getASTContext().getSizeType();
3039 
3040  llvm::APInt IndexVal{
3041  static_cast<unsigned>(SemaRef.getASTContext().getTypeSize(SizeT)),
3042  Index, SizeT->isSignedIntegerType()};
3043 
3044  auto IndexLiteral = IntegerLiteral::Create(
3045  SemaRef.getASTContext(), IndexVal, SizeT, KernelCallerSrcLoc);
3046 
3047  ExprResult IndexExpr = SemaRef.CreateBuiltinArraySubscriptExpr(
3048  MemberExprBases.back(), KernelCallerSrcLoc, IndexLiteral,
3049  KernelCallerSrcLoc);
3050 
3051  assert(!IndexExpr.isInvalid());
3052  MemberExprBases.push_back(IndexExpr.get());
3053  return true;
3054  }
3055 
3056  bool leaveArray(FieldDecl *FD, QualType ArrayType,
3057  QualType ElementType) final {
3058  CollectionInitExprs.pop_back();
3059  ArrayInfos.pop_back();
3060 
3061  // Remove the IndexExpr.
3062  MemberExprBases.pop_back();
3063 
3064  // Remove the field access expr as well.
3065  removeFieldMemberExpr(FD, ArrayType);
3066  return true;
3067  }
3068 };
3069 
3070 // Kernels are only the unnamed-lambda feature if the feature is enabled, AND
3071 // the first template argument has been corrected by the library to match the
3072 // functor type.
3073 static bool IsSYCLUnnamedKernel(Sema &SemaRef, const FunctionDecl *FD) {
3074  if (!SemaRef.getLangOpts().SYCLUnnamedLambda)
3075  return false;
3076  QualType FunctorTy = GetSYCLKernelObjectType(FD);
3077  QualType TmplArgTy = calculateKernelNameType(SemaRef.Context, FD);
3078  return SemaRef.Context.hasSameType(FunctorTy, TmplArgTy);
3079 }

3081 class SyclKernelIntHeaderCreator : public SyclKernelFieldHandler {
3082  SYCLIntegrationHeader &Header;
3083  int64_t CurOffset = 0;
3084  llvm::SmallVector<size_t, 16> ArrayBaseOffsets;
3085  int StructDepth = 0;
3086 
3087  // A series of functions to calculate the change in offset based on the type.
3088  int64_t offsetOf(const FieldDecl *FD, QualType ArgTy) const {
3089  return isArrayElement(FD, ArgTy)
3090  ? 0
3091  : SemaRef.getASTContext().getFieldOffset(FD) / 8;
3092  }
3093 
3094  int64_t offsetOf(const CXXRecordDecl *RD, const CXXRecordDecl *Base) const {
3095  const ASTRecordLayout &Layout =
3096  SemaRef.getASTContext().getASTRecordLayout(RD);
3097  return Layout.getBaseClassOffset(Base).getQuantity();
3098  }
3099 
3100  void addParam(const FieldDecl *FD, QualType ArgTy,
3101  SYCLIntegrationHeader::kernel_param_kind_t Kind) {
3102  addParam(ArgTy, Kind, offsetOf(FD, ArgTy));
3103  }
3104  void addParam(QualType ArgTy, SYCLIntegrationHeader::kernel_param_kind_t Kind,
3105  uint64_t OffsetAdj) {
3106  uint64_t Size;
3107  Size = SemaRef.getASTContext().getTypeSizeInChars(ArgTy).getQuantity();
3108  Header.addParamDesc(Kind, static_cast<unsigned>(Size),
3109  static_cast<unsigned>(CurOffset + OffsetAdj));
3110  }
3111 
3112  // Returns 'true' if the thing we're visiting (Based on the FD/QualType pair)
3113  // is an element of an array. This will determine whether we do
3114  // MemberExprBases in some cases or not, AND determines how we initialize
3115  // values.
3116  bool isArrayElement(const FieldDecl *FD, QualType Ty) const {
3117  return !SemaRef.getASTContext().hasSameType(FD->getType(), Ty);
3118  }
3119 
3120 public:
3121  static constexpr const bool VisitInsideSimpleContainers = false;
3122  SyclKernelIntHeaderCreator(Sema &S, SYCLIntegrationHeader &H,
3123  const CXXRecordDecl *KernelObj, QualType NameType,
3124  FunctionDecl *KernelFunc)
3125  : SyclKernelFieldHandler(S), Header(H) {
3126  bool IsSIMDKernel = isESIMDKernelType(KernelObj);
3127  // The header needs to access the kernel object size.
3128  int64_t ObjSize = SemaRef.getASTContext()
3129  .getTypeSizeInChars(KernelObj->getTypeForDecl())
3130  .getQuantity();
3131  Header.startKernel(KernelFunc, NameType, KernelObj->getLocation(),
3132  IsSIMDKernel, IsSYCLUnnamedKernel(S, KernelFunc),
3133  ObjSize);
3134  }

3136  bool handleSyclSpecialType(const CXXRecordDecl *RD,
3137  const CXXBaseSpecifier &BC,
3138  QualType FieldTy) final {
3139  const auto *AccTy =
3140  cast<ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl>(FieldTy->getAsRecordDecl());
3141  assert(AccTy->getTemplateArgs().size() >= 2 &&
3142  "Incorrect template args for Accessor Type");
3143  int Dims = static_cast<int>(
3144  AccTy->getTemplateArgs()[1].getAsIntegral().getExtValue());
3145  int Info = getAccessTarget(AccTy) | (Dims << 11);
3146  Header.addParamDesc(SYCLIntegrationHeader::kind_accessor, Info,
3147  CurOffset +
3148  offsetOf(RD, BC.getType()->getAsCXXRecordDecl()));
3149  return true;
3150  }
3151 
3152  bool handleSyclSpecialType(FieldDecl *FD, QualType FieldTy) final {
3153  const auto *ClassTy = FieldTy->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
3154  assert(ClassTy && "Type must be a C++ record type");
3155  if (Util::isSyclType(FieldTy, "accessor", true /*Tmp*/)) {
3156  const auto *AccTy =
3157  cast<ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl>(FieldTy->getAsRecordDecl());
3158  assert(AccTy->getTemplateArgs().size() >= 2 &&
3159  "Incorrect template args for Accessor Type");
3160  int Dims = static_cast<int>(
3161  AccTy->getTemplateArgs()[1].getAsIntegral().getExtValue());
3162  int Info = getAccessTarget(AccTy) | (Dims << 11);
3163 
3164  Header.addParamDesc(SYCLIntegrationHeader::kind_accessor, Info,
3165  CurOffset + offsetOf(FD, FieldTy));
3166  } else {
3167  if (getMethodByName(ClassTy, FinalizeMethodName))
3168  addParam(FD, FieldTy, SYCLIntegrationHeader::kind_stream);
3169  else {
3170  CXXMethodDecl *InitMethod = getMethodByName(ClassTy, InitMethodName);
3171  assert(InitMethod && "type must have __init method");
3172  const ParmVarDecl *SamplerArg = InitMethod->getParamDecl(0);
3173  assert(SamplerArg && "Init method must have arguments");
3174  addParam(SamplerArg->getType(), SYCLIntegrationHeader::kind_sampler,
3175  offsetOf(FD, FieldTy));
3176  }
3177  }
3178  return true;
3179  }
3180 
3181  bool handleSyclSpecConstantType(FieldDecl *FD, QualType FieldTy) final {
3182  const TemplateArgumentList &TemplateArgs =
3183  cast<ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl>(FieldTy->getAsRecordDecl())
3184  ->getTemplateInstantiationArgs();
3185  assert(TemplateArgs.size() == 2 &&
3186  "Incorrect template args for spec constant type");
3187  // Get specialization constant ID type, which is the second template
3188  // argument.
3189  QualType SpecConstIDTy = TemplateArgs.get(1).getAsType().getCanonicalType();
3190  const std::string SpecConstName = SYCLUniqueStableNameExpr::ComputeName(
3191  SemaRef.getASTContext(), SpecConstIDTy);
3192  Header.addSpecConstant(SpecConstName, SpecConstIDTy);
3193  return true;
3194  }
3195

3197  addParam(FD, FieldTy,
3198  ((StructDepth) ? SYCLIntegrationHeader::kind_std_layout
3199  : SYCLIntegrationHeader::kind_pointer));
3200  return true;
3201  }

3210  // struct.

3232  void handleSyclKernelHandlerType(QualType Ty) {
3233  // The compiler generated kernel argument used to initialize SYCL 2020
3234  // specialization constants, `specialization_constants_buffer`, should
3235  // have corresponding entry in integration header.
3236  ASTContext &Context = SemaRef.getASTContext();
3237  // Offset is zero since kernel_handler argument is not part of
3238  // kernel object (i.e. it is not captured)

3250  --StructDepth;
3251  CurOffset -= offsetOf(FD, Ty);
3252  return true;
3253  }
3254 
3255  bool enterStruct(const CXXRecordDecl *RD, const CXXBaseSpecifier &BS,
3256  QualType) final {
3257  CurOffset += offsetOf(RD, BS.getType()->getAsCXXRecordDecl());
3258  return true;
3259  }
3260 
3261  bool leaveStruct(const CXXRecordDecl *RD, const CXXBaseSpecifier &BS,
3262  QualType) final {
3263  CurOffset -= offsetOf(RD, BS.getType()->getAsCXXRecordDecl());
3264  return true;
3265  }
3266 
3267  bool enterArray(FieldDecl *FD, QualType ArrayTy, QualType) final {
3268  ArrayBaseOffsets.push_back(CurOffset + offsetOf(FD, ArrayTy));
3269  return true;
3270  }
3271 
3272  bool nextElement(QualType ET, uint64_t Index) final {
3273  int64_t Size = SemaRef.getASTContext().getTypeSizeInChars(ET).getQuantity();
3274  CurOffset = ArrayBaseOffsets.back() + Size * Index;
3275  return true;
3276  }
3277 
3278  bool leaveArray(FieldDecl *FD, QualType ArrayTy, QualType) final {
3279  CurOffset = ArrayBaseOffsets.pop_back_val();
3280  CurOffset -= offsetOf(FD, ArrayTy);
3281  return true;
3282  }
3283 
3284  using SyclKernelFieldHandler::enterStruct;
3285  using SyclKernelFieldHandler::leaveStruct;
3286 };
