3300 class SYCLKernelNameTypeVisitor
3301  : public TypeVisitor<SYCLKernelNameTypeVisitor>,
3302  public ConstTemplateArgumentVisitor<SYCLKernelNameTypeVisitor> {
3303  Sema &S;
3304  SourceLocation KernelInvocationFuncLoc;
3305  QualType KernelNameType;
3306  using InnerTypeVisitor = TypeVisitor<SYCLKernelNameTypeVisitor>;
3307  using InnerTemplArgVisitor =
3308  ConstTemplateArgumentVisitor<SYCLKernelNameTypeVisitor>;
3309  bool IsInvalid = false;
3310  bool IsUnnamedKernel = false;
3311 
3312  void VisitTemplateArgs(ArrayRef<TemplateArgument> Args) {
3313  for (auto &A : Args)
3314  Visit(A);
3315  }
3316 
3317 public:
3318  SYCLKernelNameTypeVisitor(Sema &S, SourceLocation KernelInvocationFuncLoc,
3319  QualType KernelNameType, bool IsUnnamedKernel)
3320  : S(S), KernelInvocationFuncLoc(KernelInvocationFuncLoc),
3321  KernelNameType(KernelNameType), IsUnnamedKernel(IsUnnamedKernel) {}
3322 
3323  bool isValid() { return !IsInvalid; }
3324 
3325  void Visit(QualType T) {
3326  if (T.isNull())
3327  return;
3328 
3329  const CXXRecordDecl *RD = T->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
3330  // If KernelNameType has template args visit each template arg via
3331  // ConstTemplateArgumentVisitor
3332  if (const auto *TSD =
3333  dyn_cast_or_null<ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl>(RD)) {
3334  ArrayRef<TemplateArgument> Args = TSD->getTemplateArgs().asArray();
3335 
3336  VisitTemplateArgs(Args);
3337  } else {
3338  InnerTypeVisitor::Visit(T.getTypePtr());
3339  }
3340  }
3341 
3342  void Visit(const TemplateArgument &TA) {
3343  if (TA.isNull())
3344  return;
3345  InnerTemplArgVisitor::Visit(TA);
3346  }
3347 
3348  void VisitBuiltinType(const BuiltinType *TT) {
3349  if (TT->isNullPtrType()) {
3350  S.Diag(KernelInvocationFuncLoc, diag::err_nullptr_t_type_in_sycl_kernel)
3351  << KernelNameType;
3352 
3353  IsInvalid = true;
3354  }
3355  return;
3356  }
3357 
3358  void VisitTagType(const TagType *TT) {
3359  return DiagnoseKernelNameType(TT->getDecl());
3360  }
3361 
3362  void DiagnoseKernelNameType(const NamedDecl *DeclNamed) {
3363  /*
3364  This is a helper function which throws an error if the kernel name
3365  declaration is:
3366  * declared within namespace 'std' (at any level)
3367  e.g., namespace std { namespace literals { class Whatever; } }
3368  h.single_task<std::literals::Whatever>([]() {});
3369  * declared within a function
3370  e.g., void foo() { struct S { int i; };
3371  h.single_task<S>([]() {}); }
3372  * declared within another tag
3373  e.g., struct S { struct T { int i } t; };
3374  h.single_task<S::T>([]() {});
3375  */
3376 
3377  if (const auto *ED = dyn_cast<EnumDecl>(DeclNamed)) {
3378  if (!ED->isScoped() && !ED->isFixed()) {
3379  S.Diag(KernelInvocationFuncLoc, diag::err_sycl_kernel_incorrectly_named)
3380  << /* unscoped enum requires fixed underlying type */ 1
3381  << DeclNamed;
3382  IsInvalid = true;
3383  }
3384  }
3385 
3386  const DeclContext *DeclCtx = DeclNamed->getDeclContext();
3387  if (DeclCtx && !IsUnnamedKernel) {
3388 
3389  // Check if the kernel name declaration is declared within namespace
3390  // "std" (at any level).
3391  while (!DeclCtx->isTranslationUnit() && isa<NamespaceDecl>(DeclCtx)) {
3392  const auto *NSDecl = cast<NamespaceDecl>(DeclCtx);
3393  if (NSDecl->isStdNamespace()) {
3394  S.Diag(KernelInvocationFuncLoc,
3395  diag::err_invalid_std_type_in_sycl_kernel)
3396  << KernelNameType << DeclNamed;
3397  IsInvalid = true;
3398  return;
3399  }
3400  DeclCtx = DeclCtx->getParent();
3401  }
3402 
3403  // Check if the kernel name is a Tag declaration
3404  // local to a non-namespace scope (i.e. Inside a function or within
3405  // another Tag etc).
3406  if (!DeclCtx->isTranslationUnit() && !isa<NamespaceDecl>(DeclCtx)) {
3407  if (const auto *Tag = dyn_cast<TagDecl>(DeclNamed)) {
3408  bool UnnamedLambdaUsed = Tag->getIdentifier() == nullptr;
3409 
3410  if (UnnamedLambdaUsed) {
3411  S.Diag(KernelInvocationFuncLoc,
3412  diag::err_sycl_kernel_incorrectly_named)
3413  << /* unnamed type is invalid */ 2 << KernelNameType;
3414  IsInvalid = true;
3415  return;
3416  }
3417 
3418  // Diagnose used types without complete definition i.e.
3419  // int main() {
3420  // class KernelName1;
3421  // parallel_for<class KernelName1>(..);
3422  // }
3423  // This case can only be diagnosed during host compilation because the
3424  // integration header is required to distinguish between the invalid
3425  // code (above) and the following valid code:
3426  // int main() {
3427  // parallel_for<class KernelName2>(..);
3428  // }
3429  // The device compiler forward declares both KernelName1 and
3430  // KernelName2 in the integration header as ::KernelName1 and
3431  // ::KernelName2. The problem with the former case is the additional
3432  // declaration 'class KernelName1' in non-global scope. Lookup in this
3433  // case will resolve to ::main::KernelName1 (instead of
3434  // ::KernelName1). Since this is not visible to runtime code that
3435  // submits kernels, this is invalid.
3436  if (Tag->isCompleteDefinition() ||
3437  S.getLangOpts().SYCLEnableIntHeaderDiags) {
3438  S.Diag(KernelInvocationFuncLoc,
3439  diag::err_sycl_kernel_incorrectly_named)
3440  << /* kernel name should be forward declarable at namespace
3441  scope */
3442  0 << KernelNameType;
3443  IsInvalid = true;
3444  } else {
3445  S.Diag(KernelInvocationFuncLoc, diag::warn_sycl_implicit_decl);
3446  S.Diag(DeclNamed->getLocation(), diag::note_previous_decl)
3447  << DeclNamed->getName();
3448  }
3449  }
3450  }
3451  }
3452  }
3453 
3454  void VisitTypeTemplateArgument(const TemplateArgument &TA) {
3455  QualType T = TA.getAsType();
3456  if (const auto *ET = T->getAs<EnumType>())
3457  VisitTagType(ET);
3458  else
3459  Visit(T);
3460  }
3461 
3462  void VisitIntegralTemplateArgument(const TemplateArgument &TA) {
3463  QualType T = TA.getIntegralType();
3464  if (const EnumType *ET = T->getAs<EnumType>())
3465  VisitTagType(ET);
3466  }
3467 
3468  void VisitTemplateTemplateArgument(const TemplateArgument &TA) {
3469  TemplateDecl *TD = TA.getAsTemplate().getAsTemplateDecl();
3470  assert(TD && "template declaration must be available");
3471  TemplateParameterList *TemplateParams = TD->getTemplateParameters();
3472  for (NamedDecl *P : *TemplateParams) {
3473  if (NonTypeTemplateParmDecl *TemplateParam =
3474  dyn_cast<NonTypeTemplateParmDecl>(P))
3475  if (const EnumType *ET = TemplateParam->getType()->getAs<EnumType>())
3476  VisitTagType(ET);
3477  }
3478  }
3479 
3480  void VisitPackTemplateArgument(const TemplateArgument &TA) {
3481  VisitTemplateArgs(TA.getPackAsArray());
3482  }
3483 };
3484 
3485 void Sema::CheckSYCLKernelCall(FunctionDecl *KernelFunc, SourceRange CallLoc,
3486  ArrayRef<const Expr *> Args) {
3487  QualType KernelNameType =
3488  calculateKernelNameType(getASTContext(), KernelFunc);
3489  SYCLKernelNameTypeVisitor KernelNameTypeVisitor(
3490  *this, Args[0]->getExprLoc(), KernelNameType,
3491  IsSYCLUnnamedKernel(*this, KernelFunc));
3492  KernelNameTypeVisitor.Visit(KernelNameType.getCanonicalType());
3493 
3494  // FIXME: In place until the library works around its 'host' invocation
3495  // issues.
3496  if (!LangOpts.SYCLIsDevice)
3497  return;
3498 
3499  const CXXRecordDecl *KernelObj =
3500  GetSYCLKernelObjectType(KernelFunc)->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
3501 
3502  if (!KernelObj) {
3503  Diag(Args[0]->getExprLoc(), diag::err_sycl_kernel_not_function_object);
3504  KernelFunc->setInvalidDecl();
3505  return;
3506  }
3507 
3508  if (KernelObj->isLambda()) {
3509  for (const LambdaCapture &LC : KernelObj->captures())
3510  if (LC.capturesThis() && LC.isImplicit()) {
3511  Diag(LC.getLocation(), diag::err_implicit_this_capture);
3512  KernelFunc->setInvalidDecl();
3513  }
3514  }
3515 
3516  // check that calling kernel conforms to spec
3517  QualType KernelParamTy = KernelFunc->getParamDecl(0)->getType();
3518  if (KernelParamTy->isReferenceType()) {
3519  // passing by reference, so emit warning if not using SYCL 2020
3520  if (LangOpts.getSYCLVersion() < LangOptions::SYCL_2020)
3521  Diag(KernelFunc->getLocation(), diag::warn_sycl_pass_by_reference_future);
3522  } else {
3523  // passing by value. emit warning if using SYCL 2020 or greater
3524  if (LangOpts.getSYCLVersion() > LangOptions::SYCL_2017)
3525  Diag(KernelFunc->getLocation(), diag::warn_sycl_pass_by_value_deprecated);
3526  }
3527 
3528  // Do not visit invalid kernel object.
3529  if (KernelObj->isInvalidDecl())
3530  return;
3531 
3532  bool IsSIMDKernel = isESIMDKernelType(KernelObj);
3533 
3534  SyclKernelDecompMarker DecompMarker(*this);
3535  SyclKernelFieldChecker FieldChecker(*this, IsSIMDKernel);
3536  SyclKernelUnionChecker UnionChecker(*this);
3537 
3538  SyclKernelArgsSizeChecker ArgsSizeChecker(*this, Args[0]->getExprLoc(),
3539  IsSIMDKernel);
3540 
3541  KernelObjVisitor Visitor{*this};
3542 
3543  DiagnosingSYCLKernel = true;
3544 
3545  // Emit diagnostics for SYCL device kernels only
3546  Visitor.VisitRecordBases(KernelObj, FieldChecker, UnionChecker, DecompMarker);
3547  Visitor.VisitRecordFields(KernelObj, FieldChecker, UnionChecker,
3548  DecompMarker);
3549  // ArgSizeChecker needs to happen after DecompMarker has completed, since it
3550  // cares about the decomp attributes. DecompMarker cannot run before the
3551  // others, since it counts on the FieldChecker to make sure it is visiting
3552  // valid arrays/etc. Thus, ArgSizeChecker has its own visitation.
3553  if (FieldChecker.isValid() && UnionChecker.isValid()) {
3554  Visitor.VisitRecordBases(KernelObj, ArgsSizeChecker);
3555  Visitor.VisitRecordFields(KernelObj, ArgsSizeChecker);
3556  }
3557  DiagnosingSYCLKernel = false;
3558  // Set the kernel function as invalid, if any of the checkers fail validation.
3559  if (!FieldChecker.isValid() || !UnionChecker.isValid() ||
3560  !KernelNameTypeVisitor.isValid())
3561  KernelFunc->setInvalidDecl();
3562 }
3563 
3564 // For a wrapped parallel_for, copy attributes from original
3565 // kernel to wrapped kernel.
3566 void Sema::copySYCLKernelAttrs(const CXXRecordDecl *KernelObj) {
3567  // Get the operator() function of the wrapper.
3568  CXXMethodDecl *OpParens = getOperatorParens(KernelObj);
3569  assert(OpParens && "invalid kernel object");
3570 
3571  typedef std::pair<FunctionDecl *, FunctionDecl *> ChildParentPair;
3572  llvm::SmallPtrSet<FunctionDecl *, 16> Visited;
3573  llvm::SmallVector<ChildParentPair, 16> WorkList;
3574  WorkList.push_back({OpParens, nullptr});
3575  FunctionDecl *KernelBody = nullptr;
3576 
3577  CallGraph SYCLCG;
3578  SYCLCG.addToCallGraph(getASTContext().getTranslationUnitDecl());
3579  while (!WorkList.empty()) {
3580  FunctionDecl *FD = WorkList.back().first;
3581  FunctionDecl *ParentFD = WorkList.back().second;
3582 
3583  if ((ParentFD == OpParens) && isSYCLKernelBodyFunction(FD)) {
3584  KernelBody = FD;
3585  break;
3586  }
3587 
3588  WorkList.pop_back();
3589  if (!Visited.insert(FD).second)
3590  continue; // We've already seen this Decl
3591 
3592  CallGraphNode *N = SYCLCG.getNode(FD);
3593  if (!N)
3594  continue;
3595 
3596  for (const CallGraphNode *CI : *N) {
3597  if (auto *Callee = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(CI->getDecl())) {
3598  Callee = Callee->getMostRecentDecl();
3599  if (!Visited.count(Callee))
3600  WorkList.push_back({Callee, FD});
3601  }
3602  }
3603  }
3604 
3605  assert(KernelBody && "improper parallel_for wrap");
3606  if (KernelBody) {
3607  llvm::SmallVector<Attr *, 4> Attrs;
3608  collectSYCLAttributes(*this, KernelBody, Attrs, /*DirectlyCalled*/ true);
3609  if (!Attrs.empty())
3610  llvm::for_each(Attrs, [OpParens](Attr *A) { OpParens->addAttr(A); });
3611  }
3612 }
3613 
3614 void Sema::SetSYCLKernelNames() {
3615  std::unique_ptr<MangleContext> MangleCtx(
3616  getASTContext().createMangleContext());
3617  // We assume the list of KernelDescs is the complete list of kernels needing
3618  // to be rewritten.
3619  for (const std::pair<const FunctionDecl *, FunctionDecl *> &Pair :
3620  SyclKernelsToOpenCLKernels) {
3621  std::string CalculatedName, StableName;
3622  std::tie(CalculatedName, StableName) =
3623  constructKernelName(*this, Pair.first, *MangleCtx);
3624  StringRef KernelName(
3625  IsSYCLUnnamedKernel(*this, Pair.first) ? StableName : CalculatedName);
3626 
3627  getSyclIntegrationHeader().updateKernelNames(Pair.first, KernelName,
3628  StableName);
3629 
3630  // Set name of generated kernel.
3631  Pair.second->setDeclName(&Context.Idents.get(KernelName));
3632  // Update the AsmLabel for this generated kernel.
3633  Pair.second->addAttr(AsmLabelAttr::CreateImplicit(Context, KernelName));
3634  }
3635 }
3636 
3637 // Generates the OpenCL kernel using KernelCallerFunc (kernel caller
3638 // function) defined is SYCL headers.
3639 // Generated OpenCL kernel contains the body of the kernel caller function,
3640 // receives OpenCL like parameters and additionally does some manipulation to
3641 // initialize captured lambda/functor fields with these parameters.
3642 // SYCL runtime marks kernel caller function with sycl_kernel attribute.
3643 // To be able to generate OpenCL kernel from KernelCallerFunc we put
3644 // the following requirements to the function which SYCL runtime can mark with
3645 // sycl_kernel attribute:
3646 // - Must be template function with at least two template parameters.
3647 // First parameter must represent "unique kernel name"
3648 // Second parameter must be the function object type
3649 // - Must have only one function parameter - function object.
3650 //
3651 // Example of kernel caller function:
3652 // template <typename KernelName, typename KernelType/*, ...*/>
3653 // __attribute__((sycl_kernel)) void kernel_caller_function(KernelType
3654 // KernelFuncObj) {
3655 // KernelFuncObj();
3656 // }
3657 //
3658 //
3659 void Sema::ConstructOpenCLKernel(FunctionDecl *KernelCallerFunc,
3660  MangleContext &MC) {
3661  // The first argument to the KernelCallerFunc is the lambda object.
3662  const CXXRecordDecl *KernelObj =
3663  GetSYCLKernelObjectType(KernelCallerFunc)->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
3664  assert(KernelObj && "invalid kernel caller");
3665 
3666  // Do not visit invalid kernel object.
3667  if (KernelObj->isInvalidDecl())
3668  return;
3669 
3670  {
3671  // Do enough to calculate the StableName for the purposes of the hackery
3672  // below for __pf_kernel_wrapper. Placed in a scope so that we don't
3673  // accidentially use these values below, before the names are stabililzed.
3674  std::string CalculatedName, StableName;
3675  std::tie(CalculatedName, StableName) =
3676  constructKernelName(*this, KernelCallerFunc, MC);
3677 
3678  // Attributes of a user-written SYCL kernel must be copied to the internally
3679  // generated alternative kernel, identified by a known string in its name.
3680  if (StableName.find("__pf_kernel_wrapper") != std::string::npos)
3681  copySYCLKernelAttrs(KernelObj);
3682  }
3683 
3684  bool IsSIMDKernel = isESIMDKernelType(KernelObj);
3685 
3686  SyclKernelDeclCreator kernel_decl(*this, KernelObj->getLocation(),
3687  KernelCallerFunc->isInlined(), IsSIMDKernel,
3688  KernelCallerFunc);
3689  SyclKernelBodyCreator kernel_body(*this, kernel_decl, KernelObj,
3690  KernelCallerFunc);
3691  SyclKernelIntHeaderCreator int_header(
3692  *this, getSyclIntegrationHeader(), KernelObj,
3693  calculateKernelNameType(Context, KernelCallerFunc), KernelCallerFunc);
3694 
3695  SyclKernelIntFooterCreator int_footer(*this, getSyclIntegrationFooter());
3696  SyclOptReportCreator opt_report(*this, kernel_decl, KernelObj->getLocation());
3697 
3698  KernelObjVisitor Visitor{*this};
3699  Visitor.VisitRecordBases(KernelObj, kernel_decl, kernel_body, int_header,
3700  int_footer, opt_report);
3701  Visitor.VisitRecordFields(KernelObj, kernel_decl, kernel_body, int_header,
3702  int_footer, opt_report);
3703 
3704  if (ParmVarDecl *KernelHandlerArg =
3705  getSyclKernelHandlerArg(KernelCallerFunc)) {
3706  kernel_decl.handleSyclKernelHandlerType();
3707  kernel_body.handleSyclKernelHandlerType(KernelHandlerArg);
3708  int_header.handleSyclKernelHandlerType(KernelHandlerArg->getType());
3709  opt_report.handleSyclKernelHandlerType();
3710  }
3711 }
3712 
3713 // Figure out the sub-group for the this function. First we check the
3714 // attributes, then the global settings.
3715 static std::pair<LangOptions::SubGroupSizeType, int64_t>
3716 CalcEffectiveSubGroup(ASTContext &Ctx, const LangOptions &LO,
3717  const FunctionDecl *FD) {
3718  if (const auto *A = FD->getAttr<IntelReqdSubGroupSizeAttr>()) {
3719  int64_t Val = getIntExprValue(A->getValue(), Ctx);
3720  return {LangOptions::SubGroupSizeType::Integer, Val};
3721  }
3722 
3723  if (const auto *A = FD->getAttr<IntelNamedSubGroupSizeAttr>()) {
3724  if (A->getType() == IntelNamedSubGroupSizeAttr::Primary)
3725  return {LangOptions::SubGroupSizeType::Primary, 0};
3726  return {LangOptions::SubGroupSizeType::Auto, 0};
3727  }
3728 
3729  // Return the global settings.
3730  return {LO.getDefaultSubGroupSizeType(),
3731  static_cast<uint64_t>(LO.DefaultSubGroupSize)};
3732 }
3733 
3734 static SourceLocation GetSubGroupLoc(const FunctionDecl *FD) {
3735  if (const auto *A = FD->getAttr<IntelReqdSubGroupSizeAttr>())
3736  return A->getLocation();
3737  if (const auto *A = FD->getAttr<IntelNamedSubGroupSizeAttr>())
3738  return A->getLocation();
3739  return SourceLocation{};
3740 }
3741 
3742 static void CheckSYCL2020SubGroupSizes(Sema &S, FunctionDecl *SYCLKernel,
3743  const FunctionDecl *FD) {
3744  // If they are the same, no error.
3745  if (CalcEffectiveSubGroup(S.Context, S.getLangOpts(), SYCLKernel) ==
3746  CalcEffectiveSubGroup(S.Context, S.getLangOpts(), FD))
3747  return;
3748 
3749  // Else we need to figure out why they don't match.
3750  SourceLocation FDAttrLoc = GetSubGroupLoc(FD);
3751  SourceLocation KernelAttrLoc = GetSubGroupLoc(SYCLKernel);
3752 
3753  if (FDAttrLoc.isValid()) {
3754  // This side was caused by an attribute.
3755  S.Diag(FDAttrLoc, diag::err_sycl_mismatch_group_size)
3756  << /*kernel called*/ 0;
3757 
3758  if (KernelAttrLoc.isValid()) {
3759  S.Diag(KernelAttrLoc, diag::note_conflicting_attribute);
3760  } else {
3761  // Kernel is 'default'.
3762  S.Diag(SYCLKernel->getLocation(), diag::note_sycl_kernel_declared_here);
3763  }
3764  return;
3765  }
3766 
3767  // Else this doesn't have an attribute, which can only be caused by this being
3768  // an undefined SYCL_EXTERNAL, and the kernel has an attribute that conflicts.
3769  if (const auto *A = SYCLKernel->getAttr<IntelReqdSubGroupSizeAttr>()) {
3770  // Don't diagnose this if the kernel got its size from the 'old' attribute
3771  // spelling.
3772  if (!A->isSYCL2020Spelling())
3773  return;
3774  }
3775 
3776  assert(KernelAttrLoc.isValid() && "Kernel doesn't have attribute either?");
3777  S.Diag(FD->getLocation(), diag::err_sycl_mismatch_group_size)
3778  << /*undefined SYCL_EXTERNAL*/ 1;
3779  S.Diag(KernelAttrLoc, diag::note_conflicting_attribute);
3780 }
3781 
3782 // Check SYCL2020 Attributes. 2020 attributes don't propogate, they are only
3783 // valid if they match the attribute on the kernel. Note that this is a slight
3784 // difference from what the spec says, which says these attributes are only
3785 // valid on SYCL Kernels and SYCL_EXTERNAL, but we felt that for
3786 // self-documentation purposes that it would be nice to be able to repeat these
3787 // on subsequent functions.
3788 static void CheckSYCL2020Attributes(
3789  Sema &S, FunctionDecl *SYCLKernel, FunctionDecl *KernelBody,
3790  const llvm::SmallPtrSetImpl<FunctionDecl *> &CalledFuncs) {
3791 
3792  if (KernelBody) {
3793  // Make sure the kernel itself has all the 2020 attributes, since we don't
3794  // do propagation of these.
3795  if (auto *A = KernelBody->getAttr<IntelReqdSubGroupSizeAttr>())
3796  if (A->isSYCL2020Spelling())
3797  SYCLKernel->addAttr(A);
3798  if (auto *A = KernelBody->getAttr<IntelNamedSubGroupSizeAttr>())
3799  SYCLKernel->addAttr(A);
3800 
3801  // If the kernel has a body, we should get the attributes for the kernel
3802  // from there instead, so that we get the functor object.
3803  SYCLKernel = KernelBody;
3804  }
3805 
3806  for (auto *FD : CalledFuncs) {
3807  if (FD == SYCLKernel || FD == KernelBody)
3808  continue;
3809  for (auto *Attr : FD->attrs()) {
3810  switch (Attr->getKind()) {
3811  case attr::Kind::IntelReqdSubGroupSize:
3812  // Pre SYCL2020 spellings handled during collection.
3813  if (!cast<IntelReqdSubGroupSizeAttr>(Attr)->isSYCL2020Spelling())
3814  break;
3815  LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
3816  case attr::Kind::IntelNamedSubGroupSize:
3817  CheckSYCL2020SubGroupSizes(S, SYCLKernel, FD);
3818  break;
3819  case attr::Kind::SYCLDevice:
3820  // If a SYCL_EXTERNAL function is not defined in this TU, its necessary
3821  // that it has a compatible sub-group-size. Don't diagnose if it has a
3822  // sub-group attribute, we can count on the other checks to catch this.
3823  if (!FD->isDefined() && !FD->hasAttr<IntelReqdSubGroupSizeAttr>() &&
3824  !FD->hasAttr<IntelNamedSubGroupSizeAttr>())
3825  CheckSYCL2020SubGroupSizes(S, SYCLKernel, FD);
3826  break;
3827  default:
3828  break;
3829  }
3830  }
3831  }
3832 }
3833 
3834 static void PropagateAndDiagnoseDeviceAttr(
3835  Sema &S, const SingleDeviceFunctionTracker &Tracker, Attr *A,
3836  FunctionDecl *SYCLKernel, FunctionDecl *KernelBody) {
3837  switch (A->getKind()) {
3838  case attr::Kind::IntelReqdSubGroupSize: {
3839  auto *Attr = cast<IntelReqdSubGroupSizeAttr>(A);
3840 
3841  if (Attr->isSYCL2020Spelling())
3842  break;
3843  const auto *KBSimdAttr =
3844  KernelBody ? KernelBody->getAttr<SYCLSimdAttr>() : nullptr;
3845  if (auto *Existing = SYCLKernel->getAttr<IntelReqdSubGroupSizeAttr>()) {
3846  if (getIntExprValue(Existing->getValue(), S.getASTContext()) !=
3847  getIntExprValue(Attr->getValue(), S.getASTContext())) {
3848  S.Diag(SYCLKernel->getLocation(),
3849  diag::err_conflicting_sycl_kernel_attributes);
3850  S.Diag(Existing->getLocation(), diag::note_conflicting_attribute);
3851  S.Diag(Attr->getLocation(), diag::note_conflicting_attribute);
3852  SYCLKernel->setInvalidDecl();
3853  }
3854  } else if (KBSimdAttr &&
3855  (getIntExprValue(Attr->getValue(), S.getASTContext()) != 1)) {
3856  reportConflictingAttrs(S, KernelBody, KBSimdAttr, Attr);
3857  } else {
3858  SYCLKernel->addAttr(A);
3859  }
3860  break;
3861  }
3862  case attr::Kind::ReqdWorkGroupSize: {
3863  auto *RWGSA = cast<ReqdWorkGroupSizeAttr>(A);
3864  if (auto *Existing = SYCLKernel->getAttr<ReqdWorkGroupSizeAttr>()) {
3865  if (*Existing->getXDimVal() != *RWGSA->getXDimVal() ||
3866  *Existing->getYDimVal() != *RWGSA->getYDimVal() ||
3867  *Existing->getZDimVal() != *RWGSA->getZDimVal()) {
3868  S.Diag(SYCLKernel->getLocation(),
3869  diag::err_conflicting_sycl_kernel_attributes);
3870  S.Diag(Existing->getLocation(), diag::note_conflicting_attribute);
3871  S.Diag(RWGSA->getLocation(), diag::note_conflicting_attribute);
3872  SYCLKernel->setInvalidDecl();
3873  }
3874  } else if (auto *Existing =
3875  SYCLKernel->getAttr<SYCLIntelMaxWorkGroupSizeAttr>()) {
3876  if (*Existing->getXDimVal() < *RWGSA->getXDimVal() ||
3877  *Existing->getYDimVal() < *RWGSA->getYDimVal() ||
3878  *Existing->getZDimVal() < *RWGSA->getZDimVal()) {
3879  S.Diag(SYCLKernel->getLocation(),
3880  diag::err_conflicting_sycl_kernel_attributes);
3881  S.Diag(Existing->getLocation(), diag::note_conflicting_attribute);
3882  S.Diag(RWGSA->getLocation(), diag::note_conflicting_attribute);
3883  SYCLKernel->setInvalidDecl();
3884  } else {
3885  SYCLKernel->addAttr(A);
3886  }
3887  } else {
3888  SYCLKernel->addAttr(A);
3889  }
3890  break;
3891  }
3892  case attr::Kind::WorkGroupSizeHint: {
3893  auto *WGSH = cast<WorkGroupSizeHintAttr>(A);
3894  if (auto *Existing = SYCLKernel->getAttr<WorkGroupSizeHintAttr>()) {
3895  if (Existing->getXDimVal() != WGSH->getXDimVal() ||
3896  Existing->getYDimVal() != WGSH->getYDimVal() ||
3897  Existing->getZDimVal() != WGSH->getZDimVal()) {
3898  S.Diag(SYCLKernel->getLocation(),
3899  diag::err_conflicting_sycl_kernel_attributes);
3900  S.Diag(Existing->getLocation(), diag::note_conflicting_attribute);
3901  S.Diag(WGSH->getLocation(), diag::note_conflicting_attribute);
3902  SYCLKernel->setInvalidDecl();
3903  }
3904  }
3905  SYCLKernel->addAttr(A);
3906  break;
3907  }
3908  case attr::Kind::SYCLIntelMaxWorkGroupSize: {
3909  auto *SIMWGSA = cast<SYCLIntelMaxWorkGroupSizeAttr>(A);
3910  if (auto *Existing = SYCLKernel->getAttr<ReqdWorkGroupSizeAttr>()) {
3911  if (*Existing->getXDimVal() > *SIMWGSA->getXDimVal() ||
3912  *Existing->getYDimVal() > *SIMWGSA->getYDimVal() ||
3913  *Existing->getZDimVal() > *SIMWGSA->getZDimVal()) {
3914  S.Diag(SYCLKernel->getLocation(),
3915  diag::err_conflicting_sycl_kernel_attributes);
3916  S.Diag(Existing->getLocation(), diag::note_conflicting_attribute);
3917  S.Diag(SIMWGSA->getLocation(), diag::note_conflicting_attribute);
3918  SYCLKernel->setInvalidDecl();
3919  } else {
3920  SYCLKernel->addAttr(A);
3921  }
3922  } else {
3923  SYCLKernel->addAttr(A);
3924  }
3925  break;
3926  }
3927  case attr::Kind::SYCLSimd:
3928  if (KernelBody && !KernelBody->getAttr<SYCLSimdAttr>()) {
3929  // Usual kernel can't call ESIMD functions.
3930  S.Diag(KernelBody->getLocation(),
3931  diag::err_sycl_function_attribute_mismatch)
3932  << A;
3933  S.Diag(A->getLocation(), diag::note_attribute);
3934  KernelBody->setInvalidDecl();
3935  break;
3936  }
3937  LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
3938  case attr::Kind::SYCLIntelKernelArgsRestrict:
3939  case attr::Kind::SYCLIntelNumSimdWorkItems:
3940  case attr::Kind::SYCLIntelSchedulerTargetFmaxMhz:
3941  case attr::Kind::SYCLIntelMaxGlobalWorkDim:
3942  case attr::Kind::SYCLIntelNoGlobalWorkOffset:
3943  case attr::Kind::SYCLIntelLoopFuse:
3944  case attr::Kind::SYCLIntelFPGAMaxConcurrency:
3945  case attr::Kind::SYCLIntelFPGADisableLoopPipelining:
3946  case attr::Kind::SYCLIntelFPGAInitiationInterval:
3947  case attr::Kind::SYCLIntelUseStallEnableClusters:
3948  case attr::Kind::SYCLDeviceHas:
3949  case attr::Kind::SYCLAddIRAttributesFunction:
3950  SYCLKernel->addAttr(A);
3951  break;
3952  case attr::Kind::IntelNamedSubGroupSize:
3953  // Nothing to do here, handled in the SYCL2020 spelling.
3954  break;
3955  // TODO: vec_len_hint should be handled here
3956  default:
3957  // Seeing this means that CollectPossibleKernelAttributes was
3958  // updated while this switch wasn't...or something went wrong
3959  llvm_unreachable("Unexpected attribute was collected by "
3960  "CollectPossibleKernelAttributes");
3961  }
3962 }
3963 
3964 void Sema::MarkDevices() {
3965  // This Tracker object ensures that the SyclDeviceDecls collection includes
3966  // the SYCL_EXTERNAL functions, and manages the diagnostics for all of the
3967  // functions in the kernel.
3968  DeviceFunctionTracker Tracker(*this);
3969 
3970  for (Decl *D : syclDeviceDecls()) {
3971  auto *SYCLKernel = cast<FunctionDecl>(D);
3972 
3973  // This type does the actual analysis on a per-kernel basis. It does this to
3974  // make sure that we're only ever dealing with the context of a single
3975  // kernel at a time.
3976  SingleDeviceFunctionTracker T{Tracker, SYCLKernel};
3977 
3978  CheckSYCL2020Attributes(*this, T.GetSYCLKernel(), T.GetKernelBody(),
3979  T.GetDeviceFunctions());
3980  for (auto *A : T.GetCollectedAttributes())
3981  PropagateAndDiagnoseDeviceAttr(*this, T, A, T.GetSYCLKernel(),
3982  T.GetKernelBody());
3983  }
3984 }
3985 
3986 // -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
3987 // SYCL device specific diagnostics implementation
3988 // -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
3989 
3990 Sema::SemaDiagnosticBuilder
3991 Sema::SYCLDiagIfDeviceCode(SourceLocation Loc, unsigned DiagID,
3992  DeviceDiagnosticReason Reason) {
3993  assert(getLangOpts().SYCLIsDevice &&
3994  "Should only be called during SYCL compilation");
3995  FunctionDecl *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(getCurLexicalContext());
3996  SemaDiagnosticBuilder::Kind DiagKind = [this, FD, Reason] {
3997  if (DiagnosingSYCLKernel)
3998  return SemaDiagnosticBuilder::K_ImmediateWithCallStack;
3999  if (!FD)
4000  return SemaDiagnosticBuilder::K_Nop;
4001  if (getEmissionStatus(FD) == Sema::FunctionEmissionStatus::Emitted) {
4002  // Skip the diagnostic if we know it won't be emitted.
4003  if ((getEmissionReason(FD) & Reason) ==
4004  Sema::DeviceDiagnosticReason::None)
4005  return SemaDiagnosticBuilder::K_Nop;
4006 
4007  return SemaDiagnosticBuilder::K_ImmediateWithCallStack;
4008  }
4009  return SemaDiagnosticBuilder::K_Deferred;
4010  }();
4011  return SemaDiagnosticBuilder(DiagKind, Loc, DiagID, FD, *this, Reason);
4012 }
4013 
4014 bool Sema::checkSYCLDeviceFunction(SourceLocation Loc, FunctionDecl *Callee) {
4015  assert(getLangOpts().SYCLIsDevice &&
4016  "Should only be called during SYCL compilation");
4017  assert(Callee && "Callee may not be null.");
4018 
4019  // Errors in an unevaluated context don't need to be generated,
4020  // so we can safely skip them.
4021  if (isUnevaluatedContext() || isConstantEvaluated())
4022  return true;
4023 
4024  FunctionDecl *Caller = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(getCurLexicalContext());
4025 
4026  if (!Caller)
4027  return true;
4028 
4029  SemaDiagnosticBuilder::Kind DiagKind = SemaDiagnosticBuilder::K_Nop;
4030 
4031  // TODO Set DiagKind to K_Immediate/K_Deferred to emit diagnostics for Callee
4032  SemaDiagnosticBuilder(DiagKind, Loc, diag::err_sycl_restrict, Caller, *this,
4033  DeviceDiagnosticReason::Sycl)
4034  << Sema::KernelCallUndefinedFunction;
4035  SemaDiagnosticBuilder(DiagKind, Callee->getLocation(),
4036  diag::note_previous_decl, Caller, *this,
4037  DeviceDiagnosticReason::Sycl)
4038  << Callee;
4039 
4040  return DiagKind != SemaDiagnosticBuilder::K_Immediate &&
4041  DiagKind != SemaDiagnosticBuilder::K_ImmediateWithCallStack;
4042 }
4043 
4044 void Sema::deepTypeCheckForSYCLDevice(SourceLocation UsedAt,
4045  llvm::DenseSet<QualType> Visited,
4046  ValueDecl *DeclToCheck) {
4047  assert(getLangOpts().SYCLIsDevice &&
4048  "Should only be called during SYCL compilation");
4049  // Emit notes only for the first discovered declaration of unsupported type
4050  // to avoid mess of notes. This flag is to track that error already happened.
4051  bool NeedToEmitNotes = true;
4052 
4053  auto Check = [&](QualType TypeToCheck, const ValueDecl *D) {
4054  bool ErrorFound = false;
4055  if (isZeroSizedArray(*this, TypeToCheck)) {
4056  SYCLDiagIfDeviceCode(UsedAt, diag::err_typecheck_zero_array_size) << 1;
4057  ErrorFound = true;
4058  }
4059  // Checks for other types can also be done here.
4060  if (ErrorFound) {
4061  if (NeedToEmitNotes) {
4062  if (auto *FD = dyn_cast<FieldDecl>(D))
4063  SYCLDiagIfDeviceCode(FD->getLocation(),
4064  diag::note_illegal_field_declared_here)
4065  << FD->getType()->isPointerType() << FD->getType();
4066  else
4067  SYCLDiagIfDeviceCode(D->getLocation(), diag::note_declared_at);
4068  }
4069  }
4070 
4071  return ErrorFound;
4072  };
4073 
4074  // In case we have a Record used do the DFS for a bad field.
4075  SmallVector<const ValueDecl *, 4> StackForRecursion;
4076  StackForRecursion.push_back(DeclToCheck);
4077 
4078  // While doing DFS save how we get there to emit a nice set of notes.
4079  SmallVector<const FieldDecl *, 4> History;
4080  History.push_back(nullptr);
4081 
4082  do {
4083  const ValueDecl *Next = StackForRecursion.pop_back_val();
4084  if (!Next) {
4085  assert(!History.empty());
4086  // Found a marker, we have gone up a level.
4087  History.pop_back();
4088  continue;
4089  }
4090  QualType NextTy = Next->getType();
4091 
4092  if (!Visited.insert(NextTy).second)
4093  continue;
4094 
4095  auto EmitHistory = [&]() {
4096  // The first element is always nullptr.
4097  for (uint64_t Index = 1; Index < History.size(); ++Index) {
4098  SYCLDiagIfDeviceCode(History[Index]->getLocation(),
4099  diag::note_within_field_of_type)
4100  << History[Index]->getType();
4101  }
4102  };
4103 
4104  if (Check(NextTy, Next)) {
4105  if (NeedToEmitNotes)
4106  EmitHistory();
4107  NeedToEmitNotes = false;
4108  }
4109 
4110  // In case pointer/array/reference type is met get pointee type, then
4111  // proceed with that type.
4112  while (NextTy->isAnyPointerType() || NextTy->isArrayType() ||
4113  NextTy->isReferenceType()) {
4114  if (NextTy->isArrayType())
4115  NextTy = QualType{NextTy->getArrayElementTypeNoTypeQual(), 0};
4116  else
4117  NextTy = NextTy->getPointeeType();
4118  if (Check(NextTy, Next)) {
4119  if (NeedToEmitNotes)
4120  EmitHistory();
4121  NeedToEmitNotes = false;
4122  }
4123  }
4124 
4125  if (const auto *RecDecl = NextTy->getAsRecordDecl()) {
4126  if (auto *NextFD = dyn_cast<FieldDecl>(Next))
4127  History.push_back(NextFD);
4128  // When nullptr is discovered, this means we've gone back up a level, so
4129  // the history should be cleaned.
4130  StackForRecursion.push_back(nullptr);
4131  llvm::copy(RecDecl->fields(), std::back_inserter(StackForRecursion));
4132  }
4133  } while (!StackForRecursion.empty());
4134 }
4135 
4136 void Sema::finalizeSYCLDelayedAnalysis(const FunctionDecl *Caller,
4137  const FunctionDecl *Callee,
4138  SourceLocation Loc,
4139  DeviceDiagnosticReason Reason) {
4140  Callee = Callee->getMostRecentDecl();
4141 
4142  // If the reason for the emission of this diagnostic is not SYCL-specific,
4143  // and it is not known to be reachable from a routine on device, do not
4144  // issue a diagnostic.
4145  if ((Reason & DeviceDiagnosticReason::Sycl) == DeviceDiagnosticReason::None &&
4146  !isFDReachableFromSyclDevice(Callee, Caller))
4147  return;
4148 
4149  // If Callee has a SYCL attribute, no diagnostic needed.
4150  if (Callee->hasAttr<SYCLDeviceAttr>() || Callee->hasAttr<SYCLKernelAttr>())
4151  return;
4152 
4153  // Diagnose if this is an undefined function and it is not a builtin.
4154  // Currently, there is an exception of "__failed_assertion" in libstdc++-11,
4155  // this undefined function is used to trigger a compiling error.
4156  if (!Callee->isDefined() && !Callee->getBuiltinID() &&
4157  !Callee->isReplaceableGlobalAllocationFunction() &&
4158  !isSYCLUndefinedAllowed(Callee, getSourceManager())) {
4159  Diag(Loc, diag::err_sycl_restrict) << Sema::KernelCallUndefinedFunction;
4160  Diag(Callee->getLocation(), diag::note_previous_decl) << Callee;
4161  Diag(Caller->getLocation(), diag::note_called_by) << Caller;
4162  }
4163 }
4164 
4165 bool Sema::checkAllowedSYCLInitializer(VarDecl *VD) {
4166  assert(getLangOpts().SYCLIsDevice &&
4167  "Should only be called during SYCL compilation");
4168 
4169  if (VD->isInvalidDecl() || !VD->hasInit() || !VD->hasGlobalStorage())
4170  return true;
4171 
4172  const Expr *Init = VD->getInit();
4173  bool ValueDependent = Init && Init->isValueDependent();
4174  bool isConstantInit =
4175  Init && !ValueDependent && Init->isConstantInitializer(Context, false);
4176  if (!VD->isConstexpr() && Init && !ValueDependent && !isConstantInit)
4177  return false;
4178 
4179  return true;
4180 }

4186 /// Returns a string ID of given parameter kind - used in header
4187 /// emission.
4188 static const char *paramKind2Str(KernelParamKind K) {
4189 #define CASE(x) \
4190  case SYCLIntegrationHeader::kind_##x: \
4191  return "kind_" #x
4192  switch (K) {
4193  CASE(accessor);
4194  CASE(std_layout);
4195  CASE(sampler);
4196  CASE(stream);
4197  CASE(specialization_constants_buffer);
4198  CASE(pointer);
4199  }
4200  return "<ERROR>";
4201 
4202 #undef CASE
4203 }
4204 
4205 // Emits forward declarations of classes and template classes on which
4206 // declaration of given type depends.
4207 // For example, consider SimpleVadd
4208 // class specialization in parallel_for below:
4209 //
4210 // template <typename T1, unsigned int N, typename ... T2>
4211 // class SimpleVadd;
4212 // ...
4213 // template <unsigned int N, typename T1, typename ... T2>
4214 // void simple_vadd(const std::array<T1, N>& VA, const std::array<T1, N>&
4215 // VB,
4216 // std::array<T1, N>& VC, int param, T2 ... varargs) {
4217 // ...
4218 // deviceQueue.submit([&](cl::sycl::handler& cgh) {
4219 // ...
4220 // cgh.parallel_for<class SimpleVadd<T1, N, T2...>>(...)
4221 // ...
4222 // }
4223 // ...
4224 // }
4225 // ...
4226 // class MyClass {...};
4227 // template <typename T> class MyInnerTmplClass { ... }
4228 // template <typename T> class MyTmplClass { ... }
4229 // ...
4230 // MyClass *c = new MyClass();
4231 // MyInnerTmplClass<MyClass**> c1(&c);
4232 // simple_vadd(A, B, C, 5, 'a', 1.f,
4233 // new MyTmplClass<MyInnerTmplClass<MyClass**>>(c1));
4234 //
4235 // it will generate the following forward declarations:
4236 // class MyClass;
4237 // template <typename T> class MyInnerTmplClass;
4238 // template <typename T> class MyTmplClass;
4239 // template <typename T1, unsigned int N, typename ...T2> class SimpleVadd;
4240 //
4241 class SYCLFwdDeclEmitter
4242  : public TypeVisitor<SYCLFwdDeclEmitter>,
4243  public ConstTemplateArgumentVisitor<SYCLFwdDeclEmitter> {
4244  using InnerTypeVisitor = TypeVisitor<SYCLFwdDeclEmitter>;
4245  using InnerTemplArgVisitor = ConstTemplateArgumentVisitor<SYCLFwdDeclEmitter>;
4246  raw_ostream &OS;
4247  llvm::SmallPtrSet<const NamedDecl *, 4> Printed;
4248  PrintingPolicy Policy;
4249 
4250  void printForwardDecl(NamedDecl *D) {
4251  // wrap the declaration into namespaces if needed
4252  unsigned NamespaceCnt = 0;
4253  std::string NSStr = "";
4254  const DeclContext *DC = D->getDeclContext();
4255 
4256  while (DC) {
4257  if (const auto *NS = dyn_cast<NamespaceDecl>(DC)) {
4258  ++NamespaceCnt;
4259  StringRef NSInlinePrefix = NS->isInline() ? "inline " : "";
4260  NSStr.insert(
4261  0,
4262  Twine(NSInlinePrefix + "namespace " + NS->getName() + " { ").str());
4263  DC = NS->getDeclContext();
4264  } else {
4265  // We should be able to handle a subset of the decl-context types to
4266  // make our namespaces for forward declarations as specific as possible,
4267  // so just skip them here. We can't use their names, since they would
4268  // not be forward declarable, but we can try to make them as specific as
4269  // possible.
4270  // This permits things such as:
4271  // namespace N1 { void foo() { kernel<class K>(...); }}
4272  // and
4273  // namespace N2 { void foo() { kernel<class K>(...); }}
4274  // to co-exist, despite technically being against the SYCL rules.
4275  // See SYCLKernelNameTypePrinter for the corresponding part that prints
4276  // the kernel information for this type. These two must match.
4277  if (isa<FunctionDecl, RecordDecl, LinkageSpecDecl>(DC)) {
4278  DC = cast<Decl>(DC)->getDeclContext();
4279  } else {
4280  break;
4281  }
4282  }
4283  }
4284  OS << NSStr;
4285  if (NamespaceCnt > 0)
4286  OS << "\n";
4287 
4288  D->print(OS, Policy);
4289 
4290  if (const auto *ED = dyn_cast<EnumDecl>(D)) {
4291  QualType T = ED->getIntegerType();
4292  // Backup since getIntegerType() returns null for enum forward
4293  // declaration with no fixed underlying type
4294  if (T.isNull())
4295  T = ED->getPromotionType();
4296  OS << " : " << T.getAsString();
4297  }
4298 
4299  OS << ";\n";
4300 
4301  // print closing braces for namespaces if needed
4302  for (unsigned I = 0; I < NamespaceCnt; ++I)
4303  OS << "}";
4304  if (NamespaceCnt > 0)
4305  OS << "\n";
4306  }
4307 
4308  // Checks if we've already printed forward declaration and prints it if not.
4309  void checkAndEmitForwardDecl(NamedDecl *D) {
4310  if (Printed.insert(D).second)
4311  printForwardDecl(D);
4312  }
4313 
4314  void VisitTemplateArgs(ArrayRef<TemplateArgument> Args) {
4315  for (size_t I = 0, E = Args.size(); I < E; ++I)
4316  Visit(Args[I]);
4317  }
4318 
4319 public:
4320  SYCLFwdDeclEmitter(raw_ostream &OS, LangOptions LO) : OS(OS), Policy(LO) {
4321  Policy.adjustForCPlusPlusFwdDecl();
4322  Policy.SuppressTypedefs = true;
4323  Policy.SuppressUnwrittenScope = true;
4324  Policy.PrintCanonicalTypes = true;
4325  Policy.SkipCanonicalizationOfTemplateTypeParms = true;
4326  }
4327 
4328  void Visit(QualType T) {
4329  if (T.isNull())
4330  return;
4331  InnerTypeVisitor::Visit(T.getTypePtr());
4332  }
4333 
4334  void VisitReferenceType(const ReferenceType *RT) {
4335  // Our forward declarations don't care about references, so we should just
4336  // ignore the reference and continue on.
4337  Visit(RT->getPointeeType());
4338  }
4339 
4340  void Visit(const TemplateArgument &TA) {
4341  if (TA.isNull())
4342  return;
4343  InnerTemplArgVisitor::Visit(TA);
4344  }
4345 
4346  void VisitPointerType(const PointerType *T) {
4347  // Peel off the pointer types.
4348  QualType PT = T->getPointeeType();
4349  while (PT->isPointerType())
4350  PT = PT->getPointeeType();
4351  Visit(PT);
4352  }
4353 
4354  void VisitTagType(const TagType *T) {
4355  TagDecl *TD = T->getDecl();
4356  if (const auto *TSD = dyn_cast<ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl>(TD)) {
4357  // - first, recurse into template parameters and emit needed forward
4358  // declarations
4359  ArrayRef<TemplateArgument> Args = TSD->getTemplateArgs().asArray();
4360  VisitTemplateArgs(Args);
4361  // - second, emit forward declaration for the template class being
4362  // specialized
4363  ClassTemplateDecl *CTD = TSD->getSpecializedTemplate();
4364  assert(CTD && "template declaration must be available");
4365 
4366  checkAndEmitForwardDecl(CTD);
4367  return;
4368  }
4369  checkAndEmitForwardDecl(TD);
4370  }
4371 
4372  void VisitTypeTemplateArgument(const TemplateArgument &TA) {
4373  QualType T = TA.getAsType();
4374  Visit(T);
4375  }
4376 
4377  void VisitIntegralTemplateArgument(const TemplateArgument &TA) {
4378  QualType T = TA.getIntegralType();
4379  if (const EnumType *ET = T->getAs<EnumType>())
4380  VisitTagType(ET);
4381  }
4382 
4383  void VisitTemplateTemplateArgument(const TemplateArgument &TA) {
4384  // recursion is not required, since the maximum possible nesting level
4385  // equals two for template argument
4386  //
4387  // for example:
4388  // template <typename T> class Bar;
4389  // template <template <typename> class> class Baz;
4390  // template <template <template <typename> class> class T>
4391  // class Foo;
4392  //
4393  // The Baz is a template class. The Baz<Bar> is a class. The class Foo
4394  // should be specialized with template class, not a class. The correct
4395  // specialization of template class Foo is Foo<Baz>. The incorrect
4396  // specialization of template class Foo is Foo<Baz<Bar>>. In this case
4397  // template class Foo specialized by class Baz<Bar>, not a template
4398  // class template <template <typename> class> class T as it should.
4399  TemplateDecl *TD = TA.getAsTemplate().getAsTemplateDecl();
4400  assert(TD && "template declaration must be available");
4401  TemplateParameterList *TemplateParams = TD->getTemplateParameters();
4402  for (NamedDecl *P : *TemplateParams) {
4403  // If template template parameter type has an enum value template
4404  // parameter, forward declaration of enum type is required. Only enum
4405  // values (not types) need to be handled. For example, consider the
4406  // following kernel name type:
4407  //
4408  // template <typename EnumTypeOut, template <EnumValueIn EnumValue,
4409  // typename TypeIn> class T> class Foo;
4410  //
4411  // The correct specialization for Foo (with enum type) is:
4412  // Foo<EnumTypeOut, Baz>, where Baz is a template class.
4413  //
4414  // Therefore the forward class declarations generated in the
4415  // integration header are:
4416  // template <EnumValueIn EnumValue, typename TypeIn> class Baz;
4417  // template <typename EnumTypeOut, template <EnumValueIn EnumValue,
4418  // typename EnumTypeIn> class T> class Foo;
4419  //
4420  // This requires the following enum forward declarations:
4421  // enum class EnumTypeOut : int; (Used to template Foo)
4422  // enum class EnumValueIn : int; (Used to template Baz)
4423  if (NonTypeTemplateParmDecl *TemplateParam =
4424  dyn_cast<NonTypeTemplateParmDecl>(P))
4425  if (const EnumType *ET = TemplateParam->getType()->getAs<EnumType>())
4426  VisitTagType(ET);
4427  }
4428  checkAndEmitForwardDecl(TD);
4429  }
4430 
4431  void VisitPackTemplateArgument(const TemplateArgument &TA) {
4432  VisitTemplateArgs(TA.getPackAsArray());
4433  }
4434 };
4435 
4436 class SYCLKernelNameTypePrinter
4437  : public TypeVisitor<SYCLKernelNameTypePrinter>,
4438  public ConstTemplateArgumentVisitor<SYCLKernelNameTypePrinter> {
4439  using InnerTypeVisitor = TypeVisitor<SYCLKernelNameTypePrinter>;
4440  using InnerTemplArgVisitor =
4441  ConstTemplateArgumentVisitor<SYCLKernelNameTypePrinter>;
4442  raw_ostream &OS;
4443  PrintingPolicy &Policy;
4444 
4445  void printTemplateArgs(ArrayRef<TemplateArgument> Args) {
4446  for (size_t I = 0, E = Args.size(); I < E; ++I) {
4447  const TemplateArgument &Arg = Args[I];
4448  // If argument is an empty pack argument, skip printing comma and
4449  // argument.
4450  if (Arg.getKind() == TemplateArgument::ArgKind::Pack && !Arg.pack_size())
4451  continue;
4452 
4453  if (I)
4454  OS << ", ";
4455 
4456  Visit(Arg);
4457  }
4458  }
4459 
4460  void VisitQualifiers(Qualifiers Quals) {
4461  Quals.print(OS, Policy, /*appendSpaceIfNotEmpty*/ true);
4462  }
4463 
4464  // Use recursion to print the namespace-qualified name for the purposes of the
4465  // canonical sycl example of a type being created in the kernel call.
4466  void PrintNamespaceScopes(const DeclContext *DC) {
4467  if (isa<NamespaceDecl, FunctionDecl, RecordDecl, LinkageSpecDecl>(DC)) {
4468  PrintNamespaceScopes(DC->getParent());
4469 
4470  const auto *NS = dyn_cast<NamespaceDecl>(DC);
4471  if (NS && !NS->isAnonymousNamespace())
4472  OS << NS->getName() << "::";
4473  }
4474  }
4475 
4476 public:
4477  SYCLKernelNameTypePrinter(raw_ostream &OS, PrintingPolicy &Policy)
4478  : OS(OS), Policy(Policy) {}
4479 
4480  void Visit(QualType T) {
4481  if (T.isNull())
4482  return;
4483 
4484  QualType CT = T.getCanonicalType();
4485  VisitQualifiers(CT.getQualifiers());
4486 
4487  InnerTypeVisitor::Visit(CT.getTypePtr());
4488  }
4489 
4490  void VisitType(const Type *T) {
4491  OS << QualType::getAsString(T, Qualifiers(), Policy);
4492  }
4493 
4494  void Visit(const TemplateArgument &TA) {
4495  if (TA.isNull())
4496  return;
4497  InnerTemplArgVisitor::Visit(TA);
4498  }
4499 
4500  void VisitTagType(const TagType *T) {
4501  TagDecl *RD = T->getDecl();
4502  if (const auto *TSD = dyn_cast<ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl>(RD)) {
4503 
4504  // Print template class name
4505  TSD->printQualifiedName(OS, Policy, /*WithGlobalNsPrefix*/ true);
4506 
4507  ArrayRef<TemplateArgument> Args = TSD->getTemplateArgs().asArray();
4508  OS << "<";
4509  printTemplateArgs(Args);
4510  OS << ">";
4511 
4512  return;
4513  }
4514 
4515  // Handle the canonical sycl example where the type is created for the first
4516  // time in the kernel naming. We want to qualify this as fully as we can,
4517  // but not in a way that won't be forward declarable. See
4518  // SYCLFwdDeclEmitter::printForwardDecl for the corresponding list for
4519  // printing the forward declaration, these two must match.
4520  DeclContext *DC = RD->getDeclContext();
4521  if (isa<FunctionDecl, RecordDecl, LinkageSpecDecl>(DC)) {
4522  PrintNamespaceScopes(DC);
4523  RD->printName(OS);
4524  return;
4525  }
4526 
4527  const NamespaceDecl *NS = dyn_cast<NamespaceDecl>(RD->getDeclContext());
4528  RD->printQualifiedName(OS, Policy, !(NS && NS->isAnonymousNamespace()));
4529  }
4530 
4531  void VisitTemplateArgument(const TemplateArgument &TA) {
4532  TA.print(Policy, OS, false /* IncludeType */);
4533  }
4534 
4535  void VisitTypeTemplateArgument(const TemplateArgument &TA) {
4536  Policy.SuppressTagKeyword = true;
4537  QualType T = TA.getAsType();
4538  Visit(T);
4539  Policy.SuppressTagKeyword = false;
4540  }
4541 
4542  void VisitIntegralTemplateArgument(const TemplateArgument &TA) {
4543  QualType T = TA.getIntegralType();
4544  if (const EnumType *ET = T->getAs<EnumType>()) {
4545  const llvm::APSInt &Val = TA.getAsIntegral();
4546  OS << "static_cast<";
4547  ET->getDecl()->printQualifiedName(OS, Policy,
4548  /*WithGlobalNsPrefix*/ true);
4549  OS << ">(" << Val << ")";
4550  } else {
4551  TA.print(Policy, OS, false /* IncludeType */);
4552  }
4553  }
4554 
4555  void VisitTemplateTemplateArgument(const TemplateArgument &TA) {
4556  TemplateDecl *TD = TA.getAsTemplate().getAsTemplateDecl();
4557  TD->printQualifiedName(OS, Policy);
4558  }
4559 
4560  void VisitPackTemplateArgument(const TemplateArgument &TA) {
4561  printTemplateArgs(TA.getPackAsArray());
4562  }
4563 };

4565 static void OutputStableNameChar(raw_ostream &O, char C) {
4566  // If it is reliably printable, print in the integration header as a
4567  // character. Else just print it as the integral representation.
4568  if (llvm::isPrint(C))
4569  O << '\'' << C << '\'';
4570  else
4571  O << static_cast<short>(C);
4572 }
4573 
4574 static void OutputStableNameInChars(raw_ostream &O, StringRef Name) {
4575  assert(!Name.empty() && "Expected a nonempty string!");
4576  OutputStableNameChar(O, Name[0]);
4577 
4578  for (char C : Name.substr(1)) {
4579  O << ", ";
4580  OutputStableNameChar(O, C);
4581  }
4582 }
4583 
4584 void SYCLIntegrationHeader::emit(raw_ostream &O) {
4585  O << "// This is auto-generated SYCL integration header.\n";
4586  O << "\n";
4587 
4588  O << "#include <CL/sycl/detail/defines_elementary.hpp>\n";
4589  O << "#include <CL/sycl/detail/kernel_desc.hpp>\n";
4590 
4591  O << "\n";
4592 
4593  LangOptions LO;
4594  PrintingPolicy Policy(LO);
4595  Policy.SuppressTypedefs = true;
4596  Policy.SuppressUnwrittenScope = true;
4597  SYCLFwdDeclEmitter FwdDeclEmitter(O, S.getLangOpts());
4598 
4599  // Predefines which need to be set for custom host compilation
4600  // must be defined in integration header.
4601  for (const std::pair<StringRef, StringRef> &Macro :
4602  getSYCLVersionMacros(S.getLangOpts())) {
4603  O << "#ifndef " << Macro.first << '\n';
4604  O << "#define " << Macro.first << " " << Macro.second << '\n';
4605  O << "#endif //" << Macro.first << "\n\n";
4606  }
4607 
4608  if (S.getLangOpts().SYCLDisableRangeRounding) {
4609  O << "#ifndef __SYCL_DISABLE_PARALLEL_FOR_RANGE_ROUNDING__ \n";
4610  O << "#define __SYCL_DISABLE_PARALLEL_FOR_RANGE_ROUNDING__ 1\n";
4611  O << "#endif //__SYCL_DISABLE_PARALLEL_FOR_RANGE_ROUNDING__\n\n";
4612  }
4613 
4614  if (SpecConsts.size() > 0) {
4615  O << "// Forward declarations of templated spec constant types:\n";
4616  for (const auto &SC : SpecConsts)
4617  FwdDeclEmitter.Visit(SC.first);
4618  O << "\n";
4619 
4620  // Remove duplicates.
4621  std::sort(SpecConsts.begin(), SpecConsts.end(),
4622  [](const SpecConstID &SC1, const SpecConstID &SC2) {
4623  // Sort by string IDs for stable spec consts order in the
4624  // header.
4625  return SC1.second.compare(SC2.second) < 0;
4626  });
4627  SpecConstID *End =
4628  std::unique(SpecConsts.begin(), SpecConsts.end(),
4629  [](const SpecConstID &SC1, const SpecConstID &SC2) {
4630  // Here can do faster comparison of types.
4631  return SC1.first == SC2.first;
4632  });
4633 
4634  O << "// Specialization constants IDs:\n";
4635  for (const auto &P : llvm::make_range(SpecConsts.begin(), End)) {
4636  O << "template <> struct sycl::detail::SpecConstantInfo<";
4637  SYCLKernelNameTypePrinter Printer(O, Policy);
4638  Printer.Visit(P.first);
4639  O << "> {\n";
4640  O << " static constexpr const char* getName() {\n";
4641  O << " return \"" << P.second << "\";\n";
4642  O << " }\n";
4643  O << "};\n";
4644  }
4645  }
4646 
4647  O << "// Forward declarations of templated kernel function types:\n";
4648  for (const KernelDesc &K : KernelDescs)
4649  if (!K.IsUnnamedKernel)
4650  FwdDeclEmitter.Visit(K.NameType);
4651  O << "\n";
4652 
4653  O << "__SYCL_INLINE_NAMESPACE(cl) {\n";
4654  O << "namespace sycl {\n";
4655  O << "namespace detail {\n";
4656 
4657  // Generate declaration of variable of type __sycl_device_global_registration
4658  // whose sole purpose is to run its constructor before the application's
4659  // main() function.
4660 
4661  if (NeedToEmitDeviceGlobalRegistration) {
4662  O << "namespace {\n";
4663 
4664  O << "class __sycl_device_global_registration {\n";
4665  O << "public:\n";
4666  O << " __sycl_device_global_registration() noexcept;\n";
4667  O << "};\n";
4668  O << "__sycl_device_global_registration __sycl_device_global_registrar;\n";
4669 
4670  O << "} // namespace\n";
4671 
4672  O << "\n";
4673  }
4674 
4675  O << "// names of all kernels defined in the corresponding source\n";
4676  O << "static constexpr\n";
4677  O << "const char* const kernel_names[] = {\n";
4678 
4679  for (unsigned I = 0; I < KernelDescs.size(); I++) {
4680  O << " \"" << KernelDescs[I].Name << "\"";
4681 
4682  if (I < KernelDescs.size() - 1)
4683  O << ",";
4684  O << "\n";
4685  }
4686  O << "};\n\n";
4687 
4688  O << "// array representing signatures of all kernels defined in the\n";
4689  O << "// corresponding source\n";
4690  O << "static constexpr\n";
4691  O << "const kernel_param_desc_t kernel_signatures[] = {\n";
4692 
4693  for (unsigned I = 0; I < KernelDescs.size(); I++) {
4694  auto &K = KernelDescs[I];
4695  O << " //--- " << K.Name << "\n";
4696 
4697  for (const auto &P : K.Params) {
4698  std::string TyStr = paramKind2Str(P.Kind);
4699  O << " { kernel_param_kind_t::" << TyStr << ", ";
4700  O << P.Info << ", " << P.Offset << " },\n";
4701  }
4702  O << "\n";
4703  }
4704 
4705  // Sentinel in place for 2 reasons:
4706  // 1- to make sure we don't get a warning because this collection is empty.
4707  // 2- to provide an obvious value that we can use when debugging to see that
4708  // we have left valid kernel information.
4709  // integer-field values are negative, so they are obviously invalid, notable
4710  // enough to 'stick out' and 'negative enough' to not be easily reachable by a
4711  // mathematical error.
4712  O << " { kernel_param_kind_t::kind_invalid, -987654321, -987654321 }, \n";
4713  O << "};\n\n";
4714 
4715  O << "// Specializations of KernelInfo for kernel function types:\n";
4716  unsigned CurStart = 0;
4717 
4718  for (const KernelDesc &K : KernelDescs) {
4719  const size_t N = K.Params.size();
4720  PresumedLoc PLoc = S.Context.getSourceManager().getPresumedLoc(
4721  S.Context.getSourceManager()
4722  .getExpansionRange(K.KernelLocation)
4723  .getEnd());
4724  if (K.IsUnnamedKernel) {
4725  O << "template <> struct KernelInfoData<";
4726  OutputStableNameInChars(O, K.StableName);
4727  O << "> {\n";
4728  } else {
4729  O << "template <> struct KernelInfo<";
4730  SYCLKernelNameTypePrinter Printer(O, Policy);
4731  Printer.Visit(K.NameType);
4732  O << "> {\n";
4733  }
4734  O << " __SYCL_DLL_LOCAL\n";
4735  O << " static constexpr const char* getName() { return \"" << K.Name
4736  << "\"; }\n";
4737  O << " __SYCL_DLL_LOCAL\n";
4738  O << " static constexpr unsigned getNumParams() { return " << N << "; }\n";
4739  O << " __SYCL_DLL_LOCAL\n";
4740  O << " static constexpr const kernel_param_desc_t& ";
4741  O << "getParamDesc(unsigned i) {\n";
4742  O << " return kernel_signatures[i+" << CurStart << "];\n";
4743  O << " }\n";
4744  O << " __SYCL_DLL_LOCAL\n";
4745  O << " static constexpr bool isESIMD() { return " << K.IsESIMDKernel
4746  << "; }\n";
4747  O << " __SYCL_DLL_LOCAL\n";
4748  O << " static constexpr const char* getFileName() {\n";
4749  O << "#ifndef NDEBUG\n";
4750  O << " return \""
4751  << std::string(PLoc.getFilename())
4752  .substr(std::string(PLoc.getFilename()).find_last_of("/\\") + 1);
4753  O << "\";\n";
4754  O << "#else\n";
4755  O << " return \"\";\n";
4756  O << "#endif\n";
4757  O << " }\n";
4758  O << " __SYCL_DLL_LOCAL\n";
4759  O << " static constexpr const char* getFunctionName() {\n";
4760  O << "#ifndef NDEBUG\n";
4761  O << " return \"";
4762  SYCLKernelNameTypePrinter Printer(O, Policy);
4763  Printer.Visit(K.NameType);
4764  O << "\";\n";
4765  O << "#else\n";
4766  O << " return \"\";\n";
4767  O << "#endif\n";
4768  O << " }\n";
4769  O << " __SYCL_DLL_LOCAL\n";
4770  O << " static constexpr unsigned getLineNumber() {\n";
4771  O << "#ifndef NDEBUG\n";
4772  O << " return " << PLoc.getLine() << ";\n";
4773  O << "#else\n";
4774  O << " return 0;\n";
4775  O << "#endif\n";
4776  O << " }\n";
4777  O << " __SYCL_DLL_LOCAL\n";
4778  O << " static constexpr unsigned getColumnNumber() {\n";
4779  O << "#ifndef NDEBUG\n";
4780  O << " return " << PLoc.getColumn() << ";\n";
4781  O << "#else\n";
4782  O << " return 0;\n";
4783  O << "#endif\n";
4784  O << " }\n";
4785  StringRef ReturnType =
4786  (S.Context.getTargetInfo().getInt64Type() == TargetInfo::SignedLong)
4787  ? "long"
4788  : "long long";
4789  O << " // Returns the size of the kernel object in bytes.\n";
4790  O << " __SYCL_DLL_LOCAL\n";
4791  O << " static constexpr " << ReturnType << " getKernelSize() { return "
4792  << K.ObjSize << "; }\n";
4793  O << "};\n";
4794  CurStart += N;
4795  }
4796  O << "\n";
4797  O << "} // namespace detail\n";
4798  O << "} // namespace sycl\n";
4799  O << "} // __SYCL_INLINE_NAMESPACE(cl)\n";
4800  O << "\n";
4801 }
4802 
4803 bool SYCLIntegrationHeader::emit(StringRef IntHeaderName) {
4804  if (IntHeaderName.empty())
4805  return false;
4806  int IntHeaderFD = 0;
4807  std::error_code EC =
4808  llvm::sys::fs::openFileForWrite(IntHeaderName, IntHeaderFD);
4809  if (EC) {
4810  llvm::errs() << "Error: " << EC.message() << "\n";
4811  // compilation will fail on absent include file - don't need to fail here
4812  return false;
4813  }
4814  llvm::raw_fd_ostream Out(IntHeaderFD, true /*close in destructor*/);
4815  emit(Out);
4816  return true;
4817 }

4849 void SYCLIntegrationFooter::addVarDecl(const VarDecl *VD) {
4850  // Variable template declaration can result in an error case of 'nullptr'
4851  // here.
4852  if (!VD)
4853  return;
4854  // Skip the dependent version of these variables, we only care about them
4855  // after instantiation.
4856  if (VD->getDeclContext()->isDependentContext())
4857  return;
4858 
4859  // Skip partial specializations of a variable template, treat other variable
4860  // template instantiations as a VarDecl.
4861  if (isa<VarTemplatePartialSpecializationDecl>(VD))
4862  return;
4863  // Step 1: ensure that this is of the correct type template specialization.
4864  if (!Util::isSyclSpecIdType(VD->getType()) &&
4865  !S.isTypeDecoratedWithDeclAttribute<SYCLDeviceGlobalAttr>(
4866  VD->getType())) {
4867  // Handle the case where this could be a deduced type, such as a deduction
4868  // guide. We have to do this here since this function, unlike most of the
4869  // rest of this file, is called during Sema instead of after it. We will
4870  // also have to filter out after deduction later.
4871  QualType Ty = VD->getType().getCanonicalType();
4872  if (!Ty->isUndeducedType())
4873  return;
4874  }
4875  // Step 2: ensure that this is a static member, or a namespace-scope.
4876  // Note that isLocalVarDeclorParm excludes thread-local and static-local
4877  // intentionally, as there is no way to 'spell' one of those in the
4878  // specialization. We just don't generate the specialization for those, and
4879  // let an error happen during host compilation.
4880  if (!VD->hasGlobalStorage() || VD->isLocalVarDeclOrParm())
4881  return;
4882  // Step 3: Add to collection.
4883  GlobalVars.push_back(VD);
4884 }

4886 // Post-compile integration header support.
4887 bool SYCLIntegrationFooter::emit(StringRef IntHeaderName) {
4888  if (IntHeaderName.empty())
4889  return false;
4890  int IntHeaderFD = 0;
4891  std::error_code EC =
4892  llvm::sys::fs::openFileForWrite(IntHeaderName, IntHeaderFD);
4893  if (EC) {
4894  llvm::errs() << "Error: " << EC.message() << "\n";
4895  // compilation will fail on absent include file - don't need to fail here
4896  return false;
4897  }
4898  llvm::raw_fd_ostream Out(IntHeaderFD, true /*close in destructor*/);
4899  return emit(Out);
4900 }
4901 
4902 template <typename BeforeFn, typename AfterFn>
4903 static void PrintNSHelper(BeforeFn Before, AfterFn After, raw_ostream &OS,
4904  const DeclContext *DC) {
4905  if (DC->isTranslationUnit())
4906  return;
4907 
4908  const auto *CurDecl = cast<Decl>(DC);
4909  // Ensure we are in the canonical version, so that we know we have the 'full'
4910  // name of the thing.
4911  CurDecl = CurDecl->getCanonicalDecl();
4912 
4913  // We are intentionally skipping linkage decls and record decls. Namespaces
4914  // can appear in a linkage decl, but not a record decl, so we don't have to
4915  // worry about the names getting messed up from that. We handle record decls
4916  // later when printing the name of the thing.
4917  const auto *NS = dyn_cast<NamespaceDecl>(CurDecl);
4918  if (NS)
4919  Before(OS, NS);
4920 
4921  if (const DeclContext *NewDC = CurDecl->getDeclContext())
4922  PrintNSHelper(Before, After, OS, NewDC);
4923 
4924  if (NS)
4925  After(OS, NS);
4926 }
4927 
4928 static void PrintNamespaces(raw_ostream &OS, const DeclContext *DC) {
4929  PrintNSHelper([](raw_ostream &OS, const NamespaceDecl *NS) {},
4930  [](raw_ostream &OS, const NamespaceDecl *NS) {
4931  if (NS->isInline())
4932  OS << "inline ";
4933  OS << "namespace ";
4934  if (!NS->isAnonymousNamespace())
4935  OS << NS->getName() << " ";
4936  OS << "{\n";
4937  },
4938  OS, DC);
4939 }
4940 
4941 static void PrintNSClosingBraces(raw_ostream &OS, const DeclContext *DC) {
4942  PrintNSHelper(
4943  [](raw_ostream &OS, const NamespaceDecl *NS) {
4944  OS << "} // ";
4945  if (NS->isInline())
4946  OS << "inline ";
4947 
4948  OS << "namespace ";
4949  if (!NS->isAnonymousNamespace())
4950  OS << NS->getName();
4951 
4952  OS << '\n';
4953  },
4954  [](raw_ostream &OS, const NamespaceDecl *NS) {}, OS, DC);
4955 }
4956 
4957 static std::string EmitShim(raw_ostream &OS, unsigned &ShimCounter,
4958  const std::string &LastShim,
4959  const NamespaceDecl *AnonNS) {
4960  std::string NewShimName =
4961  "__sycl_detail::__shim_" + std::to_string(ShimCounter) + "()";
4962  // Print opening-namespace
4963  PrintNamespaces(OS, Decl::castToDeclContext(AnonNS));
4964  OS << "namespace __sycl_detail {\n";
4965  OS << "static constexpr decltype(" << LastShim << ") &__shim_" << ShimCounter
4966  << "() {\n";
4967  OS << " return " << LastShim << ";\n";
4968  OS << "}\n";
4969  OS << "} // namespace __sycl_detail\n";
4970  PrintNSClosingBraces(OS, Decl::castToDeclContext(AnonNS));
4971 
4972  ++ShimCounter;
4973  return NewShimName;
4974 }
4975 
4976 // Emit the list of shims required for a DeclContext, calls itself recursively.
4977 static void EmitShims(raw_ostream &OS, unsigned &ShimCounter,
4978  const DeclContext *DC, std::string &NameForLastShim) {
4979  if (DC->isTranslationUnit()) {
4980  NameForLastShim = "::" + NameForLastShim;
4981  return;
4982  }
4983 
4984  const auto *CurDecl = cast<Decl>(DC)->getCanonicalDecl();
4985 
4986  // We skip linkage decls, since they don't modify the Qualified name.
4987  if (const auto *RD = dyn_cast<RecordDecl>(CurDecl)) {
4988  NameForLastShim = RD->getNameAsString() + "::" + NameForLastShim;
4989  } else if (const auto *ND = dyn_cast<NamespaceDecl>(CurDecl)) {
4990  if (ND->isAnonymousNamespace()) {
4991  // Print current shim, reset 'name for last shim'.
4992  NameForLastShim = EmitShim(OS, ShimCounter, NameForLastShim, ND);
4993  } else {
4994  NameForLastShim = ND->getNameAsString() + "::" + NameForLastShim;
4995  }
4996  } else {
4997  // FIXME: I don't believe there are other declarations that these variables
4998  // could possibly find themselves in. LinkageDecls don't change the
4999  // qualified name, so there is nothing to do here. At one point we should
5000  // probably convince ourselves that this is entire list and remove this
5001  // comment.
5002  assert((isa<LinkageSpecDecl, ExternCContextDecl>(CurDecl)) &&
5003  "Unhandled decl type");
5004  }
5005 
5006  EmitShims(OS, ShimCounter, CurDecl->getDeclContext(), NameForLastShim);
5007 }
5008 
5009 // Emit the list of shims required for a variable declaration.
5010 // Returns a string containing the FQN of the 'top most' shim, including its
5011 // function call parameters.
5012 static std::string EmitShims(raw_ostream &OS, unsigned &ShimCounter,
5013  PrintingPolicy &Policy, const VarDecl *VD) {
5014  if (!VD->isInAnonymousNamespace())
5015  return "";
5016  std::string RelativeName;
5017  llvm::raw_string_ostream stream(RelativeName);
5018  VD->getNameForDiagnostic(stream, Policy, false);
5019  stream.flush();
5020 
5021  EmitShims(OS, ShimCounter, VD->getDeclContext(), RelativeName);
5022  return RelativeName;
5023 }
5024 
5025 bool SYCLIntegrationFooter::emit(raw_ostream &OS) {
5026  PrintingPolicy Policy{S.getLangOpts()};
5027  Policy.adjustForCPlusPlusFwdDecl();
5028  Policy.SuppressTypedefs = true;
5029  Policy.SuppressUnwrittenScope = true;
5030 
5031  llvm::SmallSet<const VarDecl *, 8> Visited;
5032  bool EmittedFirstSpecConstant = false;
5033  bool DeviceGlobalsEmitted = false;
5034 
5035  // Used to uniquely name the 'shim's as we generate the names in each
5036  // anonymous namespace.
5037  unsigned ShimCounter = 0;
5038 
5039  std::string DeviceGlobalsBuf;
5040  llvm::raw_string_ostream DeviceGlobOS(DeviceGlobalsBuf);
5041  for (const VarDecl *VD : GlobalVars) {
5042  VD = VD->getCanonicalDecl();
5043 
5044  // Skip if this isn't a SpecIdType or DeviceGlobal. This can happen if it
5045  // was a deduced type.
5046  if (!Util::isSyclSpecIdType(VD->getType()) &&
5047  !S.isTypeDecoratedWithDeclAttribute<SYCLDeviceGlobalAttr>(
5048  VD->getType()))
5049  continue;
5050 
5051  // Skip if we've already visited this.
5052  if (llvm::find(Visited, VD) != Visited.end())
5053  continue;
5054 
5055  // We only want to emit the #includes if we have a variable that needs
5056  // them, so emit this one on the first time through the loop.
5057  if (!EmittedFirstSpecConstant && !DeviceGlobalsEmitted)
5058  OS << "#include <CL/sycl/detail/defines_elementary.hpp>\n";
5059 
5060  Visited.insert(VD);
5061  std::string TopShim = EmitShims(OS, ShimCounter, Policy, VD);
5062  if (S.isTypeDecoratedWithDeclAttribute<SYCLDeviceGlobalAttr>(
5063  VD->getType())) {
5064  DeviceGlobalsEmitted = true;
5065  DeviceGlobOS << "device_global_map::add(";
5066  DeviceGlobOS << "(void *)&";
5067  if (VD->isInAnonymousNamespace()) {
5068  DeviceGlobOS << TopShim;
5069  } else {
5070  DeviceGlobOS << "::";
5071  VD->getNameForDiagnostic(DeviceGlobOS, Policy, true);
5072  }
5073  DeviceGlobOS << ", \"";
5074  DeviceGlobOS << SYCLUniqueStableIdExpr::ComputeName(S.getASTContext(),
5075  VD);
5076  DeviceGlobOS << "\");\n";
5077  } else {
5078  EmittedFirstSpecConstant = true;
5079  OS << "__SYCL_INLINE_NAMESPACE(cl) {\n";
5080  OS << "namespace sycl {\n";
5081  OS << "namespace detail {\n";
5082  OS << "template<>\n";
5083  OS << "inline const char *get_spec_constant_symbolic_ID_impl<";
5084 
5085  if (VD->isInAnonymousNamespace()) {
5086  OS << TopShim;
5087  } else {
5088  OS << "::";
5089  VD->getNameForDiagnostic(OS, Policy, true);
5090  }
5091 
5092  OS << ">() {\n";
5093  OS << " return \"";
5094  OS << SYCLUniqueStableIdExpr::ComputeName(S.getASTContext(), VD);
5095  OS << "\";\n";
5096  OS << "}\n";
5097  OS << "} // namespace detail\n";
5098  OS << "} // namespace sycl\n";
5099  OS << "} // __SYCL_INLINE_NAMESPACE(cl)\n";
5100  }
5101  }
5102 
5103  if (EmittedFirstSpecConstant)
5104  OS << "#include <CL/sycl/detail/spec_const_integration.hpp>\n";
5105 
5106  if (DeviceGlobalsEmitted) {
5107  OS << "#include <CL/sycl/detail/device_global_map.hpp>\n";
5108  DeviceGlobOS.flush();
5109  OS << "namespace sycl::detail {\n";
5110  OS << "namespace {\n";
5111  OS << "__sycl_device_global_registration::__sycl_device_global_"
5112  "registration() noexcept {\n";
5113  OS << DeviceGlobalsBuf;
5114  OS << "}\n";
5115  OS << "} // namespace (unnamed)\n";
5116  OS << "} // namespace sycl::detail\n";
5117 
5118  S.getSyclIntegrationHeader().addDeviceGlobalRegistration();
5119  }
5120  return true;
5121 }

5123 // -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
5124 // Utility class methods
5125 // -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
5126 bool Util::isSyclSpecialType(const QualType Ty) {
5127  const CXXRecordDecl *RecTy = Ty->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
5128  if (!RecTy)
5129  return false;
5130  return RecTy->hasAttr<SYCLSpecialClassAttr>();
5131 }

5133 bool Util::isSyclSpecConstantType(QualType Ty) {
5134  std::array<DeclContextDesc, 6> Scopes = {
5135  Util::MakeDeclContextDesc(Decl::Kind::Namespace, "cl"),
5136  Util::MakeDeclContextDesc(Decl::Kind::Namespace, "sycl"),
5137  Util::MakeDeclContextDesc(Decl::Kind::Namespace, "ext"),
5138  Util::MakeDeclContextDesc(Decl::Kind::Namespace, "oneapi"),
5139  Util::MakeDeclContextDesc(Decl::Kind::Namespace, "experimental"),
5140  Util::MakeDeclContextDesc(Decl::Kind::ClassTemplateSpecialization,
5141  "spec_constant")};
5142  return matchQualifiedTypeName(Ty, Scopes);

5208 
5209 bool Util::matchContext(const DeclContext *Ctx,
5210  ArrayRef<Util::DeclContextDesc> Scopes) {
5211  // The idea: check the declaration context chain starting from the item
5212  // itself. At each step check the context is of expected kind
5213  // (namespace) and name.
5214  StringRef Name = "";
5215 
5216  for (const auto &Scope : llvm::reverse(Scopes)) {
5217  Decl::Kind DK = Ctx->getDeclKind();
5218  if (DK != Scope.first)
5219  return false;
5220 
5221  switch (DK) {
5222  case Decl::Kind::ClassTemplateSpecialization:
5223  // ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl inherits from CXXRecordDecl
5224  case Decl::Kind::CXXRecord:
5225  Name = cast<CXXRecordDecl>(Ctx)->getName();
5226  break;
5227  case Decl::Kind::Namespace:
5228  Name = cast<NamespaceDecl>(Ctx)->getName();
5229  break;
5230  default:
5231  llvm_unreachable("matchContext: decl kind not supported");
5232  }
5233  if (Name != Scope.second)
5234  return false;
5235  Ctx = Ctx->getParent();
5236  }
5237  return Ctx->isTranslationUnit() ||
5238  (Ctx->isExternCXXContext() &&
5239  Ctx->getEnclosingNamespaceContext()->isTranslationUnit());
5240 }
5241 
5242 bool Util::matchQualifiedTypeName(QualType Ty,
5243  ArrayRef<Util::DeclContextDesc> Scopes) {
5244  const CXXRecordDecl *RecTy = Ty->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
5245 
5246  if (!RecTy)
5247  return false; // only classes/structs supported
5248  const auto *Ctx = cast<DeclContext>(RecTy);
5249  return Util::matchContext(Ctx, Scopes);
5250 }
